title: french country chicken
directions: In 8 x 12-inch baking dish, combine vegetables and 1/2 can French fried onions; arrange chicken breasts on vegetables.
In small bowl, combine wine, bouillon, garlic salt and pepper; pour over chicken and vegetables.
Sprinkle chicken with paprika.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 40 minutes or until chicken is done.
Baste chicken with wine sauce and top with remaining onions; bake, uncovered, 3 minutes or until onions are golden brown.

title: golden glow salad for diabetics
directions: Mix orange gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 2 cups juice of	pineapple.
(If you do not have enough from pineapple,	add water
to make 2 cups.) Add salt.
Then add carrots and pineapple. Chill until congealed.

title: hawaiian ham sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on bread.

title: cherry pineapple delight
directions: Grease and flour pan.
Put pineapple in pan, then cherry pie filling. Sprinkle cake mix over this. Sprinkle nuts on top of this. Pour oleo over entire mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: swedish pecan balls
directions: Blend sugar and oleo.
Add flour and vanilla.
Stir in nuts. Bake at 235° for 30 minutes. While hot, roll in 4x sugar.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Mix; pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: crumbs for pies
directions: Mix well.
This can be mixed in larger quantities and stored in refrigerator for later use.

title: marlow dessert(frozen)
directions: Mix marshmallows and pineapple and refrigerate overnight.
Whip the cream.
Fold in powdered sugar and vanilla.
Fold into pineapple mixture.
Pour in container and freeze.
Also good with fresh strawberries.

title: meal-in-a-loaf
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper in skillet.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cut Italian bread in half, horizontally, giving a top and bottom section.
Remove doughy center of both the top and bottom sections by pinching it out.
Save the pieces of bread in mixing bowl.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix 5 to 10 minutes in blender or food processor. Stir in 1 teaspoon poppy seed.

title: country scalloped corn
directions: Place corn in a shallow casserole.
Top with cheese and cracker crumbs.
Combine egg, salt and milk and pour over cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: vegetable ball
directions: Squeeze out all juice; mix together and roll in nuts.

title: manicotti crepes
directions: Crepes:
Stir all together until smooth.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Melt a little butter in a 7-inch skillet.
Add crepe batter to just cover bottom of skillet.
Tilt to spread to edges.
Cook until lightly browned and turn.
Store crepes between layers of waxed paper to prevent sticking.
Makes approximately 19 crepes.

title: harvest casserole
directions: Saute hamburger and onion, drain.
Saute celery in a small amount of butter over low heat.
Mix all ingredients and spoon into a large casserole.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Mix sugar, cereal, oil and pumpkin in large bowl. Let stand 10 minutes.
Stir in egg whites until well blended. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pan; spread evenly. Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel and core apples; cut into chunks in bowl.
Cover with sugar for 10 minutes.
Melt butter; stir into apple mixture.
Add egg, nuts and raisins.
Sift in flour, baking soda, spices and water.
Bake in greased 8-inch pan at 375° for 45 minutes.
Cool and serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: pepperidge farm stuffed pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in nonstick skillet, remove.
Melt 1 stick margarine in skillet.
Add onion, celery and apple.
Saute until tender.
Add 1 cup water plus 3 tablespoons apple juice, stuffing mix and seasoning to skillet; mix well.
Place 4 chops in baking dish.
Spoon stuffing on each.
Top with remaining chops.
Secure with toothpicks.
Cover with foil. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Uncover, add beef bouillon mixed with 6 ounces water, soy sauce and wine.
Bake additional 15 to 20 minutes, baste as needed.

title: cheese dip
directions: Combine spices in small mixing bowl. Melt butter. Add flour and stir until thick. Remove from heat and add spice mixture; mix well. Add catsup and jalapeno juice and return to heat. Slowly add milk, stirring continuously. Add Velveeta. When melted, serve with tortilla chips. Keep warm.

title: green goddess dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in order listed.
Chill and pour generously over coarsely torn mixed salad greens.
Add more salt and pepper as needed.

title: burnt sugar cake
directions: Mix ingredients together as listed; beat until batter looks like whipped cream.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cherry pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla and fold in Cool Whip. Put mixture into cooled crusts.
Place layer of cherry pie filling on top.
Chill and serve with garnish of Cool Whip.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter until vegetables are clear. Cook broccoli by package directions; drain well.
Mix broccoli and soup with cheese.
Add celery and onions.
Stir in rice and seasons and mix well.
Put into greased casserole dish and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can be mixed ahead of time and frozen.

title: hot sauce
directions: In a medium pan, bring to boil sugar, vinegar, oil and catsup. Cut into small pieces hot peppers, onions and mangos, wieners if desired.
In a large kettle, bring to boil hot peppers, onions, mangos, mushrooms, tomato sauce, tomato paste and wieners.
Combine sauce mixture to these ingredients and bring to a boil.
Boil 30 minutes or until peppers and onions are done.
Put into pint jars and seal.
Yields approximately 21 to 22 pints.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Chill.
Roll and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 400°.

title: green eggs and ham
directions: Follow cooking instructions for rice.
Cook (fry) egg.
Fry Spam.
Cut both into small pieces and add to rice.
Mix and heat a few minutes.
Serve with your favorite vegetable.

title: oatmeal cheese cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients; bake at 350° for 12 to 13 minutes.
Remove cookies from cookie sheet at once after baking.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, 1 stick oleo and sugar.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat 20 minutes.
Mix confectioners sugar, 2 sticks oleo, eggs and vanilla.
Spread over crumbs.
Spread pineapple over mixture.
Add sliced bananas over top.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Top with cherries and nuts.
Chill.

title: 1-2-3 cobbler(8 servings)
directions: Melt margarine in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix milk, flour, sugar and baking powder.
Mix and pour into pan over melted margarine. Spoon fruit over the top and bake in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: fish fillets on curried rice
directions: Mix curry powder, onion powder and margarine in skillet.
Stir in water.
Cover and heat to boiling.
Stir in rice; reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Arrange fillets on rice.
Sprinkle peas around fillets.
Cover and simmer until liquid is absorbed, 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with sliced almonds.
Makes 2 servings.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cream sugar and shortening. Add eggs; blend well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with milk and vanilla. Add coffee.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool; frost with favorite icing.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together using a mixer.

title: dusky maiden cake
directions: Sift the first 7 ingredients.
Add the raisins, nuts, crushed pineapple (juice and pulp) and melted butter; mix well.
Bake slowly in round cake pan (similar to angel food pan) at 325° for 1 hour and 20 to 30 minutes.

title: suzy-q cake
directions: Bake according to package directions in 8 inch cake pans. Let cool on racks. Split both layers so that there are 4 halves. Assemble with Suzy-Q filling in between each layer and top of cake.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Halve pineapple slices. Melt butter in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Add brown sugar and 1 tablespoon of the reserved pineapple syrup.
Add water to remaining syrup to make 1/2 cup.
Arrange pineapple in bottom of pan.
Place cherry half in center of each slice.
Cream together shortening and sugar until light.
Add egg and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add alternately with 1/2 cup reserved pineapple syrup, beating after each addition.
Spread over pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes; invert on plate.
Serve warm.

title: raspberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water and add applesauce and raspberries. Pour in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Refrigerate.
Combine marshmallows and sour cream.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Whip cream and fold into marshmallow mixture.
Spread on top of raspberry gelatin mixture.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs one at a time, beating after each. Add all the other ingredients. Mix well. Bake in three greased and floured cake pans.

title: cheese cocktail biscuits
directions: Mix cheese, butter, salt and red pepper well.
Add flour; shape into balls, size of marble.
Flatten; put 1/2 pecan on each. Sprinkle with 10x sugar.
Bake in oven at 400° for 10 minutes. (They may incline to crumble when eaten hot but not so when cool.)

title: marinated cabbage
directions: Arrange cabbage and onion in layers.
Pour sugar over top. In a saucepan, bring to a boil the vinegar, oil, mustard, celery seed and salt.
Pour hot mixture at once over the cabbage and onion.
Let stand at least 6 hours before using.
Will save 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: man on the moon cake
directions: Mix the first 9 ingredients, then add the apples and nuts. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Slice sausage about 1/2-inch thick and brown in oil.
Drain most of oil off.
Add onions, garlic, carrots and spices.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add zucchini, tomatoes with liquid, bouillon, cabbage, salt and pepper.
Bring soup to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for about an hour.
Add beans with the liquid and cook another 20 minutes.
Serves 8.
Enjoy!

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Fold together all ingredients and set in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Put in freezer overnight.
Remove from freezer several minutes before serving.
Put on 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: corn supreme
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 to 45 minutes.

title: cream of egg drop soup
directions: In a large soup pot, scald the milk.
Gradually add the eggs, stirring constantly.
Add salt and pepper.
Garnish each serving with toasted bread crumbs and serve.
Yields 1 1/2 quarts.

title: spicy pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and beat until thick and foamy.
Beat in oil and vanilla.
Add pineapple.
Sift flour mixture and add to batter.
Stir in zucchini.
Add nuts and stir gently until blended.
Divide batter into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour for 2 pans or 40 minutes if using 3 pans.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes, then cool on rack.
Serve with butter or cream cheese.
Yields 2 large loaves or 3 small loaves.

title: raisin puff cookies
directions: In a saucepan, cook raisins in water until water is gone.
Cream shortening and sugar, add eggs.
Sift flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and raisins.
Roll into walnut-sized balls, roll in a cinnamon and sugar mix.
Place on cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven for 9 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: uncooked relish
directions: Put each vegetable through food chopper using coarse blade.
If vegetables are covered with liquid, drain off and discard liquid. Measure each vegetable after chopping.
Mix vegetables with the salt and let stand overnight.
Next morning, drain off as much liquid as possible and discard.
Add spices, sugar and vinegar to drained vegetables and mix well.
Pack into jars and seal at once.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix cornstarch in water.
Add to pineapple, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Put in pan.
Sprinkle cinnamon and butter over top. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: blueberry sour cream pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; add egg and beat well. Spoon half of mixture into crust. Combine berries and 1/2 cup brown sugar and spread evenly over sour cream mixture. Top with remaining sour cream mixture. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Chill several hours and serve.

title: salmon or tuna patties
directions: Drain liquid from tuna or salmon and place in small bowl; add baking powder and mix well.
Flake fish and add to bowl with enough crumbs to be able to form into patties.
Bake or fry, as desired.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish.

title: strawberry trifle(sugar-free)
directions: Tear angel food cake into bite-size pieces and layer into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Dissolve gelatin in one cup of boiling water. Do not add cold.
Add strawberries to this mixture, then pour over cake.
Slice bananas and add to top.
Refrigerate this while you make pudding.
Make pudding according to directions on package, using skim milk.
Pour over cake.
Top with Cool Whip. Garnish with fresh strawberries.
Makes 15 servings.
Counts as 1/2 fruit exchange, 1 bread exchange and 1/2 fat exchange.

title: granny rolls
directions: Mix yeast with warm water and set aside.
Warm milk and set aside.
In large bowl, mix together flour, sugar and salt.
Add oil, cold water, warm milk and yeast.
Mix slowly but thoroughly. Knead on floured surface 2 to 3 times.
Pinch off small balls, then smash with fingertips making a round patty; cut into 2 to 3 parts.
Deep-fry in hot oil 3 to 4 pieces at a time.
Cook until golden brown.
Or you could take a spoon and drop them in the oil, whichever is easier for you.

title: amish dressing
directions: In a large mixing bowl, put bread cubes, potatoes, carrots, onion and parsley.
Add 6 eggs, well beaten.
Then add the liquid. Then add 1 pint or more cooked diced chicken and salt, pepper and sage to taste.
Toss lightly.
The dressing may be cooked in a well buttered skillet or baked in a roaster in the oven.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar together until light and creamy.
Beat the eggs slightly.
Combine with bananas and buttermilk or yogurt.
Sift together all the dry ingredients and add to wet ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Put into oiled 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until tested done.
Let cool on rack.

title: whipped cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs one at a time.
Mix with 1 cup flour and 1/3 whipping cream.
Repeat 3 times, mixing well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Pour in tube pan (greased). Put in cold oven at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: crab casserole
directions: Mix ingredients until well mashed.
Add 4 large tablespoons mayonnaise.
Add hot sauce and Worcestershire sauce to taste.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Makes 2 pies.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Beat egg whites adding 1 heaping tablespoon sugar per egg white.
Beat well after adding sugar.

title: frozen lemon salad
directions: Prepare pudding according to directions.
Blend in other ingredients.
Freeze until firm.

title: speedy chocolate fudge
directions: Cook condensed milk, chocolate and salt over rapidly boiling water until thick, about 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Turn into buttered glass dish (9 x 13-inch).
Chill for a few hours before cutting.

title: pear relish(yields 11 pints)
directions: Cover the pears, onions, bell peppers, hot peppers and salt with water and let stand overnight.
Drain the next morning.
Run clear water over mixture.

title: never-fail divinity
directions: Combine water, sugar, cream of tartar and salt.
Do not stir. Bring to a rolling boil and boil until candy thermometer reaches 248°.
Place Marshmallow Creme in small bowl.
Beat at low speed with electric mixer while gradually pouring in hot syrup.
Add vanilla.
Beat until candy loses its gloss and holds its shape when dropped by a spoon.
If mixture underbeaten, it will not hold its shape and if it is overbeaten, it becomes dry.
Add nuts.
Drop from spoon onto waxed paper.
Cool and store.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: no-fuss meatballs
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients. Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.

title: low-fat whole wheat chocolate chippers
directions: Combine margarine, brown sugar, egg whites and vanilla extract with electric mixer until smooth.
In a separate bowl combine the flour and baking soda.
Add the flour mixture to margarine mixture and mix well.
Stir the remaining ingredients.
Coat baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls onto baking sheet, placing them 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake at 300° for about 16 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool cookies on pan for 1 minute.
Then transfer the cookies to wire racks and cool completely.
Store in airtight container.

title: chicken liver wrap-a-rounds
directions: Cut chicken livers into about 20 pieces.
Combine dressing and garlic salt.
Marinate livers in dressing for 15 minutes.
Wrap bacon slices around each piece of liver; fasten with a wooden toothpick.
Place on a shallow baking pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 50 minutes, until bacon is crisp.
Serve hot.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Pour batter on top of butter. Pour fruit over batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook shells according to directions.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Set aside.

title: microwave nachos
directions: Place tortilla chips in a circle on paper towel-lined 9-inch pie plate.
Top each chip with a few diced green chilies.
Top with shredded cheese.
Sprinkle cheese with taco seasoning mix to taste.
Microwave at 100% (High) for 25 to 30 seconds or until cheese melts.
Give plate a half turn after 15 seconds.
Makes 6 chips.

title: rabbit pie
directions: Cut rabbit into pieces.
Soak in equal parts vinegar and water for 12 to 24 hours. Drain and wipe dry.

title: fig jam(with sure-jell)
directions: In heavy pot put figs, lemon juice, water and Sure-Jell. Bring to a full boil for 1 minute.
Add sugar all at once.
Mix. Bring to a full rolling boil that you can't stir down; stir constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Skim off foam and pour into jars.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Cook uncovered.
Boil for 5 to 6 minutes.
Serve.
Refrigerate any unused portions.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: In double boiler, beat egg with fork, stir in lemon juice, sugar and salt.
Cook, stirring, over hot water about 5 minutes or until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat, cool.
Fold in cream, marshmallows, fruit and pecans.
Chill overnight.

title: novaks
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and flour. Bring to boil for 1-1/2 minutes. Remove from heat and add peanut butter; mix well. Add oatmeal and vanilla. Mix well and drop by spoonfuls on wax paper. Chill until set.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti noodles.
While warm, mix with small bottle of Italian dressing and vinegar.
Let cool.
Add all other ingredients.
Refrigerate until served.

title: gingerbread
directions: Stir together first 6 ingredients.
Make a well and add the oil, then brown sugar and egg.
Mix molasses and boiling water and add to batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: tandy cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients except peanut butter and chocolate.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch well-greased pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and spread with peanut butter. Chill until firm.
Melt chips and spread on top of peanut butter. Chill.
Cut into squares before chocolate is set.

title: bread pudding
directions: Bread bread into small pieces.
Add eggs, sugar, vanilla and milk.
Mix well.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon mixture on top. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Then 45 minutes at 350°.

title: king's potato salad
directions: Boil, peel and	slice
potatoes. While still warm, pour salad dressing over
and	chill.	Chop celery and green onion. Mix rest of	ingredients.
Add
to potatoes, celery and onion. Keep chilled.

title: chicken chalupa
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for tortillas.
Put a layer of broken tortillas in
a large 3-quart baking dish and cover with a layer of chicken mixture.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour or longer if casserole seems too moist.
Serves 8.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix the dry ingredients, then add the rest.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix remaining ingredients together and add cooked sausage.
Pour into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together the sugar, shortening, eggs and bananas. Blend in soda. Add flour. Beat well. Bake in loaf pan for 1 hour in 350 degree oven.

title: ortega rice
directions: Layer half of the rice, Ortega chilies, sour cream and cheese, then layer again with the other half.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: quick yeast bread
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients, then add very warm water. Mix well.
Let rise for 2 hours.
Knead lightly on floured board. Roll 1/4-inch thick. Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
To mashed bananas, add sugar and melted margarine.
Stir in slightly beaten egg.
Mix together dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Stir by hand until just blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool and remove from pan.

title: garden salsa
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 11 ingredients. Cover and refrigerate until serving. Serve with chips. Yields 5 cups.

title: easy chowder
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add the other ingredients and simmer until mixed well.

title: onion dip
directions: Thoroughly combine sour cream and onion soup mix; stir in remaining ingredients.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: sugarless apple cookie
directions: In a saucepan, bring to a boil, then simmer, the first 4 ingredients.
Let cool.
Combine next 4 ingredients.
Stir in first mixture and mix well.
Combine eggs and sweetener and put in batter.
Drop by tablespoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
This is a good recipe for diabetics.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Beat softened cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla until well blended.
Mix together the milk and cornstarch and blend into cream cheese mixture.
Add yogurt and mix well.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until brown around the edges.
Refrigerate and serve cool.
Can top with fresh fruit; strawberries and kiwi are good.

title: mock turkey
directions: Fry hamburger lightly. Put in mixing bowl. Add bread and soup. Mix well.
Put in greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Can add cheese on top.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Put water and margarine in pot; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in flour.
Add eggs.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Let cool 1/2 hour.
Poke with a fork.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Add milk, eggs and onion; stir in Crisco.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot deep fat in which fish has been cooked.
Fry until brown.

title: spaghetti casserole (beef)
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Top casserole with 1/2 cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: oven-fried parmesan chicken
directions: Combine first five ingredients and stir well.
Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Dip chicken in butter, then roll in cracker crumbs and other ingredients.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Have a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish ready.
Mix soup, water, soy sauce and pepper in casserole.
Stir in green beans and 1 cup of crushed crackers.
Cover and bake 20 to 25 minutes until hot.
Uncover and sprinkle with remaining crackers and bake 8 to 10 minutes longer.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grate the cheese and finely chop the artichokes.
Combine all ingredients in a small deep baking dish. Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: canadian chocolate cake
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, add vanilla and beat well.
Sift flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to other mixture, alternately with the sour cream.
Dissolve chocolate in boiling water.
Cool chocolate and water mixture.
Then add to flour mixture and fold in the walnuts.
Bake in a greased pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco mix.
Place on bottom of an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Place chopped tomatoes next.
Place shredded lettuce next.
Place shredded cheese on top.
Dip with tortilla chips.

title: giant shells with meat
directions: In frying pan, brown ground beef and onion in oil.
In a bowl, combine beef and onion with bread crumbs, eggs, Mozzarella cheese, salt, pepper and parsley.
In the meantime, cook shells according to package instructions.
Fill each shell with meat filling.
In baking dish, spread sauce on the bottom.
Arrange filled shells in single layer.
Pour remaining sauce on top of shells.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: meat stuffed peppers
directions: Remove tops and seeds from peppers and parboil for 5 minutes, drain.
Brown onions and ground beef in fat; add tomatoes, corn and seasonings (fresh corn can be used when available).
Stuff peppers and top with buttered crumbs.
Stand upright in greased baking dish.
Add small amount of water.
Cover and bake in 350° oven one hour.

title: eggs v2.02
directions: Cook frozen spinach; don't overcook, and drain well.
Get a large frying pan and saute lots of crushed garlic in real butter, if your conscience and doctor permits, garlic puree is okay.
Did I mention the bacon?
Cook a pound very crispy.
Half will be used in this great dish, the other 8 ounces will be nibbled by you and the inevitable onlookers, believe me.
Beat 6 eggs, with a little milk and add to the spinach in that large frying pan that has the great smelling warm garlic.
Now comes the Parmesan cheese which you should just keep adding and adding until your innate wisdom says enough.
Add some salt, pepper and the drained and crumbled bacon. Taste and cook, cook and taste.

title: norma's baked beans
directions: Mix together.
Cover with 2 slices of bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mom's magic christmas cake
directions: Blend ingredients well.
Pack in buttered and wax paper lined 8 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven until brown, about 40 minutes.
Double recipe for regular sized stem cake pan.

title: grilled cheese supreme(makes 6 sandwiches)
directions: In frypan in 1 tablespoon of oil place meat, onion and celery. Cook until meat is no longer pink and is crumbly and onions are golden.
Use medium heat and stir occasionally.
Add tomato paste, garlic powder, chili powder, horseradish mustard, sugar, white pepper and water (just enough water to moisten).
Turn heat low. Cover and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix jello (dry) with cottage cheese.
Mix in pineapple.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Chill.
Serve and enjoy.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Wash and trim leaf lettuce; leave pieces large.
Dry.
Add onion and salt, then toss lightly.
Add sliced or diced eggs.
Set aside and let rest.

title: nonsticky popcorn balls
directions: Place sugar and butter in skillet and stir until melted and light brown.
Add soda and pour at once over popped corn and form into balls.
These are never sticky.

title: kolacki
directions: Mix butter and cream cheese; add flour.
Roll dough with a little flour and powdered sugar.
Cut in squares.
Use your favorite filling and fold the two ends like a diamond.
Bake in oven at 325° or 350° until lightly colored and done.

title: garden veggies italian style
directions: Combine vegetables in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with oregano. Pour on the tomato sauce.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Top with cheese and bake another 4 to 5 minutes until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings at about 65 calories per serving.

title: rotis de porc a la boulangere(a la maison linda)
directions: Place steak in marinating dish or other dish which seals well. Combine all other ingredients and pour over steak.
Seal and refrigerate at least 4 hours (best overnight), turning the meat over about 1/2 way through the marinating time. Broil about 3-inches from heat, basting frequently.
Depending on the thickness of the meat and how you like meat cooked, it should take about 10 minutes on each side.
Slice thinly on the diagonal.

title: sweet crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients with hands.
Shape into crescents (1/2 teaspoon).
Bake 8 to 10 minutes, turning at 5 minutes time.
After cooling, roll in confectioners sugar.

title: short-cut pan rolls
directions: Combine grits, sugar and salt in a large mixer bowl.
Add water, oil and 2 cups flour.
Beat on low speed for 2 minutes. Add 1 cup flour and yeast.
Beat 1 minute on low speed.
Stir in additional flour to make soft dough.

title: joan's quick and easy dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: sausage grits
directions: Cook sausage until brown (stirring to break up as browning) in heavy skillet; drain well.
Spoon sausage into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine hot grits, cheese and margarine, melted.
Beat eggs and add to milk; then add mixture to grits.
Pour over sausage.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: texas sheet cake or chocolate cookie sheet cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar. Boil together the margarine, water and cocoa or chocolate. Pour over flour mixture while still hot. Mix in remaining ingredients. Pour into a greased 17 1/2 x 11 x 1-inch cookie sheet. Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: fudge
directions: Pour sugar, margarine and evaporated milk in a pot; bring to boil and stir. Boil for 5 to 6 minutes. Take off heat. Stir in vanilla and cocoa powder. Stir until smooth. Put in nuts. Pour it in a pan or cookie sheet with margarine on the bottom (grease or whatever you use). Wait only 10 to 15 minutes and then slice up.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix and serve with vegetables.

title: whiskey cake
directions: Beat all ingredients (except chocolate chips and nuts) together for 2 minutes.
Add chocolate chips and nuts and stir through batter.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: mexican fire and ice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except for 1/3 c. stewed tomato liquid and 1/3 c. cheese.
Put in a baking dish and top with remaining tomato juice and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat or ground chuck with bell pepper and onion.
Add garlic salt to taste (about 1 teaspoon).
Drain fat. Place in a casserole dish.
Spoon cream of mushroom soup over meat.
Place sliced potatoes on top of soup.
Cover and bake in a 400° oven for about 20 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: guacamole layered dip
directions: Combine avocados, lemon juice and dash of garlic salt (may use the package mix from store).
Layer ingredients in clear, glass dish in the order printed.

title: easy mushroom crescent snacks
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown mushrooms in oleo; stir in garlic powder, onion, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook until liquid evaporates; set aside.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Put all together in a 2 quart greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix carrots and cabbage together.
Mix all remaining ingredients together.
Pour over the cabbage-carrot mixture.

title: kentucky jam cake
directions: Soak raisins overnight in undrained crushed pineapple.
Cream butter and sugar in bowl until light and fluffy; add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in blackberry jam. Sift flour, soda and spices together, then add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in pineapple mixture, mixed fruits and hickory nuts.
Pour into greased, waxed paper-lined 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.
Frost with caramel icing.

title: ribs-n-beer
directions: Since ducks have a strong flavor, they are sometimes stuffed with apples, pared, cored and cut in quarters or 3 small onions. Remove before serving.

title: mexican hot dish casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and diced onion.
Crush nacho chips and spread in cake pan.
After hamburger is brown, add can of refried beans and mix together.
Put over chips and top with sliced Velveeta cheese.
Heat at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is browned and bubbly.
Dice tomatoes, cut lettuce and serve on top of mixture.
Add whatever picante or salsa sauce desired.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except stuffing and mix well.
Pour into casserole dish and sprinkle stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Wet bread.
Squeeze.
Add eggs and beat (or beat eggs separately).
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour into pan; dot with butter (raisins, if desired).
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.

title: baked apples
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Wash and core apples.
Apples may be baked whole, skins on or off.
Score apples halfway to keep apples from bursting.
Arrange apples in baking dish.
Add 1 tablespoon sugar to each apple and top with 1 teaspoon margarine.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Pour 1/2 cup water around apples to prevent sticking.
Bake, uncovered, until tender, 45 to 60 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown beef.
Mix everything together.
Save some cheese for the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: one pan banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350° and grease bottom of 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan. Stir all ingredients in pan with fork until moist.
Beat vigorously for 1 minute.
Bake until toothpick comes out clean. Takes 55 to 60 minutes.
Let cool for 5 minutes and remove from pan.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown beef and bacon, then mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or more.

title: oven omelet brunch
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a 13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, melt butter; coat bottom and sides.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs, sour cream, milk and salt.
Mix until blended.
Stir in cheese or onion.
Pour into dish.
Bake until eggs are set, but still moist, about 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix sugar and cream cheese together.
Add peanut butter.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in pie crust.
Drizzle chocolate syrup over top and sprinkle with crushed peanuts.
Put in freezer.
Remove from freezer and place in refrigerator for 1 hour before serving.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Mix ground beef, pepper, onion and celery.
Season this mixture with salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt and hot sauce (if desired) to taste.
Boil 1/2 pound spaghetti.
Make 2 layers of spaghetti, layer of sauce and use sharp Cheddar cheese and butter over each layer.
Pour 1 1/2 cans tomatoes over it and cook at 350° about 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Drop on cookie sheet by spoonsful. Bake 15 minutes in 350° oven. Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and chill 1 hour.
Stir in sliced bananas and marshmallows.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill until set, approximately 2 hours.

title: calico bean bake
directions: Cook onion and garlic in shortening.
Mix onion and garlic and the rest of the ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all but cheese in a greased casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Stir in the cheese and smooth the top. Bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes more until set.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger (salt and pepper to taste); drain.
Add tomato sauce, pepper and oregano.
Simmer for a few minutes.
Put into unbaked pie shell.

title: courtbouillon
directions: Put lard into deep pan.
When hot, add onion and garlic, then flour.
When thoroughly mixed, add tomatoes, all seasonings, water and vinegar.
Let boil 5 minutes, then add fish, slice beside slice.
Boil about 10 minutes.
Serve with parsley sprigs and lemon slices for garnish.

title: mexican cornbread pie
directions: If you like, mix the Tabasco peppers and the can of Ro-Tel in blender.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dump pecans and coconut into greased pan.
Follow directions on cake mix.
Pour cake mix on top of pecans and coconut.
Mix cream cheese and melted butter. Add confectioners sugar.
Spread on top of cake mix.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Chop celery, carrot and garlic into fine pieces or put in food processor. Saute in olive oil until brown. Add tomatoes with tablespoon sugar, oregano, basil, salt and pepper to taste. Simmer 1 hour.

title: doughnut holes
directions: For Glaze:
Stir together confectioners sugar, milk and vanilla extract.

title: fruit salad with pudding
directions: Combine fruit in bowl.
In separate bowl, mix yogurt with pudding.
Combine this with fruit on serving dish.
Top with whipped topping.
You can garnish with kiwi fruit.

title: tuna fish pate
directions: In bowl, mix all ingredients well to form smooth mixture. Pack tuna fish tightly into serving dish.
Chill well before serving.

title: mound candy
directions: Mix coconut, powdered sugar and condensed milk; refrigerate. Melt wax and chocolate morsels.
Dip small balls of coconut mixture.
Press almond in top of candy; dip again.
Chopped nuts can be added to coconut mixture.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples thin.
Cook apples, apple juice and water over medium heat for 8 minutes.
Add cornstarch and enough water to make a paste; add to apple mixture.
Pour into deep dish pie crust. Top with butter and cinnamon.
Put other crust on top; cut slits in top crust.
Dot with butter.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: volcano cake
directions: Make cake according to directions on box.
(A bundt cake pan is easy to use for this in that it can be sliced easily.)
Cool the cake and cut it into 3 layers.
Mix cream cheese and cool whip until smooth.
Spread cream cheese mixture on each layer.
Place layers on top of each other.
Put chocolate syrup over all.

title: chicken and pasta
directions: Skin and cut up chicken breasts.
Put oil in skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and brown.
Add soup, water, pasta and vegetables.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat. Cook on low for 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serves 4. Cooking time is 20 minutes.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Chop lettuce and cauliflower in bite-size pieces.
Layer in order.
Cover and let set overnight.
Mix well before serving.

title: smothered broilers
directions: Cut broilers in half.
Rub with salt.
Let stay in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to cook, rub chicken with lemon juice.
Coat all sides with butter.
Place in broiling pan, skin side down.
Sprinkle with sugar, paprika and pepper.
Brown on both sides under broiler.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 275° for 1 to 2 hours.

title: meatball saucy subs(good and very easy to make)
directions: In a medium bowl combine beef, crumbs, grated onion, egg and pepper.
Shape mix into 2-inch meatballs (about 12).
In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, cook meatballs until brown on all sides. Remove and drain on paper towels.
In the same pan, cook green pepper strips and sliced onion until crisp but tender.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.

title: hot and sour soup
directions: Remove green portion of scallions; thinly slice.
Set aside. Cut white portion in 2-inch lengths.
In a large saucepan, bring white scallions, chicken stock, ginger and peppercorns to a boil over high heat.
Reduce to medium heat; simmer 15 minutes.
Strain and reserve.

title: microwave hershey bar pie
directions: Bake crumb crust; set aside.
Combine chocolate bar pieces, milk and marshmallows in medium microwaveproof bowl.
Microwave on High (100%) for 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until chocolate is softened and mixture is melted and smooth when stirred.
Cool completely.
Whip cream until stiff; fold into chocolate mixture. Spoon into crust.
Cover; chill several hours or until firm. Garnish with sweetened whipped cream; serve with chilled cherry pie filling.

title: fresh cream-style corn(white or yellow)
directions: Shuck and remove silks from the corn. Cut off tops of corn kernels and scrape to remove milk and remaining corn. In a skillet, fry the fat back or bacon and remove from pan. Pour corn in grease and cook on medium for 30 minutes. In a bowl, place the flour. Add hot water (as needed) and beat with whisk until smooth. Add corn along with the milk. Will thicken. Add salt and pepper to taste. If mixture gets too thick, add a little milk.

title: cheesy brunch pie
directions: Beat eggs and sour cream until blended.
Stir in bacon, cheese and parsley.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Bake in preheated 375° oven on baking sheet for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving. Serves 8 approximately.

title: mom's stroganoff
directions: Combine all ingredients but sour cream.
Cook 45 minutes.
Add sour cream just before serving.
Serve over rice.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Beat egg white with water until mixture is frothy.
In shallow dish, stir together sugar, cornstarch and spices.
Toss nuts in egg white mixture to coat well.
Roll them in spiced sugar mixture and spread in single layer in 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake in preheated 250° oven 1 1/2 hours, stirring every 15 minutes.
(May use 9 x 13-inch pan, but may need to cook approximately 15 more minutes.)
Cool, then store in an airtight container.

title: quick sticky buns
directions: Combine ingredients and put in greased cake pan.
Top with 1 can of ten refrigerator biscuits (the cheap ones).
Bake as package directs or until golden brown.
Invert and serve warm.

title: sausage corn skillet
directions: Form sausage into 12 balls.
Lightly grease a 10-inch skillet. Add meat balls and cook over medium heat turning to brown evenly. Add onions, celery and pepper to skillet.
Cook until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Pour off drippings, if any.
Add rice, corn and broth to pan.
Bring to a boil; stir once or twice.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Fluff with a fork.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ribbon jello
directions: Pour boiling water over lime Jell-O; add other ingredients and let stand in loaf mold until set.

title: braunschweiger dip
directions: Mix braunschweiger, cream cheese, sour cream and chili sauce. Spread dip over the top.
Serve with crackers.

title: cheesy potato bake
directions: Mix together the soup and milk.
Place half of the sliced potatoes in greased 2-quart casserole, onion and 1/2 cup soup mixture.
Top with the other potatoes, onion and soup mixture. Top with paprika. Cook in microwave, covered, 20 to 25 minutes or until tender on medium-high temperature.

title: party salmon ball
directions: Drain and flake salmon; remove skin and bones.
Mix with other ingredients thoroughly.
Chill several hours.

title: family cream pie
directions: Mix
together.	Cool
over slow heat.
Stir constantly. When thick, pour in baked pie shell.
Top with slightly brown meringue.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl. Add oil, apples, nuts and eggs. The batter will be stiff. Pour into greased Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Grind pepper with fine blade.
Mix pepper, sugar and vinegar; bring to boil for 3 minutes.
Add pectin or Certo and boil 1 1/2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
May be strained to remove foam; put into sterilized hot jars and seal.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Mix all in bag. Shake chicken in bag. Melt 1 tablespoon butter in baking pan. Place chicken in pan and bake at 425° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper first. Turn chicken and sprinkle more salt and pepper. Bake for additional 15 minutes.

title: marinated asparagus
directions: Steam asparagus 3 to 4 minutes.
Mix vinegar and oil.
Add herbs to suit your taste.
Pour over the asparagus and chill.

title: struesel coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and baking powder together.
Cut in butter. Add egg with milk.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with any flavor of pie filling.
Sprinkle on STRUESEL:
1 C. flour, 1 C. sugar, 1/2 C. butter.
Mix with pastry cutter until small pieces.

title: cheese cake
directions: Make graham cracker crust.
Press into 2 regular cake pans. Set aside.
Whip the cream cheese with milk, a little at a time. Add Dream Whip and pudding.
Divide between cake pans.
Top with favorite fruit (blueberries, cherries, strawberries, etc.).

title: banana pudding cake
directions: Beat bananas until well mashed.
Add remaining ingredients. Blend, then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into well-greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Remove from pan; finish cooling on rack. Sprinkle with powdered sugar if desired.

title: fruit dip
directions: Serve with cut up fruit (pineapple, cantaloupe, strawberries, grapes, etc.).

title: tupperware white
directions: Fill sink with hot soapy water.
Add baking soda, bleach and vinegar.
Let Tupperware soak.
Rinse in clean warm or hot water. It takes the greasy, sticky and yellow color off Tupperware.
Good for Melmac dishes.
Not for silverware.

title: fudge in 5 minutes
directions: Cook to boiling and time 5 minutes.
Then set aside.
Add marshmallows and morsels; stir until melted.
Pour in buttered pan to cool and then cut in pieces.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put 2 cups crushed potato chips on top and bake at 450° for 15 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: corn soup
directions: Traditionally this soup uses no spices.
Cut meat into 1/2 to 1-inch cubes.
Trim fat.
In an 8-quart or larger pot, heat oil or grease (we use bacon fat) on medium heat.
Add onions and cook for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add meat in small amounts to braise.
When well brown add liquid to cover 2 inches above meat.
Boil for 1 hour hard.
Add spices to taste, about 1/4 teaspoon each.
Add liquid until pot is 3/4 full; bring to rapid boil.
Add dry sweet corn. Cook on medium to low heat (slow boil) for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
You may thicken with flour or cornstarch and cold water if you want. Serves 8.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Melt butter and beat with eggs and sugar.
Add combined flour and baking powder alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: mama's tea cakes
directions: Cream the butter. Add sugar gradually and beat until light. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat to lemon color.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add to the other ingredients. Add flavoring. Beat only until mixed.
Chill. Roll thin and cut into desired shapes or take small pieces, roll like biscuits and flatten with fingers or a glass. Sprinkle on sugar.
Cook in preheated oven at 350° until edges begin to brown.

title: chocolate crackers
directions: Heat sugar and margarine until melted and sugar is dissolved. Grease 2 cookie sheets, then line with wax paper.
Grease the paper.
Line with saltine crackers.
Pour butter-sugar mixture over crackers.

title: brewed coffee(trakte kaffe)
directions: These proportions are for two cups of coffee.
Place water and coffee in an enamel coffee maker.
Stir.
Let coffee heat up to the boiling point.
Remove from heat and let set, undisturbed, for 5 to 6 minutes before pouring.

title: bob's houseboat special
directions: Fresh fish works best !!!
1. Place whole gutted fish on sheet of aluminum foil large
enough to rap entire fish and other ingredients.
2. Cut potatoes lengthwise. Place two halves next to each
side of fish.
3. Slice lemon into 4 even pieces. Sprinkle Thyme and
Basil on both sides of fish.
4. After all ingredients are wrapped in foil place on BBQ
low heat on one sideof gas grill. Turn every 15 minutes
let cook for one hour.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix 2 boxes of vanilla pudding with 3 cups of milk; slowly mix until thick.
Add 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Mix in slow.
Mix big box chocolate pudding with 2 1/2 cups of milk.
Mix slow until thick. Layer graham crackers and vanilla pudding, then put chocolate on top.

title: grandma's chocolate frosting
directions: Boil to soft ball stage.
Powdered sugar can be added if too thin.
Stir to cool slightly.
Spread quickly.

title: herb-stuffed pork chops
directions: In a skillet, saute onion and celery in butter until tender. Add bread cubes, parsley, milk, fennel seed, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper; toss to coat.

title: cream cheese blintzes
directions: Cut crusts off bread and roll with rolling pin until thin. Blend cream cheese, sugar and egg yolks together and spread on bread; roll up.
Dip in melted butter and then in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Put in freezer for at least 4 hours.
Remove from freezer and bake in 400° oven for about 15 minutes.
These can be kept unbaked in freezer for several weeks.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan; pour melted chocolate over mixture.
Put in refrigerator until hard.
Cut into squares.

title: coconut crunch torte
directions: Combine crumbs, coconut and nuts.
Beat egg whites with salt and vanilla until frothy.
Gradually add sugar and continue beating until egg whites form stiff peaks.
Fold in graham cracker mixture.
Spread in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with ice cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: seashell pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions, rinse with cold water and drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours before serving.
My personal preference is Pietros Italian dressing.

title: fluffy frosting(frosts 9 x 13-inch cake)
directions: Mix 1/4 cup water with unflavored gelatin and let set 5 minutes, then warm to dissolve.
Let cool.
Add cherries and juice.
Let set in fridge until partially thick (about an hour). Add to Cool Whip, vanilla and almond.
Frost cake.
Top with nuts. Keep in fridge.
Good.

title: frozen lemon pie
directions: Beat yolks, salt and sugar in top of double boiler.
Stir in lemon juice and grated rind.
Cook over hot, not boiling water, until mixture thickens and coats spoon.
Remove from stove and chill.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in whipped cream and cooked mixture.
Sprinkle half of the wafer crumbs in freezing tray, then pour in mixture.
Top with remaining crumbs and freeze until firm.
Serve in finger-length slices.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine these 4 ingredients in a large saucepan.
Mix well. Bring to a boil, then cook over slow heat until it forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat and add 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla and 1 tablespoon oleo.
Let cool and beat until almost firm.
Spread in buttered platter and cut in squares.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break spaghetti into 3 pieces and cook.
Combine with other ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: tuna creole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and add bell pepper and cook gently about 3 minutes.
Stir in flour and milk gradually.
When smooth add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook slowly until thick, stirring constantly (about 15 minutes).
Add tuna fish and cook 2 minutes more.
Serve over buttered toast.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Mix popcorn, peanuts and candy in a large bowl.
In a saucepan, melt butter and marshmallows; add oil.
When melted, pour over popcorn mixture and combine. Press into a greased tube or Bundt pan.
Press down firmly.
Refrigerate for several hours. Remove from pan and enjoy.

title: chocolate rum torte
directions: Butter and flour a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Pour coffee into a small, heavy saucepan.
Add chocolate and stir over low heat until chocolate melts.
Mix in sugar, then almonds and stir vigorously, still over low heat, until blended. Take off heat and chill briefly.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese and milk.
Add rest of ingredients to cream cheese mixture and blend well.
Put into graham cracker crust (6 ounce pie crust) and freeze.
Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving time.

title: old-fashion egg custard
directions: Beat 3 egg yolks and 1 whole egg slightly; add 2/3 cup sugar, flour and cornstarch which have been sifted together.
Stir all together into uncooked pie shell and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Combine butter and graham cracker crumbs.
Add condensed milk and remaining ingredients, stirring until well blended.
Spoon into midget paper cups (1 3/4-inch).
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely on wire rack.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in skillet, which has been greased and floured, at 400° to 450°.

title: spanish rice with beef
directions: Heat butter in frying pan over medium heat.
Add rice and saute along with onion and garlic until golden. Add meat and cook, stirring, until meat is browned and crumbly.
Add tomatoes and then liquid, mushroom sauce, tomato sauce, mushrooms and their liquid, oregano, chili powder, pepper and salt.
Mix well.
Cover and simmer over low heat, stirring once or twice for 1 hour or until rice is tender.
Serves 6.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese and salad dressing mix until smooth. Add onions; mix well.
Spread about 3 tablespoons over each tortilla. Top each with two ham slices. Roll up tightly and wrap in plastic wrap. Refrigerate until firm. Unwrap and cut into slices.

title: taco dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Stir together softened cream cheese and sour cream until well blended.
Add taco seasoning.
Stir well. Layer mixture in container.
Pour picante salsa on mixture. Distribute evenly.
Dice tomatoes.
Spread tomatoes evenly over mixture.
Top with taco shredded cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Refrigerate remaining dip.

title: summersicles
directions: Mix sugar and water together and cook until sugar dissolves. Let cool.
Mash fruit. (Note: If using peaches, peel and discard pit.) Add orange and lemon juice to mashed fruit.
Mix well.
Add sugar water; mix well.
Pour into ice cube tray.
Freeze until firm enough to hold popsicle stick.
Place stick into middle; return to freezer.
Freeze until solid.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Heat on low until blended.
Do not boil.
Serve with sliced apples.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Soak bread cubes in milk.
Mix with onion, meats, eggs, salt and pepper.
Shape meat mixture into walnut-sized balls. Place on broiler pan in oven at around 350° until almost done.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Fill 1 (9-inch) pie shell.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 minutes.
(Bake longer if filling will appear softer in center; it will get stiff enough after cooled.) Put foil around sides of crust during baking to prevent burning.

title: lasagna
directions: Meat Sauce:
Brown meat and onion.
Then mix tomato sauce, basil, oregano, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil; reduce heat. Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: tomato teasers
directions: Cut out small hole in top of tomatoes.
Combine crumbled bacon with Tabasco sauce; sprinkle bacon mixture into tomatoes.
Serve with food picks.

title: one dish meal
directions: Boil noodles until tender and drain.
Melt butter.
Add ground steak, green pepper and onion; brown.
In a buttered baking dish, add layer of noodles, meat and corn until all are used.
Season well.
Add tomato soup and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spiced whole wheat banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add bananas and spices.
Combine flours and soda.
Add to creamed mixture, mixing well.

title: pound cake
directions: In
large
bowl, beat margarine, Crisco and sugar thoroughly. Add
eggs,	1 at a time, beating after each addition. Mix baking powder, salt and flour.
Add extract to milk.
Add milk and flour mixture alternately to egg mixture, ending with milk.
Pour into Bundt pan and place in 350° oven.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: sherried mushrooms
directions: Melt butter in saute pan until it foams.
Add mushrooms and saute on high. When mushrooms drop their water add sherry and boil hard until syrupy.
Then add whipping cream, herbs and salt and pepper.
Serve when liquid reduces by half.

title: chicken and pasta salad
directions: Combine chicken and dressing in a large bowl.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Cook macaroni according to package directions, omitting salt and fat.
Drain well.
Add macaroni and remaining ingredients to chicken mixture in bowl. Toss gently to coat well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
Yield: 8 servings.
Serving size: 1 cup. Calories per serving: 116.
Protein per serving: 11 grams.
Fat per serving: 1 gram.
Cholesterol per serving: 25 mg.

title: italian creme cake
directions: Using electric mixer; beat margarine and shortening.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Sift flour and soda together and add alternately with buttermilk.
Still using electric mixer, add vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 greased and lined 8 or 9-inch cake pans and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until sides break loose from pan.
Remove cake from oven.
Set on rack to cool.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Beat ingredients in large mixer bowl at low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat on medium speed 3 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center of pan comes out clean (55 to 60 minutes).
Cool for 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely before serving.

title: layered potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes and slice potatoes, onion and green pepper. Layer potatoes, onion and green pepper, alternating, until all are in the casserole.
Add the can of soup to top.
Cover and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: bread
directions: Put shortening, sugar and salt in a large bowl.
Pour in scalded milk.
Stir until shortening is softened and lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water. Add to milk about 5 cups of flour.
Stir until all flour is moistened. Add yeast. Beat until dough is shiny. Add enough flour to make soft dough
that can be handled.
Turn out on floured surface and knead until smooth.
Put in greased bowl twice to grease all over. Cover with waxed paper and clock.
Let rise until double in bulk, from 1 to 2 hours.

title: lamb chops with mint stuffing
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter. Stir together with mint and bread. Season with salt and pepper. Add egg; mix lightly. Place lamb in a shallow baking dish; brush with creme de menthe, if desired. Pile stuffing on top of chops. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Yield: 8 servings.

title: double chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine pie filling mix, milk, chips and butter in saucepan. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full bubbling boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice. Pour into shell and chill 3 hours.
Plastic wrap may be placed on pie filling before chilling.
Garnish with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chocolate curls or grated chocolate, if desired.

title: cinnamon pull apart
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Roll pieces in sugar/cinnamon mixture and put into Bundt pan.
Scatter pieces all around pan.
Cook brown sugar/butter/cinnamon mixture until it comes to boil.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Pour over biscuit pieces. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand in pan for 10 minutes after taking out of oven, then "dump" on plate.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Place caps upside-down in a casserole dish.
Put stems, garlic powder, bread, Parmesan cheese, parsley and pepper in food processor.
Blend until mixture is crumbly, then add melted butter to this mixture.
Spoon mixture (stuffing) onto mushroom caps.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, uncovered.
Then top with Mozzarella cheese and bake for 15 minutes more.

title: spaghetti sauce with meat and vegetables
directions: Saute vegetables and garlic in oil.
Add meat and brown, then add stewed tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Season to taste with Italian seasoning and salt and pepper.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Cut steak in bite size cubes.
Coat with flour; brown in butter.
Add onion, parsley, garlic, bay leaf, salt and pepper. Stir in mushrooms, Burgundy and water.
Heat mixture to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 1 hour or until tender.
Serve over hot rice or noodles.
Serves 6.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix them on high speed until creamy, then beat at least 5 more minutes on high speed.
Pour into pie crust.
Freeze.
Thaw for a few minutes before serving.
Top with warm fudge sauce and sprinkle on a few peanuts.
Enjoy!

title: mississippi mud
directions: Spread marshmallow cream.
Mix confectioners sugar, cocoa, pecans and milk.
Spread over marshmallow cream.

title: glenna's oatmeal pie
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Bake in unbaked pie shell for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: salmon salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with crackers or make sandwiches with bread.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix; store in covered container.
Use 1/3 cup mix per 1 cup hot water.

title: country style baked beans(makes 6 servings)
directions: In large saucepan over medium-high heat, cook pork and beans, sausage, steak sauce, onion and apple, stirring until mixture boils.
Reduce heat; simmer 20 minutes.
To serve, garnish with apple.

title: impossible apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 325°. Grease pie pan. Mix apples and spices. Turn into pie pan. Beat remaining ingredients 15 minutes in blender until smooth. Pour into pie pan. Sprinkle with Streusel. Bake 55 to 60 minutes.

title: easy berry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour 1/2 flour mixture in dish; add berries, then remaining flour mix.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: peach luscious
directions: Blend sugar, egg yolks and butter together in few fast stirs. Add sifted dry ingredients and lemon rind alternately with milk. Rub sides of wide shallow baking dish with lard.
Fill bottom with quartered peaches.
Bake in moderate oven, 350°, about 30 minutes. Cover with meringue.

title: pizza snacks(12 servings)
directions: Spread spaghetti sauce (without meat) onto rye bread slices. Top with cooked, sliced pork sausage, mushroom slices and grated cheese.
Place on cookie sheet; heat in a 350° oven for 5 minutes.

title: peanut butter crunch
directions: In sauce pan put sugar, Karo and water.
Cook to 290 degrees. (Beat with a little extra peanut butter.)

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook sliced carrots in salted water until fork-tender.
Drain well.
Add onion, bell pepper and celery to carrots.
Set aside. Mix and bring to a boil soup, sugar, oil, vinegar, mustard and Lea & Perrins.
Pour this hot mixture over the carrot mixture. Refrigerate overnight.
Keeps well in a tight container, refrigerated.

title: kool-aid super sour kool kubes
directions: Mix Kool-Aid drink mix with sugar and water in glass measuring cup, stirring until the drink mix is dissolved.
Pour evenly into plastic ice cube tray, lightly sprayed with no-stick cooking spray.
Freeze for 3 to 5 hours or until firm.
Remove cubes from tray and place in serving bowl or on plastic tray.
Add Kubes to any flavor prepared Kool-Aid for a special treat.
Makes about 14 cubes.

title: fluffy peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy. Beat in peanut butter and sugar. Slowly add milk, blending thoroughly. Fold topping into the mixture. Pour into pie crust and sprinkle with chopped nuts. Freeze until firm. Cut and serve.

title: herb and garlic fish
directions: Mix dressing and seasonings.
Place fish in baking dish. Brush with 1/2 of the dressing.
Broil 5 to 8 minutes, 2 to 4-inches from heat.
Turn fish over and repeat.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Soften cream cheese, then cream in a large mixing bowl.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Fold in Dream Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill.
Ready in 30 minutes.

title: meatballs and wieners
directions: Mix hamburger with garlic powder.
Shape into small balls. Brown in frying pan; drain.
Mix chili sauce and jelly; heat well. Add meatballs and wieners.
Let simmer in sauce.
The longer they simmer, the better it tastes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix white sugar and cinnamon.
Quarter each biscuit and dip in sugar cinnamon mixture.
Put into oiled or sprayed bundt pan.

title: yum-yum salad
directions: Drain pineapple and mix with pie filling.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place in a bowl and refrigerate for 4 to 5 hours before serving.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat together butter, sugar, eggs and vinegar.
Add coconut, raisins and nuts.
Pour in an unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Double recipe for two pies.

title: apple pie
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Cut shortening in mixture the size of small peas.
Add ice water; mix until a small ball.
Roll on floured board.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then turn down to 325° for 35 minutes.

title: mexican skillet supper
directions: Brown sausage, pour off fat.
Stir in green pepper and onion; cook until soft.
Add stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce, macaroni, sugar, salt and chili powder.
Stir well.
Cover skillet.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add sour cream.
Stir until hot.
May serve with grated cheese.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Parboil ribs with salt to flavor till tender, about 1/2 hour. Drain off water and let steam dry.

title: salad that's good with lasagne
directions: Make 1 package Good Seasons Italian salad dressing.

title: butterscotch bird nest
directions: Melt the butterscotch bits in a pan over low heat.
Add noodles and peanuts to the melted butterscotch bits and stir. Drop large spoonfuls of the mixture onto cookie sheets lined with waxed paper.
Shape each nest with your fingers.
Put 4 or 5 jelly beans into each and refrigerate.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine soups, sour cream, onion soup mix and ground beef. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour over cooked egg noodles.
(Cook noodles according to directions on package.)

title: vegetable lite lasagna
directions: Squeeze as much juice as possible from the thawed spinach. To the beaten egg, add spinach, Ricotta and cottage cheeses and salt.
Mix well.

title: white rabbit smash
directions: Fill 10-ounce bar glass 2/3 full of shaved ice.
Stir in ingredients and garnish with 2 sprigs of mint.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies in blender.
Set aside until needed.
Cream together the oleo, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Set aside.

title: lemon crisps
directions: Cream sugar and butter or margarine until fluffy. Add egg yolks, lemon juice and lemon extract until mixture is light. Mix in flour and salt until blended. Form a cylinder 1-inches in diameter. Wrap and chill for several hours or overnight. Slice chilled dough 1/8-inch thick onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned around the edges.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In medium bowl, combine flour, soda, salt, ground ginger, allspice and pepper.
Mix well and set aside. In large bowl, mix sugar and butter with electric mixer at medium speed.
Add egg and molasses and beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture until combined.
Chill the dough for 1 hour.

title: creamed corn
directions: Cut corn off cob.
Put in skillet and add about 1/2 cup of water (or more depending on what your amount is).
Then add sugar and salt to taste.
To thicken, mix about 2 tablespoons of flour and water to make paste.
Add to corn.

title: plum pudding
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together in an electric mixer. Beat the eggs, one at a time.
Combine the citron, prunes, raisins and pecans in another bowl.
Add the flour to the fruit and nuts; toss together so that everything is coated with flour.
Add to the butter and egg mixture, along with the remaining ingredients. Blend for 1 minute so that all is incorporated.
Grease and flour a souffle dish, about 7 x 4-inch.
Add the heavy batter and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes, or until nicely browned.
Serve warm by spooning out or cool and cut into pieces. Garnish with the whipped cream or Hard Sauce.
Serves 8.

title: basic fried rice
directions: Beat eggs with 1/4 teaspoon salt in small bowl.
Heat 2 tablespoons of peanut oil in wok over medium-high heat for 1 minute.
Pour in beaten eggs.
Stir continuously until eggs are cooked dry and separated into small pieces.
Remove cooked eggs and set aside. Heat 3 tablespoons peanut oil in wok over medium-high heat for 1 minute.
Add green onions and cold rice. Stir-fry 5 minutes.
Add chicken broth, remaining salt and soy sauce.
Stir to mix well.
Stir in cooked eggs, pepper and sesame oil.

title: hot lettuce salad
directions: Fry and drain bacon, set aside, leaving 2 Tbsp of grease in the skillet.
Mix sugar with flour and add egg.
Mix vinegar with water.
Add both mixtures together, and pour over grease in skillet.
Cook over low heat until slightly thick.
Pour over lettuce and garnish with hard boiled egg slices and crumbled bacon.

title: mom's dill pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers in jars with garlic and dill to taste.
Boil remaining ingredients and pour over cucumbers.

title: bubbi's banana nut bread
directions: Whip bananas until very light.
Cream the butter and sugar; add eggs.
Stir in flour, soda, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix strawberries with glaze.
Add other ingredients and mix together thoroughly.

title: pumpkin or sweet potato cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients until well blended and add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: three cheese pasta
directions: While pasta cooks, place milk, butter and crumbled cheese in microwave-safe bowl.
Heat on Full power until cheese and butter are melted, stirring often.
Stir in cream and grated cheese and serve over hot pasta.
Pass additional grated cheese.

title: home-style beef stroganoff
directions: In saucepan, melt butter and saute shallots (or onion) and mushrooms for a few minutes.
Add white wine, sherry, paprika, salt, pepper, cream and mushroom soup.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
In a separate pan, heat oil and add the meat, salt and pepper.
Brown meat quickly on both sides.
Remove the meat from the pan.
Add the meat to the sauce.
Do not let the meat and sauce boil. Simmer until meat is tender.
Add sour cream and mix thoroughly. Serve over cooked noodles.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain beans.
Fry bacon and crumble into pieces.
Dice onion. Mix everything together.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
May also be done in a crock-pot.
I usually do it in crock-pot for 4 or 5 hours.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Spray bottom of long casserole dish with Pam.
Tear 1 angel food cake into pieces and put in dish.
Pour prepared instant vanilla pudding over cake.
Pour drained crushed pineapple over next, scatter strawberries next.
Spread 1 container of Cool Whip over top.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: crazy cake(no eggs. no mixing bowl.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Sift the flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt into an ungreased 8 x 8 glass baking dish. Make 3 depressions in the dry ingredients. Pour oil into one, vinegar into one and the vanilla extract into one. Pour water over all and mix thoroughly with a fork to moisten all of the dry ingredients. Bake 30 minutes or a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean. Makes 9 servings.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine beaten egg whites and sugar; mix well.
Add salt, chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Turn oven off.
Place cookies in oven; leave at least 2 hours or overnight.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash okra and pack into sterile canning jars.
To each jar, add the dill seed, jalapeno peppers, garlic and pepper juice in the amount listed.
Bring the water, vinegar and dissolved salt to a boil and pour over the okra in the jars.
Seal and let stand at least 6 weeks.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Grease a 10-inch tube pan well with 2 tablespoons butter and sprinkle pan with 1/4 cup sugar to coat; set aside. Cream remaining 1 cup butter; gradually add remaining 2 cups sugar, beating well. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each. Add vanilla; mix. Combine 2 3/4 cups flour, baking powder and salt and gradually add to creamed mixture, beating until well blended. Dredge blueberries with remaining 1/4 cup flour; stir until berries are well coated and fold them into batter. Mix well and put in tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool in pan at least 10 minutes; remove and let cool completely.

title: horseshoe cookies
directions: Mix margarine and sugar; add vanilla and eggs.
Mix in flour and nuts.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Take tablespoon of dough and roll between hands.
Shape into horseshoe.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: sweet "n" sour chicken
directions: Lay chicken in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together next 4 ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour covered with foil.
Remove foil.
Put pineapple slices and green pepper strips on top.
Bake without cover for 30 minutes more.

title: vermont chicken pie
directions: Melt butter in a large pot; whisk in flour and cook over medium heat 5 minutes, whisking constantly.
Gradually add warm stock, whisking constantly.
Stir and simmer 20 minutes until it is gravy thick.
Add pepper and thyme; salt to taste.
Add chicken and vegetables and simmer until they are heated through.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole; preheat oven to 450°.
Beat Bisquick and milk, adding more Bisquick if necessary to make a manageable dough.
Turn onto a floured surface.
Knead until smooth, about 30 seconds.
Roll out large enough to fully cover the top of the casserole.
Cut to fit.
Bake until golden brown, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: baked eggs
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put cubed bread in bottom. Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over bread cubes.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake, covered, 50 or 60 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake 10 or 15 minutes longer.

title: spanish rice
directions: Mix meat and onion together while browning meat
until done. Add all other ingredients to meat.
Serve hot.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper, then brown.
Place uncooked rice in a wide, buttered casserole dish and sprinkle with salt. Place chops on rice.
Pour undrained tomatoes over chops; sprinkle with oregano.
Cover with sliced onion, pepper and bacon.
Pour broth over casserole.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 375°. Uncover.
If dry, add a little water.
Bake, uncovered, an additional 15 minutes.

title: baked chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken in 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Combine bread crumbs, salt and herb mix.
Drop chicken pieces in margarine and coat with bread crumbs.
Place on broiling pan in single layer.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: kraut salad
directions: Heat vinegar and sugar.
Pour over sauerkraut mixture. Let stand overnight in refrigerator and serve.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all together; use as desired.

title: mounds
directions: Mix together and press in 9 x 13 pan.

title: neiman-marcus dip
directions: Fry bacon until crisp and crumble up.
Mix first 3 ingredients, then add mayonnaise until desired consistency.
Add bacon pieces, salt and pepper to taste.
Refrigerate and let set. Mix well.
Makes a lot.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with broccoli.
Spread turkey or chicken over broccoli.
In medium bowl combine soup, milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over turkey.
Stir.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Return to oven for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: caramel corn
directions: Place sugar, chili powder, cinnamon and cayenne pepper in a zip tight bag.
Mix.
Spray popcorn with nonstick.
Close bag and shake until corn is coated.
Yields 6 cups.

title: rum balls
directions: Grind nuts, wafers and chocolate chips together.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Form into small balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Store in covered container.

title: peach crumb pie
directions: Sift flour, cinnamon, brown sugar and salt together.
Cut in butter or margarine until mixture is like coarse meal.
Put the fruit in pie plate and spread the crumb mixture evenly over the top.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes and then lower heat to 350° and bake for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: seafood supreme
directions: Melt margarine.
Add onions, peppers and mushrooms and cook until limp.
Remove from heat; blend in flour, salt and pepper. Stir in milk and cook until thick.
Add cheese, lemon juice, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Add seafood.
Serve over rice.

title: barbecued spareribs(from watertown)
directions: In a saucepan, brown onion in oil.
Add other ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes.
Pour over chops or spareribs that have been in baking dish in oven to brown while sauce is simmering. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes more or until tender.

title: country vegetable pie
directions: Saute squash, onions and green peppers, one vegetable at a time in butter until tender.
Layer tomatoes, squash, onions and green peppers in greased 2-quart casserole.
Combine cheeses and mayonnaise in bowl, mixing well.
Spread over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until browned and bubbly.
Yields 8 servings.

title: tortilla with spread
directions: First Layer:
Refried beans to cover bottom of oblong pan.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inch.
Brown beef and onion; drain.
Drain in salt and pepper.
Spread in plate.
Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth.
Pour into plate.
Bake 25 minutes.
