Top with tomatoes; sprinkle with cheese. Bake another 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Mix crushed cookies and margarine in medium bowl. Press firmly into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate 15 minutes. Beat the cream cheese, sugar and 2 tablespoons milk in medium bowl until smooth. Gently stir in the 1 1/4 cups whipped topping. Spread over crust.
Pour 3 1/4 cups milk into a large bowl.
Add pudding mixes. Beat with
a wire whisk 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Let stand 5 minutes or until thickened. Drop remaining whipped topping by spoonfuls over pudding. Spread to cover pudding. Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Cut into squares.
Just before serving, garnish with whole Oreo cookies. Makes 16 to 18 servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
It is best after it stands a bit.
Makes 1 cup.

title: fresh corn pudding
directions: Cut corn
from
ears, scraping well to get all the milk. Break eggs
into
large
bowl
and beat until light and fluffy. Add milk and
sugar
to
eggs and blend thoroughly.
Add corn, nutmeg and salt;
mix
well.
Cut butter into small pieces and mix through corn mixture.
Turn into large baking dish and bake about 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Blend all ingredients. Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube cake pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes. Cool 15 minutes.

title: mary's carrot cake
directions: In bowl, beat together eggs, sugar and oil.
In another bowl, combine flour, cinnamon, salt, baking soda and baking powder. Stir dry ingredients into egg mixture.
Stir in vanilla, carrots, nuts, raisins and pineapple.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan about 25 minutes or until cake tests done.
Frost with cream cheese frosting and enjoy eating.

title: white velvet
directions: Mix gelatin, sugar and cream.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Place saucepan over low heat and stir constantly until gelatin is dissolved.
Do not let boil.
Remove, cool to lukewarm and add sour cream and vanilla.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into a 1/2 quart mold.
Refrigerate until set.
Wash and hull strawberries.
Slice them and sprinkle with sugar (1/2 cup).
Add Kirsch.
Let stand. Serve over dessert.

title: "pecan pie"
directions: Beat eggs until well mixed.
Add syrup and sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla and melted butter.
Mix.
Add pecans. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake slowly at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and syrup.
Blend well.
Add melted butter and vanilla.
Blend and add pecans.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, depending on size of pans.

title: easy tater tot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and add spices to taste.
Add 2 cans of mushroom soup and the cheese.
Place in baking dish and top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
You may need to place under the broiler to crispen up the Tater Tots.

title: hot caramel apples
directions: In a large, heavy-bottom skillet, over medium-high heat, melt butter; add sugar.
Stir rapidly just until mixture is golden brown (1 to 2 minutes).
Stir in cinnamon.
Remove pan from heat; add milk.
Return to heat, stirring, until hardened sugar dissolves and mixture looks like caramel.
Cover skillet, reduce heat and simmer until apples are tender (about 5 minutes).
Put apples in a serving bowl.
Over high heat bring caramel to a boil until thickened (1 to 2 minutes).
Pour over apples and serve. Serves 8.

title: christmas balls
directions: Mix together sugar milk and butter.

title: chicken surprise
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove from bone and cut in bite size pieces.

Mix chicken with softened cream cheese and sage. Divide and shape mixture (finger size), roll into dinner rolls. Then roll the dinner rolls into melted butter and stuffing mix. Place in pan allowing room for rolls to slightly rise.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Dilute and heat chicken soup.
Pour over chicken rolls and serve.
Makes 16 rolls.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Use round cake mold or Bundt pan.
Tear angel food cake into bite size pieces.
Scoop ice cream and sherbet, alternating both. Drop pieces of cake and scoops of ice cream and sherbet into pan. Press down in pan.
Freeze.
Remove from mold.
Use whipped cream for icing.

title: smoky tidbits
directions: In saucepan, mix pineapple juice and cornstarch; add other ingredients except franks.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until mixture boils and thickens.
Add franks and cook until heated through, 3 to 4 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add egg yolks.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add alternately the milk and flour.
Beat 4 egg whites until stiff and fold in batter.
Make three 10-inch layers.
When cool, spread icing over cake.
Then cover with coconut.

title: spiced mocha mix
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.

title: peanut butter pralines
directions: You will need a candy thermometer.

title: sweetheart congealed salad
directions: Let cheese get to room temperature.
Drain pineapple and mix with cheese until smooth.
Add jello and mix.
Add Cool Whip slowly and refrigerate.

title: italian style meat loaf
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 2-quart casserole dish.
Add apples.
Sprinkle with 1/3 cup of water.

title: cinnamon rolls quick
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add cake mix and flour.
Knead well. Let rise until double, about 2 hours.

title: ruby tuesday's black sauce
directions: Mix ingredients over low heat just to boil, then reduce heat to simmer.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Boil the potatoes and let stand for a few hours or over night, still in the jackets. Peel potatoes and mash them or put through a ricer. Then add the eggs and flour and roll the mixture into little balls. Chill in the refrigerator for about an hour before cooking. Cook in lightly salted water that is just under the boiling point. When the dumplings are finished they will rise to the top. Serve hot with melted brown butter and crumbs.

title: spice pecans
directions: Cook sugar, cinnamon, salt, nutmeg and water together on medium heat. Cook until you can form a small ball in cold water in a bowl. Remove from stove and pour over pecans. Mix well in a 3-quart pan. Spread out on foil or freezer paper.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with 1 stick of butter.
Press in bottom of a 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Set in refrigerator.

title: you name it cake(i've never heard the name)
directions: Cream butter well.
Add sugar gradually and cream after each addition.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each.
Add vanilla wafer crumbs alternately with milk.
Add coconut and pecans and mix well.
Bake in a well greased and floured
pan (9 X 13) at 325 degrees for 30 minutes.	Reduce heat to 300 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger-french fry casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Line a 2-quart casserole dish on sides and bottom with ground beef.
Next spread mushroom soup on top of ground beef.
Then add cheese soup as next layer (do not mix soups together).
Next cover cheese soup layer with frozen French fries. Bake at 350° uncovered for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: orange chicken(serves 1)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix vanilla shake with can of diet orange and pour over chicken.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: custard filled cornbread
directions: Butter an 8-inch square baking dish.
Put buttered dish in preheated oven at 350° and let it get hot while you mix batter. Put eggs in mixing bowl and add melted butter.
Beat until well blended.
Add sugar, salt, milk and vinegar; beat well.
Sift into a bowl the flour, cornmeal, baking powder and soda;
add to egg mixture.
Mix just until batter is smooth and no lumps appear.

title: molasses cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a tube or Bundt pan at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream together the butter or margarine, sugar, eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Blend together the flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix cream mixture and flour mixture together. Put half mixture in Bundt pan.
Take other half mixture and add to Topping.

title: cranberry  marshmallow salad
directions: The day before serving, grind berries and add 3/4 c. sugar. Add marshmallows and mix. Cover and store overnight to allow marshmallows to absorb juice.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer in order:
Cream cheese ( spread thin in large platter); salsa; tomato (chopped fine); green pepper (chopped fine); sharp cheese shredded.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cherry jiffy
directions: Pour cherry pie filling into baking dish.
Sprinkle cake mix over top of filling.
Spread to cover.
Spoon melted margarine over cake mix.
Arrange pecans on top or spread chopped pecans over top.
Bake about 50 minutes at 350°.

title: pea salad
directions: Toss all together and chill.

title: shrimply divine
directions: Blend cream cheese with remainder of ingredients.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving with chips or crackers.
Makes 1 2/3 cups dip.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix
oats and flour.
Blend remaining ingredients until smooth.
Gradually	add
oats and flour mixture to the blended mixture.
Raisins may be added, if desired.

title: fruit bars
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add all dry ingredients; beat.
Spread on greased cookie sheet. Reserve about 1/2 cup batter, spread filling to within 1-inch of edge of pan, put rest of batter on top by small spoonfuls.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool and sprinkle top with powdered sugar and cut into bars or you can leave it plain.

title: slush
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding ginger ale last.
Stir well. Freeze to slush stage, use as beverage.
Makes 15 servings.

title: tropical cake
directions: Combine the brown sugar, oil, eggs, bananas and yogurt; mix well.
Sift the flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Stir into first mixture.
Add the coconut and pineapple and stir.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring to a boil and cook sugar, cornstarch and 7-Up until thick, stirring constantly.
Add red food coloring.
Cool.
Add strawberries.
Pour into cooled pie shell.
Top with Dream Whip or whipped cream.

title: fried chicken
directions: Mix 1 package of salad dressing mix with biscuit mix. Mix the other package with egg and club soda. Dip chicken pieces into egg mixture, then into dry mixture. Set chicken pieces on a rack to drip. Fry 3 minutes in deep fat, then bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet hot and sour meatballs
directions: In a large bowl, combine egg product, bread crumbs, onion, milk, salt and pepper. Add sausage and beef; mix well. Shape into 48 meatballs. Place meatballs in a shallow baking pan. Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven 30 minutes or until done. Remove from oven; drain.

title: eagle brand banana pudding
directions: Using blender, mix pudding according to directions on box, less 1/2 cup milk.
Add Eagle Brand and Cool Whip.
Add cream cheese. Mix well.
Layer with bananas and wafers in a large bowl.
Chill. Serve.

title: peach jam
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and let stand for 30 minutes.
Boil for 12 minutes.
Remove from heat and sprinkle in peach jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Place in jelly glasses and pour on melted sealing wax to seal.

title: green chili burrito casserole
directions: Put 2 cans chicken soup in saucepan.
Add 1 can of water.
Add green chilies and heat up.
In skillet, brown ground beef and onion.
Drain grease from meat and add refried beans and chili beans.
Mix well.
Take tortillas, put meat mixture in middle and make a layer of burritos in long cake pan.
Pour 1/2 soup mixture on top of layer.
Make rest of burritos; lay on top of first layer.
Pour remaining soup mixture.
Top with cheeses.
Heat in oven at 375° until cheese melts.

title: overnight buns
directions: Start at 4:00 p.m.
Mix ingredients, punch down on the hour for the next 4 hours.
Let set until 10:00 p.m.
Form into buns. Place buns on greased cookie sheet.
Let stand overnight.
Bake next morning at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pineapple raisin drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and egg; cream until light.
Add fruit.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add dry mixtures to cream mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Save a few mandarin oranges to decorate top of salad. Chill 2 hours. Serve for a refreshing complement to any meal!
Quick and easy!

title: oatmeal crisp cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Blend in oatmeal and nuts. Mix well.
Shape into rolls 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Wrap.
Chill overnight.
Slice with thin knife into about 1/8-inch slices. Place about 2-inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes or until done.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening and egg.
Add cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Beat well.
Blend in flour with a spoon.
Chill dough. Roll into small balls about an inch in size.
Place on cookie sheet.
Press middle of ball slightly with your thumb to make an indentation.
Put strawberry jam or chocolate chip in the middle, whatever you wish.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chinese chews
directions: Mix and spread in well-greased and floured 8 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
(Do not overbake.) Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: mamma mia meat sauce
directions: In 6-quart pot saute meat in olive oil until the meat loses its pink color.
Drain fat from pot and add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring often. Makes 5 quarts.
Can be frozen.

title: easy foolproof pie crust
directions: In large bowl, stir together with fork the flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
In small bowl, beat water, vinegar and egg together.
Add to flour mix and stir until all moistened.
Divide dough into 4 portions and shape each one in flat, round patty ready to roll.
Wrap each patty in plastic and chill at least 1/2 hour.

title: danish puff
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut 1/2 cup butter into 1 cup flour. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons water over mixture; mix.
Round into a ball; divide in half.
On ungreased baking sheet, pat each half into a strip, 12 x 3-inches.
Strips should be placed about 3 inches apart.
Heat 1/2 cup butter and 1 cup water to rolling boil in medium-size saucepan.
Remove from heat and quickly stir in almond extract and 1 cup flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball, about 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs (all at once) until smooth and glossy.
Divide in half; spread each half evenly over strips.
Bake about 60 minutes or until topping is crisp and brown.
Cool.
(Topping will shrink and fall, forming a custardy top.)

title: sausage soup with spinach and wild rice
directions: Bring 1 1/2 cups water to a boil in a medium saucepan.
Add wild rice; cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour or until tender. Set aside.

title: reese's cup cake
directions: In a saucepan, combine margarine, cocoa, buttermilk and water; bring almost to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients, except peanut butter and oil, and beat well.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Heat fruit and 2/3 cup sugar.
Melt margarine in baking dish. Mix a batter of 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk. Pour batter
in
baking dish with melted margarine; spoon fruit evenly over batter, then add juice.
Bake 25 or 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add Pizza Quick; simmer.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish with layer of cooked Creamettes.
Add layer of hamburger mixture to cover Creamettes.
Repeat layer. Top with pepperoni, Mozzarella cheese, Pizza Quick, then more cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and cooked through.

title: jeff davis pie
directions: Cream together until light and fluffy, butter and sugar.
Add flour, salt and vanilla and beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Slowly stir in milk.
Pour into well chilled pastry shells.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 30 minutes or until firm.
Serve slightly warm.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream both sugar, margarine and peanut butter.
Blend in eggs, salt and vanilla.
Work in flour, sifted with soda and baking powder, until smooth.
Make small balls size of marbles and lay them 2-inches apart on greased baking sheet.
With the tines of fork, press across the top at right angles.
If dough is sticky, put hands in flour.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes.

title: happiness cake
directions: First, mix thoroughly and add tears of joy, sorrow and sympathy.
Fold in four cups prayer and faith to lighten all other ingredients and raise texture to great heights of character.

title: cereals
directions: Mix like a pie crust; toast in oven until it's golden brown. Stir often so it doesn't get lumpy.
Cool.
Store in airtight container; use as needed for cold cereal.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening in a bowl.
Add the eggs, bananas, Bisquick and nuts.
Beat until well mixed.
Pour into a well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from pan and cool on rack before slicing.

title: smoked salmon dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients well and refrigerate.
Serve with bagels or crackers.

title: pistachio dessert or watergate salad
directions: Fold pudding mix (dry) into topping until well blended.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch glass dish. Chill well.
Best if made a day before serving.

title: kaylor's shanghi chicken
directions: Place chicken into plastic bag containing flour, paprika, salt and pepper.
Shake.
Brown chicken in large frying pan.
Remove; brown onions lightly.
Mix soup, water, wine and Gravy Master in frying pan.
Place chicken in frying pan.
Cover and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours, turning once, but basting with gravy while cooking.
If amount is doubled, use roasting pan at 350° in oven.

title: mom hunley's dutch party casserole(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Mix together beef, tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce and herbs and spices.
Heat to just below boiling and set aside.

title: christmas wreath cookies
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows together; add vanilla and green food coloring.
Stirring on low heat, mix in corn flakes until all are colored.
Cool.
Drop on wax paper by teaspoon.
Decorate with cinnamon hots.
Flatten a bit to shape like a wreath.
Fun and easy!
Great for kids to help!

title: pot luck potato casserole
directions: Defrost potatoes.
Combine in large mixing bowl with 1/2 cup melted butter.
Add salt, pepper, onions, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with corn flake/butter mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: clark bars
directions: Mix ingredients with hands.
Form into bonbon size balls and dip in chocolate.

title: black pearl clam chowder
directions: Pour clam juice in a large pot.
Add diced
potatoes, diced celery and diced onions. Broil bacon, do not crisp.
Dice and add bacon. Add milk, cream and butter (cut in half). Add clams and juice. Salt and pepper to taste.
Add dill. Slowly simmer 90 minutes to 2 hours.
Do not let boil. Do not use lid. Stir while cooking.
Serves 5 1/2 quarts.

title: fried veggie beer batter
directions: Heat oil to 375°.
Mix in a large bowl all ingredients except vegetables until well blended and smooth.
Let batter stand about 10 minutes while you cut up vegetables.
Dip vegetables in batter and fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute onions, pepper and butter. Stir in remainder in a 3-quart casserole.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Let ice cream and Cool Whip soften. Crumb up the Oreos in a blender.
Combine all three ingredients in at least a 9 x 13-inch pan and refreeze.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar, juice and water together; chill.
Just before serving, add 1 bottle of chilled ginger ale.
Top with ice cubes or a frozen mold.

title: squash casserole
directions: Add all ingredients, except crumbs, to squash.
Put layer of crumbs in a buttered casserole.
Add squash mixture.
Cover with crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
If frozen squash is used, bake for 1 hour.

title: aunt rita's city chicken
directions: Skewer chunks of pork and veal on sticks (ask butcher for sticks).
Add water to cover meat.
After placing in chicken fryer, add onion, paprika, salt and pepper to water.
Simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until meat is well done.
Save broth for gravy. Dip meat sticks in egg, then bread crumbs and deep fry.
Drain well.
Thicken gravy with flour or cornstarch and water.

title: fruit cake rocks
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs. Beat well. Add spices to flour then baking powder. Add to butter mixture then add whiskey mixture. Add fruit and nut mixture. Drop by spoonfuls on greased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: tutti-frutti salad
directions: Mix milk and ReaLemon; add cream and mix well.
Add other ingredients, one at a time, with cherries being last.
Chill 1 1/2 hours before serving.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Cool in cold water.
Chop or dice onion, tomatoes and green pepper.
Mix diced vegetables with 3/4 bottle (12 ounces) Italian dressing and 3/4 bottle of salad seasonings.
Mix with spaghetti; season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: In a saucepan, bring butter, sugar, milk and cocoa to a boil. Boil for 1 minute.
Add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla; stir well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper, removing after they have become cool and firm enough to handle.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and place in jar with 2 dill heads in each quart jar.
Boil hard the ingredients.
Takes 14 days to dill. Makes 1 gallon of pickles.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream oil, eggs and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Beat in dry ingredients.
Fold in walnuts and apples.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: garden steak rolls(serves 6)
directions: Cut steak into 6 portions. Pound to 1/4-inch thickness.
In a 10-inch skillet, cook bacon just until done.
Drain on paper toweling, reserving drippings in skillet.
Place a piece of bacon and several green beans and carrots on each meat portion. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Roll meat, jelly roll fashion.
Secure with wooden picks.
Brown meat on all sides in hot drippings.
Drain off fat.
Add gravy.
Cover and simmer 40 minutes.
Uncover.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes more or until gravy is thickened and meat is tender.
Remove picks from meat and serve with mashed potatoes.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in a bag.
Moisten potatoes with water, shaking off excess.
Shake a few at a time in the bag, coating well.
Pour margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place potatoes in a pan in a single layer.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, turning once.
Sprinkle with parsley, if desired.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: ranch chicken kiev
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese and Ranch mix; set aside. Pound chicken breasts flat. Place 3 to 4 tablespoons of Ranch mixture on 1/2 of chicken, then fold chicken over. Beat eggs, then dip chicken into egg wash. Bread chicken with a mixture of flour and bread crumbs. Seal the edges with toothpicks. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix everything but apples.
Melt 1 stick butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 batter in pan, then add apple filling.
Top with rest of batter.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions.
Add cream cheese and sugar.
Slice strawberries and place in crust.
Top with Dream Whip mixture.
Chill 3 hours before serving.

title: crock-pot cassoulet
directions: Soak beans overnight; drain.
Simmer in water 1 hour; drain and put in crock.
Saute bacon; saute and brown lamb and pork in drippings.
Put in crock.
Add wine, paste, stock with carrot, garlic, salt and thyme; cook covered on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Add sausage and cook 1 more hour.
Slice sausage and arrange on top. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: texas chili
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper in the meat fat.
Drain off the fat; add beans, tomatoes, sauce, bay leaf and seasonings. Cook below boiling for 1/2 hour.
Tastes better if made the day before and reheated.
Yield:
6 servings.
Carbohydrate 23 g, protein 19 g, fat 10 g, calories 258.
One serving = 2 meat low-fat exchange, 2 bread starch exchange, 2 fat exchange.

title: pecan pie #1
directions: Combine.
Put in unbaked shell.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°. Drop heat to 350° and bake for 30 or 35 minutes.

title: cranberry slim-down bars
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine first 8 ingredients; blend. Stir in flax seeds and cranberries.
Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into 15 squares.

title: kraut and frankfurters
directions: Combine kraut, tomato juice, onion, horseradish and sugar. Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Turn into shallow pan.
Wrap each frankfurter with 1 slice bacon and arrange in decorative fashion on top of kraut mixture.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 25 minutes or until bacon and franks are done.
Turn franks once during baking time so that bacon will be crisp.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: chop suey
directions: Mix the above ingredients in a bowl.
Put in a casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle chow mein noodles on top.
Bake 1/2 hour longer or until the liquid is absorbed.

title: caramel cake
directions: Mix 2 cups sugar and milk in saucepan.
Put 1/2 cup sugar in iron skillet or heavy pan.
Heat until melted and dark brown (burned practically).
Add to sugar and milk mixture.
Cook about 10 minutes.
Add margarine and stir until ready to spread. Delicious!

title: yellow cake
directions: Cream egg yolks, butter and sugar together.
Add one whole egg and vanilla; mix well.
Mix baking powder with flour and add slowly.
Beat egg whites in separate bowl until stiff.
Fold egg whites into batter with spoon.

title: chocolate snowflake cookies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until blended.
Add eggs and vanilla, mixing well. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add about 1/4 of dry mixture at a time to chocolate mixture, mixing after each addition.
Cover and chill dough at least 2 hours. Shape dough into 1 inch balls, roll in powdered sugar and bake on a greased baking sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown onions and meat.
Drain.
Stir in beans and next 7 ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve with topping.

title: bacon wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Wrap each chestnut in 1/2 strip of bacon, secure with toothpick.
Bake for 45 minutes or until bacon is done.
Make sauce with remaining ingredients and pour over chestnuts.
Serve in chafing dish and keep warm as sauce gets too thick when it is cold.

title: beet salad
directions: Drain beets in colander; stir them every once in a while until well drained.
Shake dressing.
Put some on the bottom of a glass bowl.
Place a layer of beets in bowl; add some dressing.
Repeat until all beets and dressing are used.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Stir before serving.

title: congealed salad
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar in a small pan and bring to a boil.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Add lemon juice.
Cool in refrigerator about 15 or 20 minutes.
Beat cream cheese until smooth and whip in Cool Whip.
Add pineapple mixture, pecans and cherries.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in salted water until tender. Mash well.
Add sour cream, cottage cheese, onion, margarine, pepper and salt. Mix well.
Place in casserole and sprinkle cheese on top.
(I sprinkle paprika on top.) Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: southern pralines
directions: Combine sugar, half and half and salt in deep 3-quart casserole.
Mix well.
Stir in butter; microwave at High for 7 to 9 1/2 minutes or until mixture reaches soft ball stage (235°), stirring once.
Stir in pecans; cool about 1 minute.
Beat by hand until mixture is creamy and begins to thicken (about 3 minutes). Drop by tablespoon onto waxed paper.
Let stand until firm.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Boil broccoli until tender.
Drain and pour into casserole dish.
Mix soup and cheese with broccoli.
Meanwhile, melt butter. Crumble crackers in butter and mix evenly.
Top broccoli with crumbs.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Combine berries, sugar, flour, salt and lemon juice.
Fill pastry lined pie pan.
Dot with butter and adjust top crust.
If desired, can sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over top of crust also. Bake in hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes; turn oven to 350° and bake for 30 minutes longer.

title: chicken-n-rice
directions: Put rice, soup, broth or milk and onion soup mix into greased casserole dish.
Dip chicken into melted butter and salt.
Place on top and bake for 2 hours for raw chicken, 1 hour for cooked chicken.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease two 8-inch cake pans.
Put the flour, salt, baking powder and sugar in a bowl.
Cut the shortening into the flour with two knives or a pastry blender until the mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add the milk, all at once, and stir just until the dough forms a ball around the fork.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill before serving.

title: party punch
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Freeze and remove 5 1/2 hours before serving. Chop and add 2 quarts ginger ale.

title: cranberry-sour cream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water, then add cranberry sauce and dissolve.
Chill until partially set, then add sour cream (fold in).
Let set.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Combine rest of the ingredients, and add to the zucchini mixture, stir well, add nuts last.
Pour mixture into loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cool on racks.
Freezes well.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend first
3	ingredients.
Sift
dry ingredients and add eggs; mix well.
Add zucchini, vanilla and raisins. Fill 2 greased and floured loaf
pans
half
full.
Bake	45
to	55 minutes at 350°. Freezes well.

title: ho ho dinner
directions: Press ground beef in bottom of 2 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Slice vegetables and layer on top of ground beef.
Crumble cheese on top of vegetables as you layer them.
Cover with soup.
Bake in covered dish for 1 hour at 350° or until vegetables are done.
Serves 6.

title: avocado salsa
directions: In a medium bowl, combine onion, cilantro and lime juice. Halve, pit, peel and dice avocado, then add to onion mixture. Season with salt, pepper and toss gently.

title: stephen's dump cake
directions: Pour cherry pie filling in bottom of tube pan.
Pour crushed pineapple over this, undrained.
Sprinkle cake mix over this.
Do not mix.
Cut up butter or margarine over top.
Sprinkle nuts over this.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour and 20 minutes (may take less time, watch closely at 1 hour).
Serve with vanilla ice cream.
Very rich!

title: navy bean and potato soup
directions: Cook the beans until done.
After beans are done, add the next 7 ingredients and cook all together.
Mash slightly.
Add the chicken soup base and Milnot; thicken with the flour (or to thickness desired) and water or milk.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: wild turkey and cornbread dressing
directions: Clean and prepare turkey for cooking.
Into cavity of turkey, insert quartered apple, sliced onion, 1 sliced orange and celery leaves.
(These ingredients will be removed after turkey is smoked.)

title: sausage and cabbage soup
directions: Add ingredients plus 3 cups of water in large pot.
Cover and simmer at least 1 hour.

title: nut torte
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add nuts, sugar and bread crumbs.
Place in desired greased pan and bake for 45 minutes in a hot oven at 375°.

title: chicken liver pate
directions: Add salt and pepper to flour.
Rinse chicken livers and pat dry.
Dredge chicken livers in flour mixture and set aside.
Saute onion in 1/2 of the butter until light in color.
Add rest of butter to pan and then chicken livers.
Cook until lightly crunchy on outside.
Transfer 1/2 of mixture to food processor; add 1/2 tablespoon brandy.
Process until finely chopped.
Repeat same for mixture in pan.
Mix together and refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Beat milk and egg together.
Mix bread crumbs and cheese together.
Dip chicken into egg mixture, then into crumb mixture. Place into oven dish which has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat butter, sugar, eggs and water together.
Stir in flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add vanilla, apples and half of nuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour in well-greased pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: mushroom and barley soup
directions: Melt butter in soup pot and add onion and all the mushrooms. Cover and steam over low heat for 10 minutes.
Stir in flour and add beef broth and barley and simmer for about 30 minutes or until barley is tender.
Add lemon juice and salt and pepper to taste. Garnish with parsley.
Soup gets richer and thicker the second day.
Serves 8.

title: double chocolate cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs and margarine (or butter); press firmly on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: black cherry dream salad
directions: Mix 1 box Jell-O as shown on package and let set until it begins to jell; add pineapple and chill until firm.
Have the cream cheese soft and beat in with Cool Whip or Dream Whip. Spread on top of firm Jell-O.
Mix other box of Jell-O and let set until it begins to jell; add cherries (either whole or cut up) and spread on top of cream cheese mixture.
Let set until firm.

title: burrito bake
directions: Grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inch.
Mix biscuit mix, water and beans.
Spread into pie plate.
Layer remaining ingredients on bean mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with sour cream.

title: peanut vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream
margarine
and
sugar;
add
eggs and beat well. Add milk
and stir in peanuts, coconut, wafer crumbs, raisins and vanilla.
Bake
in	a 12 cup Bundt pan for 1 1/4 hours at 500°.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Break chicken into small pieces.
Put drippings in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer tortilla strips, chicken, soup and grated cheese.
Repeat, but exclude cheese.
Repeat until out of items. Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour, then top with grated cheese and bake 1/2 hour longer.

title: spicy spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown sausage and drain off the grease.
Stir all ingredients together in a large pot.
Bring sauce to boil, then turn heat to low and let simmer for 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Remove bay leaf and peppercorns.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: glazed baked ham
directions: Soak ham or picnic in enough water to cover it for at least one hour.
Pull skin from ham.
Score ham in a diamond design and stud with cloves.
Place ham, fat side up, on a rack in a shallow pan.
Insert meat thermometer, making sure it does not touch bone. Bake uncovered at 325° until thermometer reaches 135°.

title: seafood puttanesca
directions: Cube tomato and place in a bowl with shrimp, crabmeat, black olives, capers and a pinch of salt and pepper.
In frying pan, place garlic and olive oil and saute until garlic is golden brown. Then add ingredients and saute for about 10 minutes.
Cook fusilli; drain and pour puttanessca sauce over top.
Serve.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat!
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Spoon batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: crabmeat toast
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on halved English muffins.
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes.
Cut muffin halves into 4 to 6 pie-shaped wedges.
Serve hot.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and butter, press equal amounts onto bottoms of 24 paper lined muffin cups.
In large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened milk until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla, mix well.
Spoon equal amounts into cups.
Bake about 20 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Chill.
Top with filling and refrigerate.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: favorite buttermilk biscuits
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Combine buttermilk and soda.
Turn dough on floured surface.
Knead 10 to 12 times.
Roll to 1/2 inch thickness.
Cut with a 2 3/4-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on a lightly greased sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Yields 10 biscuits.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Defrost hash browns.
Add melted margarine and stir.
Add other ingredients.
Toss until mixed. Put in greased casserole dish.
Top with corn flakes and small butter flakes.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter, sugar and egg.
Stir together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
(Batter will be very thick.)
Stir in the apples, nuts and vanilla.
Spread into a greased 8-inch pan.

title: banana mallow party pie
directions: Prepare pie filling as directed on pkg. using 1 3/4 c. milk. Cover with waxed paper, Chill.
Fold in marshmallows and whipped cream.
Slice bananas into crust.
Pour filling over bananas. Chill several hours.
Garnish with banana slices dipped in multicolored sprinkles and miniature marshmallows.

title: crispy baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rinse chicken. Dip in milk and roll in cornflake crumbs and place in pan (sprayed with Pam).
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: new joe's special
directions: Brown meat well in oil in large frying pan over high heat. Add onions, garlic and mushrooms; reduce heat and continue cooking until onions are soft.
Stir in seasoning and spinach.
Cook for about 5 minutes longer.
Add eggs and stir mixture over low heat just until eggs begin to set.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Serve with sourdough bread or biscuits.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix well and pour on buttered dish.
Makes 8 lbs.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add undrained strawberries and pineapple.
When cooled to room temperature, add bananas. Turn a third into a ring mold.
Chill until firm.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks; reserve whites.
In a bowl, mash yolks until smooth.
Combine mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, salt and pepper and add to yolks. Stir in onions and pickle relish.
Spoon mixture into center of egg whites.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: jam diagonals
directions: Thoroughly mix flour, soda, salt and spices.
Melt shortening in large saucepan.
Add sugar, molasses and eggs; mix well.
Cool slightly, then add 4 cups dry ingredients and mix well.

title: egg and broccoli casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Pour into a greased slow cooker.
Cover and cook on high for 1 hour.
Stir. Reduce heat to low; cover and cook 2 1/2 to 3 hours longer until eggs are set.
Sprinkle with additional cheese if desired.

title: quick whole wheat bread
directions: Sift together the whole-wheat flour, unbleached flour, salt and soda. Mix together the honey and buttermilk. Stir together the wet and dry ingredients. Add raisins or nuts if desired. Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell; dust with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until golden brown.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Boil whole zucchini 10 minutes in salted water; drain.
Cut lengthwise and scoop out centers with teaspoon.
Chop centers and set aside.
Melt butter; saute mushrooms.
Add centers (chopped), flour and oregano.
Heat through.
Add Monterey Jack cheese and stir until melted.
Fill shells and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Broil 5 minutes, until bubbly and browned.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut up squash and onion.
Cook in small amount of water until tender.
Drain; add oleo, cheese, egg, salt and pepper.
Cook in casserole dish until "set" about 45 minutes at 325°.

title: cauliflower-ham au gratin
directions: Arrange cauliflower in ungreased 11 x 7-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with ham.
Beat soup and milk until smooth.
Pour over ham and cauliflower.
Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly. Sprinkle over soup mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired. Bake at 400° until topping is golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: stir-fry sauce
directions: Combine all ingredient.
Pour over cooked meat and vegetables.
Heat and stir 2-3 minutes more until sauce is thickened.

title: lisa's favorite cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly butter, cream and flour.
Cover and chill.
Heat oven to 375°.
Roll about 1/3 of dough at a time 1/8-inch thick on floured surface.
(Keep remaining dough refrigerated until ready to roll.)
Cut into 1 1/2-inch circles.
Transfer rounds to a piece of waxed paper that is heavily covered with granulated sugar.
Turn over to coat well with sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets and prick about 4 times with a fork.
(Important!
They will not cook properly if you don't prick them!)
Bake 7 to 9 minutes (depending on your oven - mine took the full 9 minutes) or just until set but not browned.
Cool and put pairs together with Creamy Filling. Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: cinnamon rolls(makes 10 to 12 rolls)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: micro caramel-apple streusel
directions: Arrange slices in shallow micro pan.
Stir together topping, water and lemon juice.
Carefully pour over apples.
In small mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle evenly over apple mixture.
Micro on High for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Mix everything together. Let set, covered, in refrigerator overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour (or until set).

title: box cake cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix ingredients together in food processor.
Pour into a 1-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serve with crackers.

title: speedy stir-fry
directions: Slice steak into thin strips. Brown in oil with crushed garlic clove over medium heat. Remove meat. Add onion and zucchini. Stir-fry 1 minute. Add wine, cornstarch, 1 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Return beef to skillet and heat through. Serves 4.

title: "fruit punch"
directions: Pour Kool-Aid in container and add water as directed.
Add frozen lemonade, 3 cans water, pineapple juice and crushed pineapple.
Add sugar and chill until ready to serve.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: microwave spinach casserole
directions: If using frozen spinach, place package in a microwave dish. Cut a slit in top of package and microwave on High for 5 minutes. Remove from package and drain.
If using fresh spinach, cook in boiling water until tender and drain.
Combine spinach in dish with cheeses, eggs, flour, onion and salt.

title: jello cake
directions: Bake a white cake.
When it's done, punch holes in it with a fork.
Combine the Jell-O and water together.
Pour the Jell-O all over the cake.
When it cools, put the Cool Whip on it and chill overnight in refrigerator.

title: hungarian noodle side dish
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve bouillon in water.
Add the next 6 ingredients; mix well.
Stir in cottage cheese, sour cream and noodles and mix well.
Pour into a greased 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with the Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until heated through.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: jack corn chowder
directions: In saucepan, combine milk and flour; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened. Reduce heat to low; add cheese. Stir until melted and smooth, then add remaining ingredients. Cook over low heat 5 minutes until heated through. Do not boil. Makes 4 servings.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice thin.
Place half of potatoes in greased casserole.
Add half of other dry ingredients.
Add rest of potatoes, then remaining ingredients.
Pour milk over the top and add butter.
Bake in 400°
oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix Crisco and flour in a mixing bowl, adding enough milk to make it mix well. Stir until stiff enough to handle.
Dip out and put on floured wax paper.
Knead until smooth.
Pinch off small pieces of dough and roll in hand to make little biscuits.
Place in a baking pan and bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Saut onions and celery in butter. Add flour and cook, but do not brown. Add can of chicken broth and ketchup. Cook on medium heat for 3 to 4 minutes, then add crawfish tails, paprika and salt and pepper to taste.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Prepare dinner as directed, except using 3/4 cup of milk. Saute onion and green pepper in margarine until tender.
Add to prepared dinner with remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: korean kim chee
directions: Thinly slice bok choy into vertical pieces.
Then sprinkle bok choy with salt.
Let stand overnight in a cool place or in refrigerator.

title: sheath cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together; set aside.
Bring butter, water, shortening and cocoa to a boil.
Pour boiled mixture over flour and sugar.
Mix buttermilk, soda, eggs and vanilla.
Add to mixture.
(Cinnamon is optional.)
Pour into greased and floured 11 x 16-inch pan and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: diabetic coleslaw
directions: Chop fruit and mix with cabbage.
Mix mayonnaise and pineapple juice.
Pour over salad and toss.

title: sweet dough for fruit pies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg together.
Mix softened margarine and sugar real well.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
This is a hard dough but delicious to make small pies for figs, pears and peaches.
Refrigerate dough overnight. Use one rounded tablespoon dough.
Roll in hands to make a ball. Flatten on floured paper.
Fill one part and fold in half.
Cook at 375° until light brown.

title: chicken pie
directions: Debone chicken and break up in small pieces.
Mix chicken and vegetable soup together.
Spread out in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: In 10-inch skillet, over medium heat, cook onions, celery and carrots in hot margarine, stirring occasionally.
Stir in beef; heat through.
Stir in flour.
Gradually add beef broth, stirring constantly.
Heat to boiling.
Stir in Worcestershire.

title: fluffy buttermilk biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, lard and sugar.
Mix well until crumbly.
Add buttermilk and roll out.
Keep dough soft.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 11 biscuits.
Brush with butter.

title: molasses pie(page 253, grandma satchfield's cookbook)
directions: Beat and bake in pastry.

title: super bowl sub
directions: Mix slaw and 1/2 cup of the salad dressing. Spread bread halves with remaining salad dressing. Layer bottom half of bread with slaw mixture and remaining ingredients. Cover with top half of bread. Makes 8 servings.

title: southwest chicken
directions: Place prepared chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish which has been greased lightly.
Mix remaining ingredients together well and pour over the chicken.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: shredded wheat cakes(pseftiko kataifi)
directions: Dip each biscuit in
boiling
water,
using
a	slotted spoon to remove and place biscuits in a dish.
Cover and chill in a refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: swiss steak
directions: Salt and pepper meat.
Roll in flour and cut up meat in pieces. Brown in electric skillet on 350° in small amount of grease.
Then add the onion and green pepper, water and tomatoes.
Turn down to simmer until tender for about 2 1/2 hours.

title: corey's sweet apple quick bread
directions: Blend all ingredients except nuts.
Beat 3 minutes then add nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325°for 50-60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Remove from pan to cool.

title: chicken 'n' hash brown bake
directions: Thaw hash browns overnight in refrigerator.
Layer in an ungreased 13 x 9 inch baking dish.
Sprinkle hash browns with salt and pepper.
Place chicken and mushrooms over the hash browns. Stir remaining ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: dijon shrimp santa cruz
directions: Marinate shrimp in all ingredients 2 to 3 hours.
Broil 5 minutes at 450°.
Enjoy!

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together at once and blend well by hand with a wire whisk.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie crusts and bake at 375° until brown, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fruited salad
directions: In a large bowl, put the cottage cheese.
Add the Cool Whip, jello, tropical fruit and pineapple.
Mix together carefully (not real fast).
Add optional ingredients, if desired.

title: toasted almond turkey cutlets(yields 4 servings)
directions: On waxed paper, sprinkle both sides of each cutlet with cheese and pepper.
In large nonstick skillet, heat 1 teaspoon oil. Add turkey.
Cook over medium-high heat, 4 to 6 minutes per side, until cooked through.
Transfer to platter and keep warm.

title: vegetable salad #2
directions: Dice or slice celery, onion and pepper.
Place in layers in mixing bowl.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste.
Mix sugar, vinegar and oil together.
Pour over vegetables and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Stir gently the next morning. This will keep several weeks in refrigerator.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add sliced cabbage and onion.
Cook slowly until cabbage is tender.
Stir in cooked noodles.
Mix together.

title: mcfadden's flats
directions: Arrange ingredients, except soup, in order given, being sure to salt and pepper first layer (beef) and the last or top layer (potatoes).
Spoon can of soup over the top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: pear cottage mold
directions: Drain pears, reserving 1/3 cup syrup.
Combine reserved syrup, water and lemon juice in small saucepan; bring to boil.
Add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
With rotary beater, beat in mayonnaise until smooth; chill until partially set.
Set aside 3 pear halves for garnish; dice remaining pears into 1/2-inch cubes. Fold remaining ingredients into gelatin mixture.
Pour into 5 or 6 cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold onto lettuce-lined serving plate.
Slice reserved pear halves; place around mold for garnish. Makes 6 servings.

title: williamsburg orange cake
directions: *Or all softened butter.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and spread in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar. Spread on top of first layer.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: 2 cheese chili squares
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake in a preheated 425° oven for 30 minutes or until firm.
Let cool slightly, then cut into 1-inch squares.
Serve warm.

title: oriental chicken wings
directions: Remove wing tips and reserve for stock.
In large skillet, heat oil and brown wings on both sides.
Remove from heat and drain off excess oil.

title: special salad dressing
directions: Combine yogurt and mayonnaise, beating briskly with a wire whisk.
Add lemon juice, onion, salt and sugar.
Stir well. Store in covered glass container in refrigerator.
Yields 4 cups.

title: operation desert sand cookies
directions: Mix well and chill overnight.
Roll out dough 1/4-inch thick.

title: lasagna roll-ups
directions: Prepare lasagna noodles as package directs; drain and lay flat until ready to use.
Meanwhile, heat oil in a 12-inch skillet over medium heat and saute garlic 2 minutes or until tender, stirring frequently.
In medium size bowl, combine spinach, Ricotta, salt, garlic and 1/2 Mozzarella.
Spread each cooked lasagna noodle with 1/4 cup of spinach mixture.
Roll up firmly, jelly roll fashion. Pour 1/2 spaghetti sauce into 12-inch skillet.
Place rolls seam side down in skillet.
Pour remaining sauce over rolls.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella.
Cover and simmer 3 to 5 minutes longer or until rolls are heated through.
Garnish with parsley.
Serve with salad and Italian bread.
Serves 4.

title: chef bob's hot artichoke cheese dip
directions: Stir all until well mixed.
Spoon into small ovenproof dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 cups.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Heat oven to 350°.
Toss spaghetti with butter or oil.
Combine with eggs, 1/2 cup Parmesan and 3/4 cup Mozzarella.
Put in pie plate; press lightly into place.
Spread with Ricotta; top with sauce (you can add some cooked turkey Italian sausage to sauce).
Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining Mozzarella and bake 5 minutes more, until melted.
Top with 1/4 cup Parmesan.
Cool 10 minutes and serve.

title: raspberry dessert
directions: Melt butter and mix graham cracker crumbs and brown sugar. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan to make bottom layer.
Let set.
Soften cream cheese; mix with powdered sugar and Dream Whip.
Spoon over bottom layer.
Add hot water to jello.
stir until dissolved.
Add frozen raspberries.
Let sit until almost thick.
Pour over second layer.
Refrigerate.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain and season with salt, pepper, garlic powder and ground cumin.
Layer Doritos and meat mixture, ending with the meat mixture.
Sprinkle the grated cheese on top.
Stand some whole Doritos around the sides.
Heat at 350° for 20 minutes or until the cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients in stew pot.
Simmer on low until hot.
Serve over tortilla chips and top with Monterey Jack and Colby cheese, shredded.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix the ingredients well and bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: dip
directions: Cook each of the meats and drain well.
Put in crock-pot.
Add the soup, relish and cheese (cut up).
Cook on low.

title: mixed layered veggies
directions: Put lettuce that has been torn in bite sized pieces in a pan, add celery, pepper and peas in layer on lettuce.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and sugar together and pour over layered vegetables. Sprinkle with bacon bits and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: spinach whip
directions: Cook spinach (no salt).
Drain well and add other ingredients. Mix well.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.
If too thick, add a few drops of milk.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix and beat well.

title: finger size meatballs
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Roll into meatballs about golf ball size.
Bake in shallow pan 20 minutes at 350°.
Mix grape jelly with catsup and pour over meatballs.
Put in oven again at 325° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes approximately 70 meatballs.

title: fern's green bean casserole
directions: In a large pot layer vegetables in order of list. Add onion soup mix to meat. Layer meat patties on top of vegetables. Cover and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer until meat is done (about 1 hour).

title: low calorie salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and fruit cocktail.
Chill until lightly firm.
Mix Cool Whip, cottage cheese and marshmallows.
Contains about 60 calories per 3/4 cup serving.

title: banana fruit punch
directions: Boil sugar and water; cool. Put bananas, lemon juice, lemonade and orange juice in blender; blend until bananas are mush. Combine cooled syrup mixture, banana mixture, pineapple and 3 cups of water. Stir until blended. Pour into container and freezer.
Thaw 1 hour before serving. Add ginger ale in punch bowl. No ice is necessary, as mushy frozen punch should make it just right.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Combine all ingredients except Kisses in large bowl. Mix on lowest speed of mixer until dough forms. Shape dough into balls, using a rounded teaspoonful for each. Roll balls in sugar; place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes. Take out and place 1 Kiss on each cookie & press down firmly so cookie cracks around edge and put back in oven & bake for 3 minutes more. 48 cookies.

title: meat loaf with cheese stuffing
directions: Combine beef, eggs, bread crumbs, onions and green pepper. Add Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper, mustard, milk and ketchup. Mix lightly but well.
Meat will be juicier and more tender if you handle it as little as possible.
Divide meat mixture into 3 equal parts into bottom of a greased loaf pan.
Gently pat 1/3 of mixture.
Cover with 4 overlapping cheese slices and repeat meat, cheese and meat.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: hummus dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender just until blended.
Do not puree.
Place in serving platter.
Surround with pita wedges and serve.
Top with sliced tomatoes, if desired.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, eggs, soda, baking powder, salt, creamed corn and oil.
Mix well; add cheese, pepper, onion, garlic and sugar.
Add buttermilk until right consistency.
Pour into hot pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
For best results bake in iron skillet.

title: peach pie alaska
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add ice cream by spoonfuls.
Blend in whipped topping.
Spoon into crust.
Chill about 3 hours.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Add sugar, salt, nutmeg and lemon juice.
Add ice cold milk and cream.
Beat with mixer until frothy.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough into slices 1/2-inch thick.
Line a 14-inch pizza pan, overlapping slices.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes. Cool.
Combine softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until well blended.
Spread mixture over cookie crust.
Arrange slices of fresh fruit:
bananas, grapes, mandarin oranges, strawberries, peaches, pears (or any type of fruit that you like) over the cream cheese.
Glaze with marmalade combined with water.
Chill.

title: broccoli rice
directions: Prepare broccoli according to package instructions and cook rice.
Saute onion in margarine.
Combine broccoli, rice and onion with one can of soup and half of the grated cheese.
Top with remaining cheese.
Place in greased casserole and bake at 350° long enough to melt cheese, 5 to 20 minutes.

title: mom's specialty baked beans
directions: Mix together.
Bake, uncovered, for 2 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: no roll pie crust
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Add butter or margarine and stir until blended.
Press into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: piri piri wings
directions: Wash, dry and separate wings. Mix together all ingredients. Marinate wings in sauce for at least 2 hours. Wings may be grilled or broiled in the oven.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pasta with basil and garlic
directions: Combine and stir to blend all ingredients.
Cook pasta until al dente.
Toss hot pasta with sauce.

title: chick and chips
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease dish.
Mix evaporated milk and poultry seasoning in deep plate.
Spread crushed chips on another deep plate.
Dip each chicken piece first in milk mixture, then in chips.
Place in baking dish.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes, or until meat is tender.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend the cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Add peanut butter and Cool Whip and blend well.
Pour in baked shells.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: wasetti
directions: I half this recipe and prefer to use all ground beef.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Boil chicken, debone and save 1 cup of broth.
Cook noodles (I usually cook them in the chicken broth).
Combine all ingredients. Cook at 350° for about 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: sausage and chilies casserole
directions: Pat sausage into 8 patties; fry and drain on paper towels. Place in a 9-inch square baking dish.
Spoon chopped chilies over sausage.
Sprinkle cheese over chilies.
Beat eggs with salt and pepper; pour over sausage, chilies and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until eggs are set.

title: miss katie's brownie pie
directions: Put eggs, sugar, cocoa, milk and vanilla in blender and mix well.
Add melted oleo.
Pour into frozen pie crust.
Bake about 1 hour in a 325° oven.

title: cheese strips
directions: Mix all ingredients except for the bread.
Spread evenly over the bread and cut into 1-inch strips and place in the freezer on a cookie sheet.
When frozen, store in plastic bags in the freezer. Remove as needed.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: french toast
directions: Beat eggs, milk and cinnamon in deep dish. Set aside. Drop a pat of butter into frying pan over medium heat until melted. Dip bread slices one at a time in egg batter; coat both sides. Don't soak, just get bread good and wet. Put bread slice into pan and cook both sides until golden brown. Serve with maple syrup.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine onion, carrots, celery, ham and butter.
Fry until onions brown.
Stir in water.
Add potatoes, half and half, parsley and chives.
Cook 1/2 to 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Thicken with 1/2 cup cornstarch dissolved in water.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Put oleo, flour and 3/4 cup pecans into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Let cool.
Mix powdered sugar and softened cream cheese along with 2 tablespoons milk.
Spread over crust.
Spread 1/2 of Cool Whip over this.

title: corn bread loaf or muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Blend wet ingredients.
Stir wet with dry just until blended.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full and bake at 350° for approximately 12 to 15 minutes .
Watch carefully and test with a toothpick for doneness.

title: chocolate "philly" fudge
directions: Gradually add sugar to softened cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in greased 8-inch square dish.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Makes 1 3/4 pounds.
This is very easy and delicious!

title: coconut fried shrimp
directions: Wash shrimp and pat dry.
Dip into batter.
Then lightly press into coconut, all sides. Then fry in oil.
Shrimp floats when done. Coconut turns light golden.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes, remove stems and halve crosswise.
Place cut side up in a lightly greased baking dish.
Sprinkle lightly with salt, pepper and red pepper.
Spread each with mustard.
Mix together margarine, bread crumbs and cheese.
Spread mixture over tomatoes.
Bake in a 350` oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth. Pour into 9-inch buttered pie plate.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°. Take out of oven but leave oven on. After 20 minutes, make topping.

title: round steak meal
directions: Cut round steak into 1/2-inch strips.
Brown in skillet. (Steak should not be overcooked, slightly brown is sufficient.) Add mushroom soup and water.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes over low heat.
Add beans, tomatoes and mushrooms.
Stir and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: brown bread
directions: Boil raisins and water for 5 minutes.
Mix with rest of ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry salad or dessert
directions: Mix the gelatin and boiling water.
Add pie filling and pineapple to jello mixture when cool.
Let set in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Top with the sour cream, mixed with the softened cream cheese.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut off tops of peppers and clean out centers.
Place peppers in boiling water for just 3 or 4 minutes, then take up and drain. Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add rice, tomatoes, 1/2 cup water and dash of Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes. Stir in cheese, then stuff peppers.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fudge nougats
directions: Combine in pan	the
sugar, evaporated milk and butter. Bring to a full
rolling boil; boil hard for 10 minutes.	Stir occasionally.
Blend
in
chocolate,
flour,
graham
cracker crumbs, walnuts and
vanilla;
mix	well.
Spread in well buttered 12 x 18-inch pan.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Mix together to make soft dough.
Divide into three parts, roll very thin and cut in strips.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Cook in broth until done.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together margarine, sour cream and eggs.
Stir in whole kernel corn and creamed corn.
Then stir in corn muffin mix. Grease 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Rinse and pat dry the chicken breasts.
Dredge in 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, pat in the cheese into the flesh and lightly dredge in flour.
In a nonstick skillet, heat the butter until the foam begins to subside.
Saute the breasts over medium-high heat, until it is golden on each side.
Transfer to a baking dish, pour the vermouth over it and sprinkle with the remaining 1 tablespoon of Parmesan.
Bake, covered loosely, in a preheated 325° oven for 15 minutes.
Serve with a green vegetable or salad. Serves 2.

title: tamale pie(main dish casserole)
directions: Cook meat until onions and pepper are soft; simmer 5 minutes. Stir in corn meal.
Blend in the cup of water.
Simmer 10 minutes. Add other ingredients and stir together.
Place in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Add all together, adding zucchini last.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.
Freezes very well.

title: texas chocolate sheet cake
directions: Combine sugar and flour in bowl.
Set aside.
On stove, stir water, oil and cocoa until boiling.
Pour over dry ingredients and beat with mixer.
Add eggs, baking soda and buttermilk.
Stir well.
Pour into greased 10 x 15-inch sheet pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: banana cake
directions: Grease and flour bottom of pans.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 350°.
This cake is rich.
It doesn't need icing.

title: shrimp butter
directions: After coming to room temperature, cream the butter and cream cheese.
Add lemon juice, mayonnaise and onion.
Drain and add the shrimp.
Chill.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Mix well shortening, brown sugar and egg.
Add buttermilk. Sift together and stir in dry ingredients.
Mix in pecans, dates and candied cherries.
Chill dough 1 hour.
Drop with teaspoon about 2 inches apart onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Top each cookie with a pecan half or half a candied cherry.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400° (moderately hot).
Makes 4 dozen.

title: crab casserole
directions: Melt butter in pan and add flour. Thicken with milk.
Remove from stove. Add beaten egg, mayonnaise, green pepper and seasoning. Fold in crabmeat.
Top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for about 1 hour, then pour sauce over entire meat loaf.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add Starter, oil and water.
Mix ingredients well.
Put dough in a large greased bowl, turning once to coat with oil on all sides.
Cover lightly with foil; let stand overnight or until dough has more than doubled.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, salt, nutmeg and vanilla.
Beat at low speed until sugar and eggs are dissolved.
Eggs will be lemon color. Continue mix.
Add milk that has been scalded or heated.
Pour into unbaked pie shell; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° in small (8 x 8-inch) pan.

title: cherry yum yums
directions: Melt margarine and mix with crumbs.
Press 1/2 crumbs into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla. Beat Dream Whip and half and half.
Add to cheese mixture.
Pour half of the mixture onto cracker crust.
Add cherries and top with remaining cheese.
Top with remaining crumbs.

title: fruit shake
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and mix until fully blended. This refreshing breakfast shake can be made with bananas, strawberries, peaches, cantaloupe or just about any fruit that you enjoy.
Be sure to freeze fruit the night before.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
together and beat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour
in	greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken and vegetables in a foil packet
directions: Tear off 4 sheets of heavy duty aluminum foil (18 x 14-inches). Brush with oil.
Divide vegetables evenly among the foil sheets. Brush with oil.
Top with chicken quarters, skin side up, brushing with remaining oil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bring the top half of foil over chicken; fold open edges in a series of lock folds.
Grill over medium direct heat for 40 minutes or bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes, until chicken is tender.
Open foil packets carefully and serve.
Serves 4.

title: nana's chicken-n-dumplings
directions: Brown onions in oil.
Place chicken in pan with onions and cover with water.
Cook approximately 1/2 hour over medium heat. Slice carrots and add.
Sprinkle with parsley and paprika (enough to color top of broth).
Cook about 1/2 hour or until carrots are done.
Broth should just cover top of ingredients at this point. Pour sour cream in and stir well.
Fill sour cream container 1/2 way with water and 3 tablespoons flour.
Shake well and mix slowly into broth.
Stir until smooth.
(End mixture should be slightly thick and creamy.)

title: apple dumplings
directions: Prepare dough for crust; per package directions.
Roll into 6 circles, 6-inches in diameter.
Peel and core apples; dice into cubes and divide into 6 equal piles.
Place each pile of apples in a round of dough and form into balls, shaping as you would a snowball.
Place crimped side down; arrange all 6 balls in a glass baking dish.
Pour over with a mixture made from the water, sugar, nutmeg, vanilla and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Watch closely!

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine and store in airtight container.
Use 6 tablespoons to 1 cup hot water.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream together sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla, then dry ingredients, mixing well.
Stir in chopped apples.
Batter may be stiff.
Pour into nonstick sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped topping and nuts, if desired (walnuts or pecans).

title: broccoli-carrot stir-fry
directions: For sauce, in a bowl stir together orange juice and cornstarch. Set aside.
Preheat wok or large skillet over high heat.
Add oil. Stir-fry ginger root for 15 seconds.
Add carrots and stir-fry 1 minute.
Add broccoli and stir-fry for 3 to 4 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Push vegetables from center of wok or skillet.
Stir sauce; add to center of wok.
Cook and stir until thickened, 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in vegetables and walnuts to coat.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: grilled chicken teriyaki
directions: Combine all ingredients listed and marinate overnight if possible.
Cook chicken (10 to 15 minutes) on foil on the barbecue grill.
Use the marinade juice to baste chicken while cooking. Serve with rice and a salad.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and oil; beat well.
Combine dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture and beat well.
Stir in apples and nuts (batter will be stiff).
Spoon into 10-inch greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: red bean gallop
directions: Cook meat, celery and onions for about 15 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients and cook for 15 minutes longer.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Combine chicken, noodles and broccoli in a large casserole dish.
Stir in cheese, sour cream and soups.
Top with onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 50 minutes.

title: shrimp spread
directions: In small mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in lemon juice.
Stir in rest of ingredients. Chill to blend flavor.
Garnish as desired.
Serve with crackers or fresh vegetables.

title: mom's rice pudding
directions: Cook rice in 3 or 3 1/2 cups of milk.
Mix in a bowl eggs, sugar, cinnamon and vanilla.
After rice is done, add bowl mixture into rice; then cook until thickened.

title: peanut butter and jelly french toast
directions: Spread peanut butter on six slices of bread; spread jelly on other six slices of bread.
Put one slice of each together to form sandwiches.

title: drumstick treat frozen dessert
directions: Mix the vanilla wafer crumbs, peanuts and melted margarine. Set aside 1/4 cup for the topping.
Pat the rest into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix the cream cheese, peanut butter and powdered sugar until creamy.
Add 2 cups of the whipped topping.
Spread over cooled crust.
Set in refrigerator.
Combine pudding and 3 cups milk.
Beat well.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate until set.
Spread remaining 2 cups of whipped topping over pudding layer.
Sprinkle with the remaining 1/4 cup of crumb topping.
Cover with foil and freeze. Serve partially frozen.

title: frozen pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour (in a dishpan or other large container).
Dissolve salt in water and mix into flour along with the syrup.
Divide dough into portions for 1 crust, shaping each portion into a ball.
Place balls in individual vapor-proof bags (such as Ziploc that can be sealed) and freeze.
When ready to use, thaw and roll out on floured board. This is just as good after it has been frozen as before and does not get soggy.
It takes time to mix, but it is worth the trouble.
Makes approximately 20 single crusts.

title: granola bars
directions: Toast oats in shallow baking pan in preheated 350° oven for
8 minutes.
Melt together butter, brown sugar, peanut butter and syrup in saucepan over low heat.
Add toasted oats mixture, peanuts and egg.
Mix well.
Press firmly into well-greased jelly pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: never fail dill pickles
directions: Pack washed cucumbers in jars.
While packing, add dill, garlic and yellow pepper (if desired).
In the top of each jar, put powdered alum.
Combine water, vinegar and pickling salt. Heat to boiling, then pour over cucumbers.
Add hot lids and process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
Makes enough liquid for 2 bottles.

title: peas in the pod
directions: Cook new garden pea pods (before peas are fully formed) in salted water until pods are tender.
Season with butter and salt. Eat with fingers, pods and all.

title: tangerine blush punch
directions: In pitcher, combine all ingredients.
Serve over ice in tall glasses garnished with orange slices.
Makes 6 servings.

title: green beans with shallots
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter with the oil in a small skillet. Add shallots and cook 7 to 9 minutes over low heat, stirring occasionally, until very tender.
Stir in remaining butter, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Cook green beans, uncovered, in a large pot of water 5 to 7 minutes until crisp-tender. Drain well. Add shallots, butter and parsley.
Toss to mix and coat.
Makes 15 servings.
Shallot butter may be made up to 5 days ahead.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts on top or put in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Let chopped cabbage stand in cold water 1 hour.
Drain and dry (pat with cloth).
Add nuts and marshmallows.
Stir together.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in water, stir in orange juice and next 3 ingredients.
Pour into large plastic container (milk jug works well) freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer 1 hour before serving.
Place into punch bowl and break into chunks, pour soda or ale over and serve.
Makes 6 qts.

title: garlic popcorn
directions: In a medium saucepan, pour in olive oil, just enough to coat the bottom of the pan. Add in garlic cloves and simmer until golden brown. Add 3 kernels. Shake pan constantly until they are all popped, then add the rest and shake until completely popped. Transfer into bowl and enjoy!

title: eclair dessert
directions: Mix pudding and milk until thickened.
Blend in Cool Whip. In baking pan, layer graham crackers, pudding mix, graham crackers, pudding mix, graham crackers and frosting.

title: never fail lemon bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into greased cookie sheet with sides.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
When cooled, frost with glaze.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and salt in top of a double boiler. Add milk slowly and stir and cook over heat until boiling point is reached.
Place over hot water and cook approximately 20 minutes. Add well beaten egg yolks and butter; cook for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Cool and turn into cooked pastry shell.
Spread with meringue made from egg whites and bake until meringue is brown.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar and add to vegetables. Add peanuts just before serving.

title: goulash
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Brown hamburger, bell pepper and onion together.
Cook macaroni until almost done.
Grease casserole dish.
Pour macaroni and hamburger mixture
into casserole.
Pour soup and water over mixture.
Add salt and pepper.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Mix everything together except tortillas.
Break one dozen tortillas; put in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Alternate layers of tortillas and meat mixture, ending with meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Cream butter with shortening, sugar and eggs until light and fluffy. Add flour, baking powder and salt alternately with milk. Add flavoring and walnuts. Stir with spoon; grease and flour tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes. Test with toothpick.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg, butter and pecans together. Press into pan. Mix together cream cheese, 3 eggs, vanilla and powdered sugar. Pour over cake. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, ginger (if used) and salt.
Stir in chicken, grapes, celery, green onions and walnuts (if used).
Cover and chill.
Makes 5 1/2 cups.
