title: grilled pork or beef appetizers
directions: Cut pork or beef into bite-size thin strips.
Peel and cut pineapple into bite-size chunks.
Clean and cut green pepper into 3/4-inch squares.
Combine soy sauce, salad oil, sugar, cinnamon, garlic, red pepper sauce and cloves in a bowl and mix.
Add meat. Mix.
Cover and refrigerate about 2 hours, stirring 2 or 3 times. Drain meat.
Save marinade.
String meat, pineapple and green pepper on heavy bamboo skewers.
Arrange on cooking grill over drip pan.
Cover kettle and cook 5 to 10 minutes for beef and 10 to 15 minutes for pork or until meat is done, baste with marinade during cooking.
Turn 2 or 3 times.
Protect hands with asbestos gloves before turning kabobs.

title: dip for strawberries
directions: Mix well and store in refrigerator until ready to serve. Good for any kind of fruit.

title: broccoli florentine
directions: Cook broccoli until barely done. Drain. Heat garlic and oil in a skillet. Add broccoli and saute until tender, turning occasionally. Season with salt, pepper and a generous sprinkling of Parmesan cheese.

title: riz biscuits
directions: Sift together the flour, soda, salt and sugar. Dissolve yeast in lukewarm buttermilk. Cut shortening into flour mixture as for biscuits. Stir buttermilk into dry ingredients quickly. Turn dough out onto floured cloth and knead just until smooth. Roll to 1/4-inch thickness and cut with a biscuit cutter. Brush top of each round with melted butter.
Place one biscuit on top of another, making double biscuits. Cover and place in a warm place to rise until light and doubled, about 1 hour. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in the hot water.
Add cranberry sauce; stir to dissolve.
Add pineapple, juice and celery.

title: fabulous fudge
directions: Combine
milk,	sugar
and butter.
Stir and bring to a boil. Boil
minutes,	stirring occasionally.	Remove from heat and add chocolate pieces.
Stir and add vanilla and nuts. Pour in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill and cut in squares.

title: raspberry lemon muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Combine eggs, milk, oil and lemon extract; stir into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Fold in raspberries.
Spoon into 18 muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: saucy chicken with mushrooms(makes 6 servings)
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°. Place chicken in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with Italian seasoning, 1/8 teaspoon salt and pepper. Pour wine over chicken. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Remove chicken to a serving dish, reserving 2/3 cup drippings in a saucepan. Combine flour and water. Stir into reserved pan drippings. Add carrot and remaining 1/8 teaspoon salt and bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Add mushrooms and cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and stir in sour cream. Spoon sauce over chicken. Garnish with fresh oregano or thyme sprigs, if desired.

title: cereal cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening together. Add eggs and mix well. Add salt, soda and flour. Mix. Add remaining ingredients and drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheets. Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: smear cheese
directions: Chop eggs, onion and olives fine.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Serve on crackers and celery.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine jello and undrained pineapple over low heat until jello dissolves.
Cool.
Stir in Cool Whip, buttermilk and nuts.
Let set until congealed.

title: eggnog
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add vanilla ice cream.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: summer corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; toss well.
Let marinate overnight. Serve chilled.

title: funshine cookies
directions: *A.J.'s is strawberry preserves.

title: taglarina
directions: Cook noodles in a large pot according to package directions. Brown hamburger and onions.
When noodles are done, drain them. To the noodles add all the other ingredients except the cheese. Mix thoroughly and place in a 9 X 13
or other casserole pan.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees until cheese melts.

title: anytime soup
directions: Shred or chop the cabbage.
Add the remaining ingredients in large pan.
Bring to a boil, lower heat and simmer 45 minutes. This is a good fat free soup.

title: pepper steaks
directions: Brown meat on all sides in butter.
Add onions, seasoning and water.
Cover and cook slowly for about 1 hour.
Add green pepper, tomatoes and cornstarch, blended with 2 tablespoons water.
Cook until thick.
Serve on rice.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crusts, in a large mixing bowl.
Beat until all lumps are out of the potatoes.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie crusts.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Combine eggs, buttermilk and margarine.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: corn bake
directions: Mix all together; bake in an 8 x 8-inch greased pan at 350° for approximately 40 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: butterscotch yams
directions: Cook yams, peel and quarter.
Arrange yams in single layer in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in 325° oven for 15 minutes. In a 2-quart saucepan, combine remaining ingredients, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil over medium heat and boil 5 minutes. Pour over yams.
Bake, basting frequently for 15 minutes longer, or until glazed.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet and sour beef
directions: Brown beef in butter in skillet; stir in flour.
Combine remaining ingredients, except rice.
Add to meat mixture.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Makes 8 servings.
Freezes well.

title: mexi-salad
directions: In a med. saucepan heat oil on med heat.
Add garlic, seasoning, and saute for a minute.
Add beans and mix well, add salt and pepper.
Saute for 5 minutes.
Add picante sauce.
Remove from heat.

title: fruit salad
directions: Prepare pudding; use only 2 cups milk.
Fold in Cool Whip; set aside.
Drain fruits; cut into chunks.
Fold fruits into pudding mixture, except bananas.
Put in covered container and refrigerate.
Just before serving, slice bananas into mixture.

title: raspberry delight
directions: Combine crumbs, nuts and butter.
Pat in 8 x 10-inch pan. Place marshmallows and milk in double boiler over hot water.
Stir until melted.
Cool.
Fold whipped cream into marshmallows.
Pour over crust.
Cook raspberries, sugar, lemon juice and cornstarch with 1/4 cup water until clear; cool.
Pour over marshmallow mixture.
Best if made several hours before serving.
Garnish with more whipped cream, if desired.

title: butterscotch rounds
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in each of two 8 or 9-inch layer pans.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup brown sugar and 1/4 cup pecan halves over butter in each pan.
In large mixer bowl, dissolve yeast in hot water.
Add 1 1/3 cups of the flour and the remaining ingredients. Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 2 minutes high speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in remaining flour.
Drop batter by tablespoonfuls over mixture in pans; let rise in warm place (85°) 50 minutes.
(Dough will not double.)

title: untidy joseph's (sloppy joes)
directions: Brown hamburger and drain juices.
Then add other ingredients. Add a can of chicken gumbo soup for a different taste.
(This makes it more like a Sloppy Joe; very good.)

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown cut up smokie links in a large, nonstick skillet.
Add rice, zucchini and onions.
Cook and stir about 3 minutes.
To this mixture, add tomatoes, tomato sauce, water, mustard, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer 15 minutes or until zucchini is cooked to your liking.
Sprinkle cheese on top; heat just to melt.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: double baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes 1 to 1 1/2 hours until done.
Cut in half or slice off piece of skin on potatoes.
Scoop out potatoes from skins.
Put in large bowl and beat, adding milk, butter, sour cream, salt and chives.
You may use more or less milk, butter and sour cream according to your taste.
Spoon back into each potato skin.
Bake again until heated through.
Can be made ahead and stored until ready to use.

title: snickers salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip with softened cream cheese.
Add fruit.
Mix together with spoon.
Crush 3 or 4 frozen Snicker bars with a hammer and mix in with fruit.

title: crab dip
directions: Drain crab meat.
Add mayonnaise and then add other ingredients.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: pizza fritta
directions: Allow dough to reach room temperature.
Cut or break off pieces of dough and stretch to approximately 3 to 4-inch circles, 1/4-inch thick.
Place pieces on dish towels and cover with other dish towels (to prevent formation of crust).
Place oil about 1/2-inch deep in large skillet.
Heat oil over heat (medium to hot). Drop tiny piece of dough in oil to test if hot enough. Drop dough pieces in oil and turn when 1 side is light brown.
Turn to brown the other side.
Remove with tongs or slotted spoon.
Drain on paper towels. Continue to brown remainder of dough.
You can top with your choice of the sugar, cinnamon, butter or honey, or eat plain without any toppings.

title: country supper
directions: Fry sliced potatoes, carrots, celery and onions in bacon drippings or oil over low heat in heavy skillet. Season with salt and pepper to taste. When carrots and potatoes are tender, place sausage on top. Cover and heat about 12 minutes. Makes a hearty meal for 4.

title: rice krispies squares
directions: Measure margarine into large saucepan; melt over low heat. Add marshmallows and cook, stirring constantly, until marshmallows are melted and mixture is very syrupy.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies cereal; stir until well coated.
Spread warm mixture in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Using waxed paper or greased spatula, press firmly into an even layer.
Cut into squares when cool.
Yield: 24 squares, 2 x 2-inches.

title: carrot pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients; add gradually to butter-egg mixture.
Add vanilla, carrots, pineapple, coconut and nuts.
Pour into pan; bake until done, about 45 minutes to 1 hour. Remove from oven and let cool.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: almond tea
directions: Brew tea.
Combine all ingredients.
Before serving, add water to make 1/2 gallon of tea.
This may be doubled to make 1 gallon.

title: mutinys
directions: Blend together and serve.

title: stuffed cheese rolls
directions: Cut tops off of rolls; reserve.
Remove inside of roll. Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Place filling in each roll. Replace reserved top.
Wrap each roll in waxed paper, twisting ends.
Heat at 250° for 30 minutes in flat pan.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Saute celery, bell pepper, and onions in margarine for about 15 minutes. Add broth and soups; add salt, pepper, and garlic powder. Add chicken to mixture and simmer while cooking spaghetti. Drain spaghetti; add to sauce mixture and mix well. Place in large baking dish and cover with shredded cheese. Cover with foil and let set till cheese is melted.

title: meatball chowder
directions: Combine meat, seasoned salt, pepper, eggs, parsley, cracker crumbs and milk; mix thoroughly.
Form balls the size of walnuts; brown balls in frying pan.
Put in the soup mixture and cook until the vegetables are done.

title: low country beef and rice
directions: In a large pot with lid, put in stew beef.
Cover with water. Bring to a boil, then simmer about 3 hours.
Add water when needed.
When meat is tender, add salt and pepper, onion and rice. Cook 20 minutes longer.
Keep lid on pot at all times.

title: steak marinade for grilling
directions: Mix together in large pan and marinade overnight.
Enough for a large steak or 8 pork chops.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Mix Ragu in hamburger.
Put a little of the hamburger mixture in the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Layer with noodles, hamburger, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Keep layering until hamburger is all gone.
Pour 1 cup water around the edge of pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: venison roast
directions: In a roaster, mix the soups and water.
Add the chopped onion. Add roast, salt and pepper.
Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, until tender and meat falls off the bone.

title: cheesy polenta(cornmeal)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. In a large saucepan, saute onions in butter.
Add water, bring to boil.
Gradually add cornmeal, stirring constantly.
Add half and half, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese and salt.
Spread half of cornmeal mixture into pan.
Sprinkle with more cheese and 1/3 of the Mozzarella.
Spread rest of cornmeal on top and sprinkle with remaining two cheeses.
Bake 20 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pour into crust.
Refrigerate.

title: rhubarb freezer jam
directions: Mix rhubarb and sugar.
Let set 8 hours or overnight.
Boil 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and add crushed pineapple and jello. Stir and put in containers.
Makes about 3 1/2 pints.

title: lemon-lime punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: molasses mocha icing(good!!)
directions: Combine all ingredients except	powdered sugar and nuts. Sift sugar into liquid and beat well. Add enough sugar to make icing the consistency to spread. Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Yield: Enough to ice between 3 (8-inch) layers.

title: pineapple-banana pie(lo-cal)
directions: Cook pudding, mixed with sugar substitute, pineapple juice and milk, until it thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add pineapple and vanilla.
Mix well.
Slice banana over cooked pie crust.
Pour pudding over banana.
Serves eight.

title: squash puppies
directions: Slice squash. Cover with water and cook over medium heat until done. Drain, mash and drain again. Combine all ingredients and drop mixture by scant tablespoons into hot oil (350°) for several minutes until golden brown. Drain on paper towels. Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: ranch potato salad
directions: Peel, boil and dice potatoes.
Slice celery and chop onion. Combine dressing with mayonnaise and water.
Stir well and add to potatoes.
Toss to coat.
Chill.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: oven swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into six serving portions.
Combine flour and salt; with meat mallet, pound 2 tablespoons of mixture into meat on both sides.
Brown meat on both sides in shortening.
Transfer meat into 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish and blend remaining 2 tablespoons flour into skillet drippings.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, celery, carrots and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly; pour over meat.
Bake steak, covered, in 350° oven for about 1 hour and 20 minutes or until tender.

title: chocolate pom pom balls
directions: Mix confectioners sugar, butter, peanut butter and Rice Krispies; roll into 1-inch balls.
Cook chocolate and butterscotch chips and paraffin wax in double boiler until shiny.
Dip balls in coating and let sit on wax paper for 5 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: elise's spiced tea
directions: Mix all together.
Use about 2 teaspoons per cup.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients; set aside.
Meanwhile, saute hamburger.
Season with salt and pepper.
Drain off fat.
Prepare onion, cheese, jalapenos and pimentos; place in separate mounds. Grease and heat iron skillet.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons corn meal and brown slightly. Pour 1/2 batter in skillet.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over batter, then meat, onion, pepper and pimento. Pour remaining batter over top.
Bake 50 minutes in 350° oven until brown on top.

title: oatmeal coconut coronets
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease baking sheets.
Cream the shortening and sugars.
Add eggs one at a time.
Sift together the dry ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Blend in coconut, oatmeal and vanilla.
Drop onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° until lightly browned.
They freeze well.
Yields 6 to 7 dozen.

title: chicken in creamy white sauce
directions: Arrange seasoned chicken in shallow baking dish so that pieces don't overlap.
Mix undiluted mushroom soup, mushrooms, wine, cornstarch, sour cream, basil and garlic until blended.
Pour over chicken, completely covering it.
Dust with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Super dish to serve company.

title: chicken tomato soup
directions: Boil chicken stock, chicken and onion until chicken is cooked and onion falls apart.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until macaroni is cooked.
Enjoy!

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine salmon, crumbs, onion, margarine and salt in a bowl. Combine milk and egg and mix thoroughly.
Shape into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Follow directions on roll mix, but do not add egg or let it rise.
After dough is mixed, roll out immediately on a floured surface into a rectangle shape.
Mix cheeses together and spread on top of dough.
Lay pepperoni on top of cheeses.
Add spices. Roll up tightly like a jelly roll.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes on a baking sheet.
Brush with melted margarine over loaf and bake for 5 more minutes.
Let cool before cutting.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and work into balls.
Flatten slightly when placing on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 40 to 50 minutes.
When cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: gram ward's date cake
directions: Stir soda and water into dates.
Cream sugar, eggs and margarine.
Add dates, flour, baking powder and nuts.
Batter will be very thin.
Pour into prepared 9 x 13-inch or slightly smaller pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until it springs back when touched.
Needs no frosting.
Very good with whipped cream.

title: veal or chicken scaloppini
directions: In a small bowl, combine the flour, salt and pepper. In another bowl, lightly beat the egg. Dip veal or chicken in egg and then coat with flour mixture.

title: chipped beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole. Let set for 6 to 12 hours in a cold place.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: barbecue smokies
directions: Use equal portions of jelly and mustard to make sauce.
Use 1 to 1 1/2 cups sauce per pound of sausage.
Blend jelly and mustard to smooth and even consistency.
Layer in crock-pot on low heat until sauce is thick and dark or bake in a shallow baking pan at 350° in gas oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Put ingredients into a microwave-safe bowl and microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir at 3 minutes.
Continue heating for the other 2 minutes.
Once done, don't stir again.
Pour over already popped popcorn.

title: mexican chicken corn chowder
directions: Melt butter in a Dutch oven over medium high heat and add chicken, onion and garlic and saute for 10 minutes.
Stir in next seven ingredients and cook over low heat, stirring often for 15 minutes.
Stir in cilantro and serve.

title: brownie pizza
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and place in well-greased pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brownies pull away from pan.
Sprinkle chopped Reese's cups and mini marshmallows on top.
Return to oven for 5 minutes or until marshmallows are fluffy.
Remove from oven and spread M&M's on top.
Let cool and cut in small squares.

title: far east celery
directions: Cook celery in small amount of salted water until barely tender.
Drain celery and place in casserole.
Add pimento, water chestnuts and soup.
Stir carefully until fairly well blended. Melt butter in small saucepan; add bread crumbs and almonds.
Toss. Place mixture over top of casserole; bake in 350° oven until brown, about 35 minutes.
Serves 6 to 7.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: By hand, mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Add dry ingredients, then nuts and strawberries.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Yields 2 loaves or 3 coffee-can rounds.

title: raisin puffs
directions: Cook raisins and water until water is gone.
Blend final ingredients, mix well.
Roll into small balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 mins.

title: spanish rice
directions: In medium frying pan, over medium heat, add oil. Add rice, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned. add garlic and onion and stir constantly until garlic is brown. Add tomato sauce. Continue to stir 1 minute. Add broth and seasonings.
Stir well and let cook until half the broth is absorbed. Cover pan, lower heat and let simmer until all liquid is absorbed. This should take 15 to 20 minutes, total.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Cream 1/2 cup oleo and 3/4 cup sugar; beat until light.
Add egg and beat well.
Sift 2 cups flour with baking powder and salt; add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Beat until smooth. Fold in berries.
Blend remaining 1/4 cup oleo, 1/2 cup sugar, 1/3 cup flour and cinnamon.
Sprinkle topping over batter.
Bake in greased 9 x 9-inch pan at 375° for about 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean (350° if using glass pan).

title: hamburger pizza
directions: Mix Bisquick with water.
Roll crust out and place in two pie pans.
Spread a little oil inside crust with pastry brush.
Divide ground chuck and place in pie pans.
Sprinkle salt, pepper, garlic salt and oregano on each pie.
Top with 1/2 can tomato sauce each and cheese slices.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cube eggplant.
Boil in small amount of water; set to cool.
Do not drain and mash with fork.
Saute onion in 1 stick oleo; add cheese, eggs, salt, pepper and soda and add to eggplant. Bake in greased casserole dish in 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Then add buttered bread crumbs over top and bake for another 10 minutes or until browned.

title: gringo cabbage
directions: Chop cabbage coarsely into large pan; add 1/2 teaspoon salt. Cover with boiling water; boil for 7 minutes and drain.
Place half of cabbage in shallow baking dish.
Make white sauce with butter, flour, salt, pepper and milk.
Pour half of sauce over cabbage.
Sprinkle with half the cheese and half the bread crumbs. Layer with the remaining cabbage, cheese and crumbs.
Pour remaining white sauce over top.
I sprinkle can of Durkee onions over the top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: extra crispy chicken
directions: Place crushed corn flakes, Parmesan cheese and pepper in a large plastic bag that zips shut.
Beat egg in a separate bowl.

title: chocolate tea bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Mix nuts and biscuit mix; set aside.
Put remaining ingredients into blender; blend until smooth.
Add biscuit mix and nuts; mix until moistened.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: oatmeal caramel apple cake
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed. Stir in apples and nuts.
Pour into a lightly greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs lightly in a large bowl; stir in oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt onto wax paper.
Stir into egg mixture until well blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Spoon batter into well-greased 8 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 1 hour or until center springs back when lightly pressed.
Cool in pans on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely.

title: broiled stuffed mushrooms
directions: Into food processor or blender, put mushroom stems, bacon, bread and seasonings.
Cover and process 15 seconds or until chopped.
Remove to bowl; moisten with 2 tablespoons butter.
Roll mushroom caps in remaining butter.
Fill with mixture; arrange in broiling pan.
Broil 4 inches from heat until stuffing is browned and mushrooms tender.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Add ingredients to onions and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Cook spare ribs in water; drain water off and add sauce to ribs.
Cook until tender, about 1 hour.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients.
Chill before serving.
May be served with crackers, chips or raw vegetables.

title: quick italian chicken
directions: Cut chicken breasts into finger size pieces no more than 1/2 inch thick.
Wash thoroughly and pat dry.
Dredge in flour seasoning and fry until golden brown all over in olive oil over medium heat, turning frequently.
Drain any excess oil.
Cover chicken with spaghetti sauce and sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and simmer over very low heat for about 15 minutes or until cheese has melted.
Serve.

title: cheese cake
directions: Blend cake mix, butter and 1 egg together. Spread or pat mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend powdered sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs together with mixer.
Spread over the first layer.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecan pie delight
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients except 2/3 cup cake mix. Pour into 9x13 greased pan, bake at 350° 20-25 min.

While this cooks mix 2/3 c. cake mix with the syrups, beaten eggs and brown sugar, mix for 3 min. add vanilla, stir in pecans; pour onto hot cooked cake and return to oven for 40 min. or till filling is set.

title: we're number 1 pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat thoroughly	after
each
addition.	Add flour alternately with milk;
stir
in
vanilla.
Pour into greased tube or Bundt pan and bake at
for	1 hour and 45 minutes.	Reduce heat to 275° for 15 minutes longer.

title: yeast potato biscuits
directions: Mix in order given.
Let stand overnight in a large bowl. This will double in size until morning.
Knead in flour until a nice texture.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Let rise about 2 hours, until double in size.
Grease pans.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes, until light brown.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Mix egg yolks, sugar, milk and oil.
Add crumbs, salt and baking powder; fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350° in an oblong greased and floured pan.

title: hawaiian chops
directions: Trim excess fat from pork chops.
Coat meat with mixture of flour, salt and pepper; brown in greased skillet.
Combine vinegar and remaining ingredients; pour over chops.
Cover; simmer 45 minutes or until done.
Makes 6 servings.
Serve over cooked rice or noodles.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender. Reserve 1 cup broth. Tear chicken into small pieces; layer bottom of dish. Heat milk, soups and butter in pan until butter melts; pour over chicken. Mix stuffing with 1 cup chicken broth. Layer on top of chicken in casserole pan. Bake at 370° for 50 minutes.

title: fish marinade
directions: Mix ingredients.
Immerse fish 1 hour, turning once. I use a Ziploc bag.

title: bacon wrapped shrimp
directions: Take jumbo shrimp; wrap 1/2 slice bacon around each one. Secure with toothpicks or put on skewers; cook on barbecue grill until bacon is crisp, approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Brush with barbecue sauce.

title: easy gingerbread bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Combine first 4 ingredients in large mixing bow. Beat at medium speed until creamy. Add next 4 ingredients; reduce speed to low. Beat until well mixed. Press dough into ungreased 15 x 10 x 1 inch jelly roll pan. Sprinkle with sugar. Bake for 16 - 20 minutes. Cool completely. Cut into desired shapes with cookie cutter or into bars. Makes approximately 48 bars.

title: green bean salad
directions: Marinate in juice for 24 hours.
Stir every now and then.

title: cheese soup
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Heat slowly.
Sticks very easily. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: hamburger noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles according to box.
While noodles are cooking, mix ground meat, onion, salt and pepper and tomato sauce in a 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole.
Drain noodles and cover top of ground meat mixture with the noodles.
Dot with butter and top with cheese slices.
Bake in 350°
oven for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: milky way bar cake
directions: Melt candy bars and 1/2 cup of butter in saucepan over low heat.
Beat remaining 1/2 cup of butter and sugar in bowl until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Add sifted flour and soda alternately with buttermilk, stirring until smooth.
Add melted candy; stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.
Top will be dark.

title: champagne cake
directions: Make yellow cake mix as directed; pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cool.
Mix together pudding, cream cheese and milk; mix until smooth with mixer.
Pour over cake; spread well the drained pineapple over mixture.
Spread Cool Whip over top; sprinkle chopped walnuts on top.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Cook sweet potato.
Cool, peel and mash to make 1/2 cup.
Blend milk into potato.
Set aside.
Sift together flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Cut in butter and margarine.
Beat in potato mixture with a fork.
Knead dough 3 times.
Roll out 1 1/2-inches thick.
Cut into rounds.
Bake 14 to 17 minutes in a 425° oven on greased baking sheet.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together.
Put in bread pan. Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 1 deep dish pie shell or 2 small pie shells.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pineapple delight pie
directions: Mix together ingredients and pour into shells.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: microwave baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 3-quart glass casserole dish. Cover with a paper towel.
Microwave 9 to 12 minutes or until beans are piping hot.
Stir twice during cooking.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: angels on horseback
directions: Cut bacon in half; place oysters in the center.
Sprinkle with seasonings and parsley.
Wrap bacon around oyster and secure with a toothpick.
Place in a shallow pan.
Bake at 450° for 8 minutes (until bacon is crisp).
Serve with lemon wedges.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: butter pecan sunrise
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and melted margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes. Cool.
Mix instant pudding and milk.
Add to ice cream.
Pour over crust and refrigerate 8 to 10 hours.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding mixture and sprinkle with 8 crushed Heath bars.

title: swiss style green beans
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Stir in sour cream.
Do not boil.
Add cheese and season with salt and pepper. Combine beans and cheese sauce in casserole dish.
Bake at 350 for 20-25 minutes.
Sprinkle with French fried onions and bake for 5 more minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Cook broccoli in microwave for 5 minutes.
Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan and mix with other ingredients.
Pour back into pan and bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Be sure and grease pan well.

title: pan-zit
directions: Saute pork chops, onions and bell peppers.
Drain, then add crab and shrimp; simmer for 10 minutes.
Prepare noodles as usual. Then make a noodle bed with meat sauce on top.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Simmer first 4 ingredients for 10 minutes, then add sugar to which cornstarch has been added.
Cook until clear.
Remove from fire and add egg yolks.
Pour into baked pie shell and cover with meringue.

title: honey pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients as given.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 400°.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook onions, green pepper and celery until tender in 1 tablespoon oil.
Add meat and brown.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until well blended.
Cook macaroni; add to mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Top with Parmesan cheese before baking.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Heat pineapple to boiling.
Add jello; stir until dissolved. Chill until partially set.
Soften cream cheese with 1/3 of the whipped cream.
Stir into jello mixture.
Add celery, nuts and cherries.
Let set a little longer.
Fold in remaining whipped cream.
Pour into mold.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, water and syrup to 260° or soft crack.
Add butter and peanuts.
Lower flame and stir constantly.
Bring to boil; cook until peanuts are done and turn to a golden brown (takes about 10 minutes).
Have ready vanilla and soda.
Add vanilla and soda and beat hard, just until foamy.
Pour out immediately onto buttered enameled tray.
(A regular cookie sheet is too thin.)
Do not spread with spoon or you will loose the bubbles. Get everything ready before starting because the last steps go so fast.
Use a heavy kettle for cooking.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans, in saucepan.
Place over medium heat;
bring to
a
boil.
When
mixture starts to boil, cook exactly 2
minutes,
stirring	constantly.
Pour in pecans. Stir quickly until pecans are coated and all syrup is absorbed. Pour out
on
ungreased
cookie
sheet.
Separate. Cool and serve.

title: beef and cheese foldovers
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onion.
Drain.
Add barbecue sauce.
Separate crescent rolls into rectangles.
(One package will equal 4 sections.)
Pinch seams together; pat dough thin.
Place a spoonful or 2 of meat mixture in center of crescent roll.
Place cheese slice on top of meat.
Fold crescent roll over meat like an envelope.
Pinch ends together.
Two cans equal 8 Foldovers.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and top with 1 box yellow cake mix mixed with 1 stick butter.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: heart healthy whole wheat bread
directions: This recipe is for a bread machine.
Follow the instructions given by your machine.
This recipe is for a 1 1/2 pound loaf, for a 1 pound loaf reduce by 1/3.

title: french toast
directions: Beat eggs and sugar for 1 minute.
Beat in rest of ingredients, except butter.
Pour over slices of bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Cook in butter until lightly browned.

title: scotch eggs
directions: Boil the potatoes and 4 eggs until done.
Mash the boiled potatoes and add salt and pepper to taste.
Add cilantro.
Mix well.

title: banana pudding
directions: Fold in above ingredients and layer in dish vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: boyfriend chocolate cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
In saucepan, bring cocoa, water, butter and shortening to a boil.
Pour over flour mixture.
Add beaten eggs.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Add buttermilk to cake batter.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
While cake is cooking, prepare Boyfriend Chocolate Icing.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Layer in a covered dish as listed.
Add a little salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Take off lid, brown for 15 minutes.

title: mom's chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt in a bowl.
In a sauce pan, bring margarine, Crisco, salt and water to a boil.
Add dry ingredients. Then add eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured 9x13 pan.
(I use two pans for thinner cake.)
Pour frosting on hot cake.

title: high protein eggnog
directions: Beat eggs.
Add whole milk and sugar.
Mix well.
Sprinkle powdered milk and flavoring over mixture.
Beat or blend until smooth.
Chill thoroughly before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: twinkie frosting
directions: Soften Crisco and margarine.
Don't melt!
Heat milk and flour to make a paste.
Add softened Crisco and sugar.
Add to cool paste.
Beat until fluffy.

title: almond chicken
directions: Dice pepper and onion.
Saute in butter in skillet.
Add chicken, salt, pepper and almonds.
Cover and simmer until tender.

title: ratatouille
directions: In medium saucepan with lid, saute onions and garlic in olive oil.
Remove/discard onions and garlic.
Add, in layers, remaining ingredients to saucepan.
Sprinkle with olive oil.
Cover and simmer over very low heat, 35 to 45 minutes.
Uncover and heat 10 minutes.
Serve over pasta, rice or couscous.

title: potato patties
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and mix well. Shape into 6 patties. Brown well in hot fat, about 4 minutes on each side. Yields 6.

title: rice mandarin(serves 8)
directions: Cook carrots and cauliflower in small amount of water.
Add beans and green onion.
Cook 1 minute longer.
Add mixture of water, Vegit seasoning, cornstarch or arrowroot powder and garlic. Cook and stir until thickened.
Vegetables should be crisp. Serve over brown rice and top with slivered almonds.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: First mix oatmeal, boiling water and salt.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Cream oleo, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add all this to the oatmeal mixture.
Sift flour, soda and cinnamon and add to mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Mix all together in stock pot. Cook over medium-low heat until vegetables are about done. Add shrimp or clams or any desired seafood. Cook until seafood and vegetables are done. Serve over rice.

title: blueberry cassis pie
directions: Add salt and vanilla to egg whites.
Beat until foamy. Add sugar in slow stream; continue beating until egg whites form shiny peaks.
Combine remaining ingredients; fold into mixture. Spread in well-greased and floured 9-inch pie pan, making the rim slightly higher than center.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: angel-whip cherry dessert
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Prepare jello following package directions using 2 cups boiling water and 1 cup cold.
Prepare pudding following package directions.
In mixing bowl combine slightly set jello and slightly cooled pudding.
Beat mixture about 2 minutes.
Mix in fruit of choice.
Chill in refrigerator until set or overnight. Serves 10 to 12.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine mayonnaise, pickle, onion, parsley and pimento into a bowl; mix well.
Chill until serving time.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into a long baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salmon mousse
directions: Mix ingredients together and place in well-greased mold. Serve with crackers or French bread (baguette).

title: no-bake drop cookies
directions: In heavy saucepan, stir together sugar and cocoa; stir in milk.
Add butter and corn syrup; bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Boil vigorously for 3 minutes.
Stir in peanut butter until smooth.
Stir in rolled oats until well combined. Return mixture to boiling.
Remove from heat; beat until slightly thickened.

title: kansas dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies and put 1/2 crumbs in 9 x 13 - inch pan.
Mix cream cheese and butter until smooth.
Mix in powdered sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In a separate bowl, mix pudding, milk, and vanilla. Fold 2 mixtures together and pour into pan on crumbs.
Spread remaining crumbs over top.
Can be served, frozen or chilled.
Very good!

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Cream butter flavored Crisco, sugar, brown
sugar,
egg and vanilla in large bowl.
Combine flour, salt and soda and blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate bits and drop level tablespoon onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 8 minutes.
Cool on baking sheet for 1 minute and place on wire rack to finish cooling.

title: italian sausage pasta soup
directions: Place sausage links into large saucepan.
Add 1/2-inch water. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Drain. Cut into slices.
Return to saucepan.
Add tomatoes, chicken broth, tomato sauce, basil and oregano.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add pasta and vegetables. Cover.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: lasagna
directions: Simmer over medium-low heat for 30 minutes to 1 hour. Cook and drain 9 lasagna noodles.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, layer sauce, noodles, grated Mozzarella cheese, sauce, noodles, cheese, sauce, noodles, cheese, finishing with the cheese and maybe a little Parmesan cheese sprinkled on top.
Cover with foil and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chili soup
directions: Cook and drain ground chuck.
In a large saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Heat and serve.

title: chicken salad
directions: Drain all ingredients and toss together.
Serve on crisp lettuce.

title: zucchini supreme
directions: Do not peel squash.
Slice thin.
Put all ingredients in a casserole and mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Put bread crumbs on top.

title: ruby workman's pie crust
directions: Cut in shortening with flour, salt and sugar.
Beat egg, vinegar and water all together and add to mixture.
Roll out as usual for pies.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mixture will be rather stiff; then mix next 4 ingredients and pour on top of first layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Mix
as if you were making biscuit dough;
knead
on
a floured
surface and roll out real thin with
a
rolling
pin. Cut into 1 inch squares.
Drop into
thickened,
boiling
hot chicken broth and boil until dumplings are done.

title: chocolate-quick oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute; remove from heat.
Add the next 3 ingredients; stir until well coated.
Spoon onto wax paper, foil, etc.
Keep in fridge until firm, about 1 hour.
Ready to serve.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: In a large pan, bring pineapple and syrup to a boil.
Stir in gelatin.
Cool to room temperature.
Stir in buttermilk; fold in whipped topping and nuts.
Pour into an 8-cup mold.
Chill 4 hours or overnight.

title: double apple pie(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place apples in large bowl.
Coat apples with flour.
In small saucepan combine apple juice, cornstarch, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir until smooth.
Cook until thickened.
Pour mixture over apples, mixing gently.
Line pie pan with bottom half of crust.
Add apple mixture to pie pan.
Place top crust on top and crimp edges.
Cut several slits in crust. Bake for 10 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 375° and bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add liquid. Beat 1 minute. Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: south seas chicken
directions: In a bowl, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt; gradually add vinegar, then soy sauce, pineapple with syrup, green pepper and onion; set aside.
In a large skillet, melt shortening.
Add chicken pieces and brown on both sides.
Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes or until tender.
Remove chicken from skillet; add pineapple-green pepper mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Place rice on serving platter; top with chicken and sauce.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: squash on the grill
directions: Wash squash and cut off ends.
Do not peel squash.
Slice squash lengthwise but do not cut through.
Cut spring onion and insert into squash.
Add butter, salt and pepper.
Wrap in aluminum foil tightly so butter will not leak out.
Put on grill and cook until soft, turning often.
Can be baked in oven.
Great with barbecue chicken.

title: favorite sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, 2 tablespoons plus 2 teaspoons melted butter, salt, milk and eggs in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole.
Mix brown sugar, pecans, flour and remaining butter in bowl.
Sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May add 1 teaspoon vanilla extract to sweet potatoes, if desired.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: low-fat sausage
directions: Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Form into patties.
Grill or pan fry until done.

title: brunch egg casserole
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Mix 5 top ingredients; put in blender.
Pour over bread cubes.
Shred Cheddar cheese over eggs. Sprinkle bacon crumbs over cheese.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.
Cut like cake.

title: hot chocolate heaven
directions: Gently heat half and half in saucepan until simmering. Remove from heat. Add chocolate and vanilla. Let stand 1 minute. Whisk until smooth.
Makes 8 servings.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour
three 9-inch cake pans. Sift flour, sugar, salt and cocoa together.
Add buttermilk, oil, eggs and vanilla to dry ingredients.
Mix together with mixer until well blended.
Blend in red food coloring.
Finally, mix vinegar and soda together and blend into other mixture.
Mix at medium speed only until well blended.
Pour into pans and bake 30 to 35 minutes. Cool.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: salsa dip and chips
directions: Microwave cheese spread and salsa in 1 1/2-quart bowl on High 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Stir after 3 minutes.
Serve hot with chips or cauliflower spears.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients. Beat eggs. Add sugar, vanilla and oil.
Mix well.
Stir in grated zucchini. Add dry ingredients and blend. Stir in nuts. Bake in two greased loaf pans, 9 1/2 x 5 1/2-inch, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken and cheese.
Place this mixture on crescent dinner rolls and roll up.
Arrange in casserole.

title: yam pie
directions: Combine egg yolks, mashed yams, firmly packed brown sugar, salt, melted butter, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Blend well.
Add milk. Blend in egg whites (beaten until they peak).
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes.
Serve warm or cool.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine fruits and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Fold and blend gently.
Decorate with red maraschino cherries.
Chill overnight.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Prepare yellow cake mix as usual.
Let cool.
Mix in bowl strawberry gel and strawberries cut in halves.
Spread on top of cake. Spread the whipped topping around cake.
Ready to serve.

title: very special jello salad
directions: Melt marshmallows and lime jello in 7 cups boiling water. Stir until completely dissolved.
Set aside to congeal.

title: stuffed meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, cracker crumbs and egg together.
Form meatballs around cheese cubes.
Chill for 1 hour or so.
Brown in oil and serve hot.

title: wicked cinnamon rolls(low-fat)
directions: Make the Pastry Dough.
Sprinkle flour onto a countertop. Place the dough on top.
Sprinkle enough flour on top of the dough to keep it from sticking to your rolling pin.
Roll the dough flat until it's about 1/4 inch thick.
Work the corners with the rolling pin and try to get a rectangular shape rather than a circle.

title: potato-onion surprise
directions: Wash potatoes thoroughly.
Slice potatoes approximately 1/8 inch.
In plastic bag, put onion soup mix, potatoes and oil. Shake bag to coat potatoes.
Layer evenly in baking dish all potatoes.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Fast and easy.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Combine shortening, salt, vanilla and one cup sugar.
Add remaining milk and sugar alternately.
Mix until smooth and creamy.
Add more sugar to thicken or more milk to thin.

title: spinach salad
directions: Toss spinach, eggs, bacon and bean sprouts together.
Garnish with croutons.
Serve with salad dressing.

title: green rice
directions: Steam rice and add oil, parsley and onion and let stand 1/2 hour.
Add cheese, salt and beaten egg yolk.
Mix together and fold in beaten egg whites carefully.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish for 1 hour at 325°.
Place baking dish in a pan of water to bake.
Serve with creamed chicken, turkey, tuna, crab or shrimp. Serves 8.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook and stir hamburger, sausage, onion, garlic salt, parsley, oregano and sugar.
Cook 8 to 10 lasagna noodles.
Layer in greased 9 x 13-inch pan hamburger mixture, cottage cheese, Mozzarella, noodles, Parmesan.
Repeat.
Sprinkle leftover Mozzarella on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and cheese melts (about 30 minutes).
Can be made ahead and refrigerated.
Serves 10.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Chop vegetables.
Mix all ingredients in kettle.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat for 45 minutes or until vegetables are crisp and tender.
Place in hot, sterilized jars; seal.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry pecan cake
directions: Mix cake mix and jello; add Wesson oil, milk and eggs.
Blend well.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into 3 cake pans.
Bake at 350°.

title: linguine with clam sauce
directions: Cook onions in butter until tender; add garlic.
Continue to stir until garlic is tender, then add olive oil.
Add clams (and juice) along with all other ingredients except for white wine and parsley.
Continue to stir; add parsley and white wine.
Simmer on a low heat for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole with marshmallows
directions: Wash sweet potatoes; boil until tender.
Mash as you would Irish potatoes.
Add butter, salt and vanilla.
If too dry, add enough milk to make like mashed potatoes.
Pile half into a buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with half of brown sugar and press enough marshmallows to cover casserole on top of mixture.
Pour remaining mixture; add rest of brown sugar, then again press enough marshmallows to cover casserole.
Bake in moderate oven until marshmallows are brown.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend well.
(Use a little buttermilk if needed.)

title: tacos
directions: Fry hamburger; salt and pepper to taste. Fry tortillas in hot oil about 15 seconds per side.
Fill with chopped tomatoes, diced onions, shredded lettuce and cheese, beans and your favorite taco sauce.
Makes 12.

title: summer cake
directions: Prepare Jell-O as directed but omit the cold water.
Do not refrigerate.
Let set at room temperature.
Bake cake, using a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool.
Poke holes in cake.
Pour Jell-O over cake and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Frost with Cool Whip before serving.

title: canned apple pie filling
directions: Cook all ingredients until thick.
Fill quart jar 1/2 full of sliced apples.
Put some sauce in jar to cover apples.
Fill jar with more apples, then more sauce.
Fill to 1-inch top of jar. Makes 6 to 7 quarts.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer lettuce, carrots, onions, celery, green peas and cheese. Spread mayonnaise to cover top of dish.
Sprinkle bacon on top. Refrigerate overnight.

title: sweet potatoes with pineapple
directions: Cook potatoes until tender; drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Let boil 5 minutes.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Bring sugar and milk mixture to a full boil and cook to soft-ball stage (238° to 240° on candy thermometer).
Remove from heat and add margarine and vanilla. Beat until thickened but still pourable.
Pour over cake. (You can add a small amount of milk if it is too thick.)

title: peach ice cream
directions: Put peaches in blender; beat well.
Add rest of ingredients. Pour into freezer can.
Finish filling freezer can to make 1 gallon.

title: pedernales river chili
directions: Place chili meat, onion, garlic and bacon drippings in a heavy or Dutch pan.
Cook until light colored.
Add oregano, cumin seed, chili powder, tomatoes, beans, hot sauce, dried mushrooms, salt and hot water.
Bring to boil, lower heat and simmer for 1 hour.
Skim off fat during cooking.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt bark chocolate and chips in microwave.
Add peanuts. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Makes about 70 to 75.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt over cucumbers and onions. Soak 2 hours.
Drain off.
Mix vinegar, sugar and celery seed until completely dissolved.
Pour over cucumbers and onions.
Put in containers and freeze. Take out in time to thaw before serving; better served cold.
Delicious.
Tastes like bread and butter pickles.

title: cindy's punch(great for a shower)
directions: Stir together all ingredients except ice cream and ginger ale. Let sit for 1 hour in refrigerator.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale and stir.
Then add ice cream in scoops so that they float on top.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Pour 3 tablespoons sugar over the blueberries.
Let the sugar and blueberries come to a boil.
Mix together flour, 3 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon and add to blueberries slowly.
Cook until mixture thickens and pour into a baked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine. Refrigerate until set. Roll into ball. Roll into pecans. Serve with crackers.

title: frosting
directions: Cook milk and cornstarch until thick.
Mix butter (or oleo), shortening and sugar.
Beat for 10 minutes using electric mixer. Add cornstarch mixture after cooling.
Add vanilla.
Beat until smooth.

title: rocky road brownies
directions: Mix first three ingredients well.
Add eggs, vanilla, nuts and flour.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cover top with marshmallows.
Bake 5 minutes more, cool.

title: peanut butter candy cake
directions: Combine water and rolled oats; cool to room temperature.
Set aside.
Cream together butter, brown sugar, sugar and vanilla. Beat in eggs.
Blend in oatmeal mixture.
Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt; add to creamed mixture. Beat 1 minute on medium speed; pour batter into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chop peanut butter cups and sprinkle on top of batter (do not stir).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: savory spaghetti sauce
directions: In Dutch oven, cook ground beef and onion until meat is browned and onion is tender; drain.
Add the next eight ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Remove the bay leaf.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: creamy broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions, omitting salt and set aside.
Combine milk and margarine in medium saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thoroughly heated (do not boil).
Stir in potato flakes and onion.
Place in container of an electric blender; add broccoli and process for 30 seconds.
Scrape down sides; process an additional 30 seconds or until almost smooth.

title: lace cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar. Then beat egg.
Beat well.
Add rest of ingredients and stir well.
Drop by small teaspoon on heavy duty aluminum foil on cookie sheet.
Bake 7 minutes at 375°.
Remove foil with cookies on it and place on cake racks to cool 3 to 4 minutes.
Then peel off foil.
Wipe the aluminum foil clean and place on cookie sheet for next batch of cookies.
Makes about 250 cookies.

title: baked chicken breast supreme
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 8 ingredients.
Place chicken in mixture and turn to coat.
Cover and marinate overnight in the refrigerator.
Remove chicken and coat with crumbs.
Arrange in a shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, or until juices run clear.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with chicken. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove foil last 1/2 hour to brown chicken.

title: ooh-la-la meat loaf
directions: Saute onion, celery and green pepper in butter until tender. Stir in chili sauce.
Combine 1/2 cup of this mixture with lean ground beef, bread crumbs and egg, beaten with salt.
Form into loaf and place in 8 x 4 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.
Serve remaining sauce cold or heated over sliced meat loaf.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Put hamburger in large soup pot.
Add onion and water to cover burger.
Cook over medium heat for 45 minutes.
Add potatoes and carrots.
Cook until vegetables are done.
Add remaining vegetables.
Salt and pepper to taste. Add tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Simmer over low heat for several hours.

title: ice cream squares
directions: Sprinkle half of the nuts on bottom of baking pan.
Cut ice cream into 1-inch slices.
Place on the nuts.
Let stand until slightly softened.
Spread evenly with half of each topping. Sprinkle other nuts on top and freeze until firm, about 6 hours. Serve with additional topping.
Cut into squares.

title: almond squares
directions: Cream butter in large mixing bowl.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolk and almond paste and extract.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in flour.
Spread mixture in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Beat egg white until foamy. Brush over entire surface of dough and sprinkle with almonds. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool thoroughly and cut into 2-inch squares.
Store in airtight containers.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: microwave broccoli casserole
directions: Cut an X on boxes of broccoli and cook in box on High for 10 minutes.
Cut corner off box and drain well.

title: molded chicken salad(american)
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water.
Dissolve in hot broth.
Add mayonnaise, chicken and pimentos.
Turn into mold and chill.
Serve with biscuits.

title: tender fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken.
Mix flour and garlic pepper together.
Melt oil in skillet until slightly hot (when bubbles form from water).
Dip chicken in buttermilk, then roll in flour mixture.
Let brown on both sides, then put brown chicken in baking dish and cover.
Bake in oven for 20 minutes or until tender at 350°.

title: beef fried rice
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat lightly.
Add onion, green peppers and oil.
Cook until the onion is tender.
Stir in rice, water chestnuts, mushrooms and soy sauce.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in beaten eggs.
Cook 2-3 minutes longer.

title: butterhorns
directions: Heat milk to scalding.
Add shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and stir until dissolved.
Add eggs and flour; mix to a smooth, soft dough.
Knead lightly on floured surface.
Place dough in a greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in moderately warm place until double in size.

title: taco salad
directions: Fry beef.
Drain and rinse off fat.
Add taco seasoning.
Set aside to cool.
In very large bowl, dice or chop tomatoes, peppers, lettuce and onions.
Stir together all ingredients except the Fritos.
When ready to serve, crunch the Fritos slightly and stir into salad.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place unbaked pie crust in 9-inch glass pie dish according to instructions on box.
Meanwhile in skillet, cook bacon until crisp, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings.
Crumble bacon finely and set aside.
Cook sliced onion in reserved drippings until tender; drain.
In bowl thoroughly stir together eggs, cream, milk, flour, salt and nutmeg.
Stir in onion, bacon and cheese; mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
If necessary, cover edge of crust with foil to prevent overbrowning.
Bake in 325° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until set in center.
Let stand 10 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: apple squares
directions: Cook for 10 to 15 minutes, until thick.

title: slaw
directions: Boil two minutes and pour over first mixture.
Refrigerate for four hours or overnight.

title: cheese and spinach
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Add the sour cream.
Put in a casserole dish; let it set in refrigerator overnight.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil well.
Add bananas, pineapple and nuts and stir.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Flour cake pan; pour batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Cool about 30 minutes.

title: hunter's venison roast
directions: Sprinkle meat with salt and Accent.
Mix other ingredients; pour over meat in pan.
Cook at 300° to 350 for 3 to 4 hours, until meat is done and very tender.
Add small amounts of water as necessary.
Make gravy after removing meat.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion; drain.
Add other ingredients.
Heat and serve.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Blend all together slowly in mixer or blender.
Makes 5 pints.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: rum cake
directions: Put pecans in bottom of bundt pan. Mix all other ingredients together and pour over pecans in bundt pan. Bake for 1 hour at 325 degrees.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake mix on edged cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until golden brown.
Let cool before topping.

title: ham, potato and onion casserole
directions: Melt drippings or butter.
Blend in flour and add milk, stirring constantly.
Cook mixture until thickened, boiling about 3 minutes.
Add cooked ham, potatoes and onions.
Pour mixture into a greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake uncovered in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until crumbs are lightly brown.

title: no-fail pie crust
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt; mix well.
Cut in shortening and blend until mixture resembles small particles. Break egg into measuring cup and add enough water to measure 1 cup.
Using a fork, mix egg and water well.
Pour slowly over dry ingredients and mix just long enough to form dough.
Do not overmix.
This makes a large amount of pie dough.

title: luscious layered blueberry delight
directions: Line 9-inch pan with whole graham crackers, breaking if necessary.
Prepare pudding and let stand 5 minutes, then blend in whipped topping.
Spread half the pudding mixture over the crackers.
Add another layer of crackers.
Spread rest of pudding mixture, then spread pie filling over top.
Chill 3 hours.

title: rhubarb marmalade
directions: Set rhubarb and sugar in refrigerator overnight.
Cook until transparent or cooked-up.
Stir in strawberry jello.
Put in jars and freeze.

title: pineapple refrigerator cake
directions: Soak gelatine in water for 5 minutes.
Heat pineapple to boiling; add gelatine.
Stir until dissolved and then add sugar and lemon juice.
Chill until it begins to thicken.

title: beef log(or summer sausage)
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
in
bowl.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove
once
a
day for 3 days.
Knead well for 5 minutes.
On 4th day divide into 6 or 7 rolls.
Lay on broiler pan with drip pan under it.
Bake 9 hours at 160°.
Turn over rolls in
4 1/2 hours.
At 9th hour, remove and wrap in paper towel to remove grease.
Roll in handy wrap, freeze or refrigerate.
Will keep in refrigerator 3 weeks.

title: honey-mustard glazed sausage kabobs
directions: Cut sausage into 24 pieces.
Cut peppers and onion into 1-inch pieces.
Arrange sausage and vegetables on 6 (12-inch) metal skewers.

title: bacon cheddar puffs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Bring milk and margarine to boil over medium heat.
Add flour all at once, stirring constantly until mixture forms ball and leaves side of pan.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs and stir until mixture is smooth.
Add remaining ingredients. Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased, foil-lined cookie sheet.
Bake 25 minutes or until puffed and golden brown.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: old cheese wafers
directions: Sift flour with salt and pepper. Cream margarine and mix in nuts and cheese and flour. Mold into long, slender roll about 1 inch in diameter and wrap roll in wax paper. Chill for several hours. Slice into 1/4 to 1/2 inch slices and back at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: willeta's homemade bread
directions: Put 1/2 cup hot water in a cup with yeast and 1 tablespoon honey.
Stir well and set aside for 15 to 20 minutes until raised and bubbly.
Put remaining 2 1/2 cups hot water in large bowl with salt, oil and 1/3 cup honey.
When yeast is bubbly, add to large bowl.
Add whole wheat flour.

title: orange punch
directions: Mix well.
Ready to serve at once.

title: chocolate fudge cream pie
directions: Mix in double boiler or heavy saucepan sugar and flour.
Add and cook until thick milk and chocolate square. Remove from heat and add egg yolks.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes more.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cool slightly.
Pour into baked shell and top with meringue.
Brown meringue and cool, the keep in refrigerator. Double for a 10-inch thick pie.

title: aunt matte's pie crust
directions: Blend flour, Crisco and salt. Mix in egg.
Mix vinegar and water then add to flour mixture.
Roll out as needed.

title: best ever chocolate pie
directions: Mix and press into a greased pie plate.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup finely chopped pecans over crust.
Bake at 325° until lightly browned.

title: toffee
directions: Butter a
x	9
x 2-inch pan.
Spread pecans in pan. Heat sugar
and margarine to boiling in a saucepan.
Boil over medium heat
for
7 minutes.
Immediately spread mixture over pecans in pan.

title: antipasto pasta salad
directions: Set aside dressing mix.
In 2 quarts boiling water, cook pasta and vegetables package, stirring occasionally, 9 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water until chilled; drain.
In bowl, blend dressing mix, water and reserved marinade.
Add pasta and vegetables, artichokes, salami and onion; toss.
Serves 4.

title: dumplings for sauerkraut
directions: Mix all together.
Spoon about 4 mounds over boiling sauerkraut.
Cook about 1/2 hour.

title: unfried green tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix together cornmeal, paprika, salt and black pepper.
Put green tomatoes in egg whites and mix well. Dip each tomato slice in cornmeal mix.
Spray cookie sheet with vegetable cooking spray 3 times.
After the green tomatoes are laid out, spray the vegetable spray on top of the green tomatoes. Bake until golden brown, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: carrot-lemon bread
directions: Grind peeling, pulp and all of lemon.
Beat eggs; add oil and sugar.
Mix well.
Add carrots and lemon and blend.
Mix dry ingredients and add to others, just to blend.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: christmas tea
directions: Stir and store in airtight container.
Mix 2 teaspoons per cup boiling water.

title: fluffy french toast
directions: Dip bread in mixture made of first 5 ingredients, then fry in butter.
Makes 6 to 8 pieces.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Place sugar on bottom of 9 x 14-inch pan.
Add the next 3 ingredients in layers.
Melt butter and pour over dry cake mix. Sprinkle pecans on top, if desired.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for about 1 hour or until when tested, it is done.

title: my grandma's cornbread dressing
directions: Precook celery and onion over low heat until almost tender. Combine all ingredients.
Pour broth over.
Mix lightly with a wooden spoon.
Turn into a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Sprinkle thickly with cheese.
Bake at 375° until cheese is bubbly.

title: south of the border casserole
directions: Saute zucchini and onion in butter until tender crisp. Fold in chilies, flour, salt and pepper.
Place in 2-quart green baking dish. Sprinkle with Mozzarella.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring 1/2 cup water to boil.
Add 1 box 10x sugar and boil 5 minutes exactly.
Remove from heat and add marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into greased pan. Cool, cut and eat.

title: chess cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: lime pickles
directions: Soak in solution 24 hours, stirring 2 to 3 times.
Drain and wash well.
Cover with cold water.
Let stand 3 hours.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix butter,
Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Blend in cream of tartar, baking
soda, salt and flour.
Roll dough mixture into balls (small).
Roll balls in cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Bake in 400° preheated oven for 8 to 10 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: taco soup 2
directions: Brown ground beef and onion, drain.
Transfer to large pot. Add all other ingredients and let simmer for 1 hour.
Serve over corn chips in bowl.
Top with sour cream, grated sharp cheddar or mexican cheese, chopped onion.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Separate eggs; beat yolks.
Add dry ingredients and blend well.
Add lemon and rind gradually and add milk.
Cook until thick; remove from burner, add butter and cool.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue (use the separated egg whites). Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: potato cheese bacon
directions: Cook bacon until partially done.
Remove from fat; drain. Combine potatoes, onion, mayonnaise, onion and cheese.
Pour into casserole dish, top with bacon, cut in pieces.
Top with olive slices (optional).
Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sausage and corn chowder
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Saute onion and bell pepper in small amount sausage grease until done about 8 to 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and bring almost to a boil.
Serve with your favorite bread.

title: lima-pear casserole
directions: Soak limas as directed by package.
Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot and bake for 8 hours or longer.
Or use a heavy casserole with a tight fitting lid and bake in 200° oven for 8 hours or longer.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chinese cabbage salad
directions: In a saucepan, mix together salad oil, sugar, soy sauce and white vinegar.
Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Saute noodles (break them up), almonds and sesame seed in 1/4 stick of butter or margarine.
Drain on paper towel.

title: sugarless cake
directions: Mix above ingredients with buttermilk or sweet milk.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until done.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and chop artichoke hearts and mix with cheese and mayonnaise.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cube steak swiss style
directions: Combine flour, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Cut steaks into 12 pieces.
Coat with flour and brown well in oil in a large skillet. Add tomato sauce, 1 cup water, celery, onion, garlic, Worcestershire sauce and sugar.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger.
Mix with pinto beans and tortilla chips. Put lettuce on plate.
Add cheese, onions, tomatoes, hamburger and beans; top with salsa.

title: strawberries and cream(diet)
directions: Combine Sugar Twin, whipped cream and strawberry jam in small mixing bowl and mix with electric mixer.
Pour over strawberries.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Fry,
crumble
and
drain
sausage well.
Spread evenly into 9 x
13-inch
pan
or
dish.
Sprinkle cheese over.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over sausage and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until set and lightly browned. Cool 5
minutes before slicing.
Yields 12 (3-inch) squares or 36 (1 x 3-inch) bars for appetizers.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Cover and refrigerate a few hours before serving.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid (Mountain Berry
or
Tropical)
in
gallon jar. Add water and sugar and stir.
Add	juice and stir.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Yields 50 cups.

title: peppermint torte
directions: Cook first three ingredients on low heat; melt and stir. Gradually add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Whip with wire whisk. Add additional water, 1/2 teaspoon at a time, to thin out glaze. Drizzle top and sides of cake.

title: brandy cream cups
directions: Spread chocolate smoothly around inside of 20 to 25 petit four cases.
Chill hard and peel off paper.

title: shipwreck
directions: Put in layers in order as listed.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a covered baking dish.

title: moist and tasty meatballs
directions: Mix cornflakes, diced onion, ground beef, salt, pepper, egg and applesauce.
Shape into balls (about 24).
Place meatballs in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover with mixture of the soup, water and tomato juice.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: pickled shrimp
directions: Arrange shrimp and sliced onions in layers in a large bowl. Mix other ingredients together and pour over shrimp.
Cover and store in refrigerator not less than 24 hours before serving. (These can be kept one week.)

title: hot cocoa for a crowd
directions: *May be reduced if too sweet or chocolaty.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni, then drain.
Mix with tuna, tomato, mayonnaise, garlic salt and onion in
a large bowl.
Chill in refrigerator before serving.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spread coconut on bottom of well-greased 11 x 15 x 2-inch pan. Spread pecans over coconut.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions (adding the ingredients called for on box). Pour cake mix over top of coconut and nuts.
Mix softened oleo, cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Drop by spoons in dollops on top of cake.
Do not stir.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: italian paprika fillets
directions: Lightly oil rack or broiler pan.
Grind oats in blender or food processor about 1 minute; stir.
In shallow dish, combine dry ingredients.
In another shallow dish, combine milk and egg white. Coat fillets with oat mixture; shake off excess.
Dip into egg mixture, then coat again with oat mixture.
Place onto pan; drizzle with 1 tablespoon margarine.
Broil about 4 inches from heat 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes or until golden brown.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Spoon over fish before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: texas style barbecue sauce
directions: Melt oleo and add other ingredients.
Simmer for 40 minutes. Keep in refrigerator.
Improves with age.

title: icicle pickles
directions: Wash cukes and cut lengthwise into fourths or eighths.
Soak in ice water for 3 hours.
Then drain and pack in pint size jars. Add onions, celery and 1/2 teaspoon of mustard seed to each jar. Combine vinegar, sugar, salt and water.
Bring to a boil and pour over cukes to within 1/2-inch of the top.
Seal and process in boiling water for 10 minutes.
Very crisp and delicious.
Makes 6 pints.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Mix margarine, peanut butter, powdered sugar and cereal with hands, then form into balls.

title: diane's broccoli
directions: Mix all together.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: diabetic raisin cookies
directions: Boil raisins, cinnamon, nutmeg and Crisco for 3 minutes.
When cool, add eggs, salt, flour, baking soda, baking powder, sweetener and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto baking sheet at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate cobbler
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Mix sugar and cocoa. Sprinkle over other mixture.
Bring water to boil and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: snow on the mountain cake
directions: Tear cake up into pieces about the size of your thumb.
Make pudding according to directions on the box.
Mix one container of Cool Whip into the pudding.
Put the cake into the same bowl as the pudding and stir to combine well.
When mixed, put this mixture into a flat pan.
Spread pineapple over the cake.
Top with the other container of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with the coconut.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
In a separate bowl, mix together flour and soda.
Sift 5 times.
To butter and sugar mixture, add alternately sour cream and flour mixture.
Add vanilla and lemon extract.
Whip egg whites until stiff; add 1/2 cup sugar and fold into batter.
Pour into tube pan and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: impossible cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate (9 x 1 1/4-inch).
Place milk, vanilla, eggs, sugar and baking mix in blender.
Cover and blend on high 15 seconds.
Add cream cheese.
Cover and blend on high 2 minutes.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until center is firm, 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool.
Spread cheesecake topping carefully over top.

title: fresh peach salad
directions: Mix jello with hot or cold water.
Set aside to cool. Mix cream cheese and sugar. Add jello to cream cheese and sugar mixture.
Blend well with mixer.
Add peaches and then stir in Cool Whip. Refrigerate for the salad to congeal.

title: delicious baked apples
directions: Core apples; pare strip from top of each.
Place apples in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Stir together the brown sugar and ground nutmeg; spoon into apple center.
Top each with 1 teaspoon of butter.
Pour wine into baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour, basting occasionally.
Serve warm.
If desired, top with a little sour cream and sprinkle with a little nutmeg.

title: strawberry yogurt pie
directions: Stir yogurt into whipped topping until blended well.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze 4 hours or overnight until firm.
Let stand at room temperature for 15 minutes or until pie can be easily cut. Garnish with additional whipped topping and fruit, if desired. Store leftover pie in freezer.
Makes 8 servings.

title: zippy chicken wings(microwave)
directions: Cut off wing tips at joint (save tips for soup or stew).
Cut each wing in half at joint.
On waxed paper, combine bread crumbs, red pepper and garlic salt.

title: orecchiette with broccoli rabe
directions: Trim and discard any yellow or coarse leaves and the tough stem ends from the broccoli rabe and chop the broccoli rabe coarsely.
Wash the broccoli rabe and drain it.
In a heavy skillet, cook the anchovy fillets until melted.
In a kettle of salted, boiling water, cook the orecchiette to desired tenderness, adding the broccoli rabe 1 minute before the pasta is done.
Drain the orecchiette mixture well and transfer to the skillet.
Toss the mixture until it is combined well.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Pop corn and set aside, bring other ingredients to a boil (except the baking soda).
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring often. Remove from heat, stir in baking soda.
Pour over popped corn, mixing well.
Divide into two 13 x 9-inch pans and place in a 250° oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Peanuts may be added. Cool, break apart.

title: lemon rice pudding
directions: Simmer rice, salt and sugar in milk in 2-quart saucepan until rice is soft, about 20 minutes.
Separate eggs and beat yolks. Whisk a small amount of hot milk into beaten yolks.
Blend yolks back into hot rice.
Simmer until thickened.
Remove from heat and add butter, lemon juice, grated rind and raisins.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into rice mixture.
Turn into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole and set in pan of water (1 inch deep).
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Grate nutmeg to taste on top.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Put sugar, brown sugar, syrup and water in a saucepan, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Add butter and continue cooking, without stirring, until the temperature 240° is reached or until mixture forms a soft ball when tested in cold water.
Put popped corn in a large bowl and sprinkle with salt.
Pour the hot syrup over it and mix thoroughly.
Shape in small balls.
Wrap in wax paper.

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine crab meat, salt, pepper, eggs, butter, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce in medium mixing bowl; mix well.
Combine crab meat mixture with just enough bread crumbs to shape mixture into small cakes.
Coat with bread crumbs as well.
Place on baking sheet and place in 400° oven for 20 minutes or until golden, flipping cakes over once during baking process.

title: cheese rice krispie rounds
directions: Mix grated cheese, butter and margarine well.
Add flour and mix well.
Fold in Rice Krispies.
Shape into small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten each with a fork and top with pecan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden brown around edges.

title: granmary's potato cheese soup
