directions: In a soup pot, combine chicken broth, half and half, potato flakes, 3 1/2 c. cheese, and the pepper.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil over medium high heat and cook for 2-3 minutes, or until thickened, stirring constantly.
Top with the remaining 1/2 c. cheese and 2 scallions if desired.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat the eggs, sugar, oil, cinnamon, nutmeg and ginger together with whisk. Add flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda to the whisked ingredients and mix with wooden spoon.
Add zucchini gradually.
Stir in raisins, nuts and vanilla last.
Bake at 350° in 2 loaf pans for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: blueberry muffins (1 dozen)
directions: Mix dry ingredients; stir in others.
Add blueberries last. Spray muffin pan and pour in batter.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9-inch glass pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: perfect sweet milk gravy
directions: Brown flour in drippings.
Add salt, pepper and milk.
Stir until thick.
If you like thicker gravy, use 1 tablespoon flour when browning in drippings.
Yields 1 cup of gravy.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut up squash and boil in salted water until tender. Saute in butter the chopped pepper, onion and celery. Combine the drained squash, sauteed vegetables, soups, cornbread mix and drained corn. Add 1 cup of grated cheese to mixture. Pour into greased 11 x 13 casserole dish and cover with remaining cheese. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Be sure and cover with foil and last 5 minutes take off foil and brown for 5 minutes. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: date and nut cookies
directions: Cream sugar and
margarine;
add
eggs and water.
Sift dry ingredients; add to
above.
Add
vanilla, dates and nuts. Drop by teaspoons on
greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: macaroni casserole #1
directions: Mix
soup, milk, cheese, mayonnaise, onion and pimento. Microwave
until
cheese melts.
Stir thoroughly; add macaroni and pour
into
x 13-inch casserole dish.
Cover with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: italian stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells as directed on package, drain and cool.
Mix cheese, eggs, parsley, salt and cracker meal.
Remove one shell at a time.
Stuff each shell with cheese mixture.
Pour 1 pint of spaghetti sauce into large shallow casserole.
Arrange stuffed shells on top.
Cover with second pint of spaghetti sauce.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caramel nut pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
In a large bowl cream butter and shortening.
Add the brown sugar and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating until creamy.
Sift flour and add alternately with milk and vanilla.
Blend well.
Fold in nuts. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until a cake tester inserted near center of cake comes out clean.

title: top stove meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 can of soup with beef, bread crumbs, egg, onion, salt and pepper.
Shape firmly into 2 loaves.

title: oven fries
directions: Clean
potatoes,
peel
and
slice lengthwise, 1/4-inch thick. Cut slices in half lengthwise again to form the fries. Place in a
bowl and add remaining ingredients.
Mix together well.
Spread on
Pam-sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Flip and continue baking 20 minutes more.
Serves 4.

title: transparent pie
directions: Mix in order given.
Fill an unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven until knife inserted in middle of pie comes out clean.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Cut chicken 1/4-inch chunks, season and flour lightly; slowly cook in 1/3 cup of oil until done.
In a large skillet, saute in margarine over low heat carrots, broccoli, green peppers and onions approximately 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Mix together the chicken and vegetables, serve over rice, add pineapple and sweet and sour sauce.

title: crawfish bisque
directions: Grind celery, onions, bell pepper, garlic and parsley.
Simmer in melted butter until wilted.
Add ground-up crawfish tails and green onions.
Simmer 1 minute.
Stir in seasonings, milk, eggs and bread crumbs.
Use milk, if needed, to bring mixture to consistency for handling.
Stuff heads; roll in flour and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add salt and flour; mix well.
Mix in nuts.
Roll in a ball and chill 3 to 4 hours.
Roll dough in 1-inch balls and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set, but not brown.
While still warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Cool and roll in powdered sugar again. This makes about 4 dozen 1-inch cookies.

title: one dish meal casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in butter.
Place a layer of meat in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with a layer of each vegetable and rice.
Put rice on top of meat layer.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour hot water over all.
Cover; bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Add more water or juice if needed during baking.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate syrup for hot fudge cake
directions: Melt the first 4 ingredients on stove; remove from heat.
Add the vanilla. Serve hot over chocolate sheet cake and vanilla ice cream.

title: unbelievable baked chicken
directions: Sprinkle box of salt in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Place chicken, breast side up, on top of salt.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours, uncovered.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar, beaten eggs, sour cream and lemon extract.
Sift dry ingredients and add to the first mixture. Chill about 1 hour.

title: stew
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Start cooking on high; turn to simmer. Cook for 1 hour and stir often.

title: marshmallow waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle apples with lemon juice. Add marshmallows, celery, nuts and enough mayonnaise to moisten.
Toss lightly. Serve on lettuce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: corn bread cake
directions: Sift together the flour and sugars.
Mix the eggs, vanilla and oil.
Add the nuts and mix by hand.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Good plain or use cream cheese icing to keep it moist.

title: southern sweet potato pie
directions: Scrub potatoes; place in saucepan.
Cover with boiling water and cook until soft.
Pour off water and peel potatoes while hot. Mash thoroughly, then beat in butter, eggs, sugar, salt and nutmeg.
Beat until creamy.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until set.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Mix sugar and Karo syrup and heat to a rolling boil.
Add peanut butter and pour over cornflakes.
Drop onto wax paper.
Eat and enjoy.

title: smoked salmon
directions: Mix first six ingredients together.
Shape into log and wrap in foil.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Roll in chopped pecans with chopped parsley.

title: lumpy green goop
directions: Put pineapple in a bowl.
Put pistachio pudding on top and stir.
Mix in Cool Whip, marshmallows and pecans.
Mix well. Refrigerate.
Enjoy!

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine into baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk. Pour mixture into margarine.
Next pour peaches on mixture.
Pour 1 cup sugar over peaches.
Pour juice over sugar.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hamburger delight
directions: Put rice in bottom of baking dish.
Sprinkle hamburger meat over rice.
Sprinkle onion over hamburger meat.
Add mushrooms and then tomatoes.
Pour mushroom soup over tomatoes.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Add margarine, sugar, syrup and cocoa together.
Cook on low heat.
Bring to a boil until it forms a soft ball in cold water. Add milk and vanilla.
Beat until firm.
Add pecans.
Spread in lightly greased dish.

title: easy crab stew
directions: Dice onion and celery.
Saute in butter and Worcestershire sauce and cook until tender.
Add crab, soup and milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly.
(Do not bring to a boil.)
Salt and pepper to taste.
For thinner soup, add equal amounts of whole and evaporated milk.
Serve hot.

title: our favorite goulash
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Cook beef and onion in 1 tablespoon of butter.
Add remaining ingredients, except bread crumbs and mix well.
Put in pan.
Mix crumbs in 3 tablespoons of melted butter and sprinkle over top.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: company broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli by package directions, then drain.
Combine with next 5 ingredients; mix well.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish. Top with cracker crumbs and dribble butter or margarine on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until browned.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and grate or chop the pepper, onion and carrots. Combine the vegetables and the celery seed.
Simmer the oil, vinegar and sugar together.
Pour over the vegetables while hot. Mix well.
This can be made a day ahead.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Blend the Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice together, then add all the other ingredients together.
Mix well.
Pour into graham cracker crusts.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease baking sheet.
Combine Crisco, sugar, egg, milk and vanilla.
Mix until creamy and smooth.
Combine oats, flour, soda, salt and cinnamon in large bowl.
Slowly add dry ingredients to creamy mixture until well blended.
Add raisins and/or nuts, if desired.
Drop rounded spoonfuls on baking sheet and bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: date pinwheels
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar.
Add eggs, then mix in dry ingredients.
Divide dough into 4 parts.
Roll each part into a long rectangle.
Spread with date filling.
Roll from the long side.
Cover and chill.
Then slice and bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil 1 large fryer chicken in 4 cups water.
Debone and chop chicken.
Retain 2 cups broth.
Spread chopped chicken in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Add in layers: cream of chicken soup, English peas, dried onions, mushroom soup, first cup of broth, almonds, crushed noodles and second cup of broth.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until bubbly and the cheese melts. Serves 8 to 10.

title: baked chili meat balls
directions: Combine all ingredients except soup and hot water.
Form into 10 or 12 balls.
Roll in flour and brown in hot olive oil.
Place in a 2-quart casserole.
Combine soup and hot water.
Pour over meat balls.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: french onion soup(ultra low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large skillet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray, brown onions until golden brown.
Sprinkle flour over onions and continue browning and stirring.
In a medium saucepan, combine beef broth, water, Molly McButter, wine, salt and black pepper.
Add onions and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour soup into individual bowls; top with 1 slice of toast and 1 slice of cheese.
Warm at 375° until cheese starts to melt.
Serve immediately.
Recipe makes 6 servings.

title: corn pone
directions: Place meal, sugar and salt in a bowl.
Add boiling water and stir until smooth.
Let stand overnight or mix early morning and bake in the evening.
In morning, add flour, buttermilk, eggs, baking powder and soda.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine all ingredients and spoon into a buttered baking dish.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, margarine and sugar. Add 1 egg yolk at a time, beating well after each addition. Mix flour, salt and baking powder and add to batter alternately with milk. Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold them into batter along with the flavorings. Grease a Bundt pan well and sprinkle with flour, dusting entire pan. Pour batter into pan and strike pan on a flat surface to rid the batter of bubbles. Start baking process in a cold oven set on 325° and bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onions and pepper in margarine (may also add chopped mushrooms).
Cook vermicelli in leftover broth and drain.
Debone chicken in bite size pieces.
Add cheese and Ro-Tel to sauteed mix to melt.
Mix all together well.
Bake, covered, in a 2-quart casserole dish at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Set aside. Mix dry ingredients. Cut in shortening. Add remaining ingredients and yeast. Mix well. Refrigerate until chill. Roll out and cut in rounds. Bake slowly at 200°. Mixture can be stored for 2 weeks.

title: eggplant crab casserole
directions: Brown onion
and
celery in butter.
Drain eggplant and beat with mixer.
In large bowl, mix eggplant, eggs, onion and celery. Add
crab
and
1 cup bread crumbs; put in casserole. Sprinkle with
remaining
bread
crumbs.
Bake
at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: vanilla frosting
directions: Beat butter and shortening at medium speed with an electric mixer; gradually add sugar, beating mixture until light and fluffy.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Yields 3 cups.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat first three ingredients until creamy.
Beat in water, egg and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients; mix well.
Cover. Chill about 2 hours.

title: apple butter
directions: Combine ingredients in large slow cooker.
Cover and cook on high 8-10 hours.
Remove lid after first 4 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: vegetable chili(very low-fat)
directions: Cut green pepper, onion and celery into large pieces.
Slice mushrooms.
Slice carrots into short thin strips.
spray Pam on bottom of large soup pot.
Saute all vegetables.
Add Chili-O mix and stir.
Add can of water.
Add all beans (undrained), tomato sauce and stewed tomatoes (undrained).
Add garlic salt and chili powder.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve as is or over rice.

title: molded royal anne fruit salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Let cool.
Add ginger ale and sherry.
Drain fruit and add to mixture.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together butter and sugar, add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla extract.
Mix in a large bowl flour, salt and baking soda. Combine butter mixture along with flour mixture.
Spoon in chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on a cookie rack.
Yields 4 dozen cookies.

title: seashell salad
directions: Cook pasta till tender, drain, and cool.
Add cucumbers, onion, green pepper and pimentos, in large bowl.
In medium bowl mix soup sugar, oil, vinegar.
Pour 1 cup of dressing over pasta mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Add rest of dressing and toss before serving.

title: salted nut rolls
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and egg.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Place miniature marshmallows on top and return to oven for 3 minutes.
Melt peanut butter chips, corn syrup and margarine; add vanilla.
Pour over peanuts and Rice Krispies.
Put over marshmallows.
Refrigerate.

title: divinity
directions: Combine frosting mix, corn syrup, vanilla and boiling water in small bowl.
Mix at high speed 5 minutes, or until stiff peaks form.
Turn into a large bowl and blend in powdered sugar at low speed.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Let stand until surface feels firm.
Turn candy over and let stand 12 hours. Store in airtight container.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus and reserve liquid.
Add mushroom soup, diluted with 2 tablespoons of asparagus liquid.
Brown bread crumbs in butter.
Put asparagus mixture in casserole dish and bake in a 300° oven for 15 minutes.
Cover with bread crumbs and brown.

title: wassail
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil.
Add spices and boil for 15 minutes.
Remove spices from water, add to juices and simmer. Serve warm.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in a single layer in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine all ingredients in a medium sized bowl. Spoon sauce over chicken. Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender and richly golden brown. Serve with rice or noodles and broccoli, if desired.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook rice with vegetable broth and water.
Cook peas.
Add rice, peas, tuna, celery and parsley in a 2-quart casserole. Blend soup, milk, basil and pepper in a small bowl; pour over tuna mixture; toss lightly to mix.
Place egg slices in a layer on top. Add melted butter and crackers on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: bleached raisin irish bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Sprinkle a little over the raisins and currants.
Cut in butter with a pastry blender, then add eggs (beaten) and milk.
Turn onto floured board and mold into round loaf.
Place in greased skillet and bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Keeps for several days and is good for tea sandwiches.

title: cornbread taco bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Brown beef in a skillet and drain. Stir in taco seasoning, water, corn, pepper and tomato sauce. Pour into a 7 x 12 glass dish or 2-quart casserole dish.

title: tom clarke's chicken liver pate
directions: Poach livers on medium-low flame in salted water with celery leaves (all the leaves from one bunch of celery) for 1 hour.

title: chocolate-peanut butter ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and remaining ingredients.
Pour into freezer can.
Add enough milk to fill as desired.
Freeze and enjoy.
THIS IS NOT LOW CALORIE!!

title: chicken livers in sour cream
directions: Roll chicken livers in flour and salt.
Heat oil and add livers; cook until brown on all sides.
Add onion rings, stirring, until browned.
Drain off excess oil and add lemon pepper, parsley and hot water.
Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Add sour cream and heat through.
Serve over toast points, white rice or noodles.

title: sausage pop-ins
directions: Cook sausage, drain and crumble.
Mix with cream cheese until spreadable.
Cut each slice of bread in half (24 rectangles). Spread sausage-cheese mixture on each rectangle.
Roll bread up and wrap one piece bacon around each.
Secure with wooden pick. Bake 35 minutes at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet.
Makes 24 snacks.

title: craft clay
directions: Combine ingredients and heat until dough-like.
Cook over medium fire.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Knead until completely cooled.
Roll until 1/8-inch thickness; cut into desired shapes.
(Can roll out with a rolling pin and use cookie cutters.) Let dry on cookie sheets, covered with wax paper.
(Waxed paper keeps "dough" cookies from sticking.)
If hole is necessary for hanging, place hole when cut into desired shapes.

title: cream cheese delight
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, margarine and pecans in bowl; mix well.
Press into 9-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Chill in refrigerator.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Prepare whipped topping using package directions.
Fold into cream cheese mixture. Spread in chilled crust.
Chill until serving time.
Spread with pie filling.
Garnish with additional whipped topping.
May substitute cherry or strawberry pie filling for blueberry.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and oil together until crumbly (save 1 cup).
Put mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; press lightly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Beat the cream cheese, 1 egg and 1/3 cup sugar until smooth.
Spread over baked layer; sprinkle the 1 cup of crumbs over top.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Cool, then cut into bars.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place in a shallow dish, 6 x 10-inch, the apples.
Sprinkle with water, cinnamon and salt.
Work together until crumbly the flour, sugar and oleo.
Spread mixture over apples.
Bake uncovered about 40 minutes, until brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: southern baked beans
directions: Cook ground beef and drain off grease.
Combine ingredients into a oblong baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.
Take out and cool for 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: western beans
directions: Lightly fry bacon in a heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Add onion; cook until transparent.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat for 45 minutes or until lentils are tender, stirring once or twice.
Remove bay leaf before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: veal scallopini
directions: Saute mushrooms in lemon juice and half of margarine.
Remove from pan; reserve.
Combine cornstarch, salt and pepper.
Cut veal into 1-inch thick strips; coat evenly with cornstarch mixture. Heat remaining margarine; brown veal in small batches.
Remove from pan; reserve.
Combine beef bouillon and water; add to pan. Add wine and garlic.
Cook, stirring for 1 minute.
Add mushrooms and veal; heat until hot.
Top with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Cook fruit in juice; add all other ingredients.
Pour into a 10-inch pie shell and cover with top crust.
Bake at 350° until browned very well.
Serve ar room temperature for best sweetness.

title: orange pineapple delight salad
directions: Mix Jell-O per box instructions and allow to partially jell. Add drained pineapple, bananas, and nuts.
Allow to completely jell.
Mix 1/2 cup of pineapple juice, 1 1/2 cups sugar, 1 teaspoon butter, 1 beaten egg, and 2 tablespoons flour.
Cook slowly until slightly thickened.
Add softened cream cheese while mixture is still warm.
When cool, add 8 ounces of Cool Whip and spread over Jell-O.
You may also add miniature marshmallows to the Jell-O if you like, and sprinkle coconut over top to make pretty.

title: quick cobbler pie
directions: Heat fruit and sugar.
Melt oleo in baking dish (9 x 13-inch). Mix dry ingredients with milk and pour batter over melted oleo; do not mix oleo and batter.
Pour fruit over batter and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: crunchy oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoons onto lightly greased foil-lined cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes.
Very healthy!

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water until dissolved.
Add cranberry sauce (after breaking it up with a fork).
Add pineapple (juice and fruit) and the lemon juice.
Chill until the consistency of egg whites.
Add apples and place in a 9-inch square dish.
Chill until set. Chopped nuts may be sprinkled on top, if desired.

title: chicken and mushrooms
directions: In a skillet, over medium heat, in 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned.
Remove chicken.
Add 1 tablespoon margarine and cook broccoli and mushrooms until tender. Add soup, milk and chicken.
Heat to boiling.
Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes until chicken is no longer pink.
Stir occasionally.
Serve over noodles.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers and butter. Place in casserole dish. Melt butter and pour over crumbled crackers. Stir until cracker crumbs are coated. Spread on top of casserole and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: fish chowder
directions: Brown onion in butter; add potatoes and 1 pint of boiling water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add fish and simmer 20 minutes.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Serves 6.

title: burritos
directions: Cook hamburger; drain.
Warm beans.
Cut tomatoes, lettuce and cheese.
Heat shells as directed.
Pile on the goodies.

title: peanut butter cup pie(weight watchers)
directions: Melt peanut butter and honey in microwave for 20 seconds.
Stir in cereal.
Pat in 9-inch pie plate.
Refrigerate for 20 minutes. Slice banana over crust.
Mix milk and pudding according to package.
Pour over banana and chill until firm.

title: ruby fulp's blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add crushed pineapple, juice and pie filling.
Mix well.
Place in refrigerator to jell. When firmly set, mix cream cheese, sour cream, sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Top congealed salad with mixture and return to refrigerator.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cook cornbread and green chilies as per directions; cool.
Mix tomatoes, onion and green pepper in small bowl.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and salad dressing mix in small bowl.
In a large casserole dish, crumble half of the cornbread and layer as follows:
tomato mixture, bacon, cheese, corn and sour cream mix. Beginning with cornbread, layer again.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight and serve cold.

title: coconut cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, cream of coconut, sugar and vanilla at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs; mix until blended.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Top with whipped topping and toasted coconut before serving.

title: spinach(microwave)
directions: Wash spinach and remove any bruised leaves or thick stems. Shake excess water off leaves.
Use a 2-quart casserole.
Place spinach.
Tightly cover and heat on Full power 5 minutes.
Stir after 2 minutes.
Drain excess water and season to taste.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: boyett cauliflower salad
directions: Thoroughly mix cauliflower, onions, olives, crumbled bacon, cheese and bell pepper.
Combine mayonnaise and Green Goddess salad dressing and pour over the salad ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Add cooked rice and cooked broccoli in a buttered baking dish, each in layers.
Put melted cheese on each layer and add cream of celery soup on each layer.
The top should have some of the cheese and celery soup.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven until top browns, about 1/2 hour or more.

title: onion chive muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 12 muffin cups.
In a small skillet, over medium heat, saute onions in 1 teaspoon oil until crisp-tender; set aside.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Boil a fryer or a hen with seasoning of your choice.
When cooked, deboned the chicken or hen and keep the broth.
Cut chicken into small, diced, pieces.
Cook two boxes of Jiffy cornbread mix and cool.

title: warm cabbage slaw
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven, combine cabbage, garlic and oil; cook over low heat for 3 to 4 minutes, tossing lightly. Cover and cook for 4 to 5 minutes or until cabbage is crisp-tender. Add onion. Combine cornstarch, water, soy sauce and salt; mix well. Pour over cabbage; toss lightly. Cook and stir for 2 to 3 minutes or until mixture thickens. Place in a serving bowl. Top with almonds. Serve warm. Yield: 12 to 16 servings.

title: bride's salad
directions: On
a
lettuce	leaf place 1 slice of pineapple.
Stand 1/2 banana
in	hole in pineapple slice.
Top with red cherry. Drip salad dressing down banana to resemble melting candle.
A strip of pepper or a date may be the handle.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix together and place in a buttered crock-pot all day on low or 4 hours on high.
Stir once.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Beat sugar, oil and egg; add salt and vanilla.
Mix soda into sour milk and add to first mixture.
Mix well.
Add flour, then rhubarb and nuts last.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans and top with crumbs made of 1/2 cup brown sugar, 1 tablespoon butter and 1/4 cup nuts.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: snack mix
directions: Pop the corn, using no salt or fat.
Combine popcorn, cereal and pretzels in a large Ziploc bag.

title: chocolate-dipped oat cookies
directions: Combine oats, sugar, oil, walnuts, egg, orange peel and salt in large bowl until blended.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook sliced carrots in salt water with a little sugar.
Place in bowl with green pepper and onion.
Heat rest of the ingredients and pour over; marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Serve at room temperature.

title: maryland fried chicken
directions: With flour, dip pieces of chicken into egg mixture, then into cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until chicken is golden brown on both sides.

title: hot turkey or chicken salad
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients. Mix mayonnaise and water until smooth.
Pour over mixture.
Add chopped eggs.
Put in greased 2 quart baking dish (shallow pan). Put in refrigerator 8 hours or overnight.
Bake
at 450° until bubbly hot.
Sprinkle with potato chips
and
cheese.
Bake
more
minutes.
Makes
8 servings.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, water and cornstarch in saucepan.
Cook until thick and add 3 tablespoons dry strawberry Jell-O.
Let cool, then add 2 cups fresh strawberries.
Pour in baked pie shell and top with Cool Whip.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In 2-quart round glass casserole, place broccoli, onion and butter; cover.
Microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes, or until broccoli is thawed.
Stir in flour and seasonings.
Gradually add broth and nondairy creamer, stirring until smooth.
Cover and microwave on medium 8 to 9 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Let stand, covered, about 3 minutes before serving.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat together oil and eggs.
Add sugar, salt, soda, and cinnamon.
Add apples, flour, and vanilla.	Beat well.
Add pecans.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until cake pulls away from side of pan.

title: hannah's dressing
directions: Mix until soupy.
Other seasoning (sage, thyme, etc.) may be added.
Better if mixed about 1 to 2 hours before cooking.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan (second pan may be needed).
Cook at 375° until firm, but moist.

title: skillet stew
directions: Cook ground beef and drain.
Add vegetables and extra liquid. Add remaining ingredients.
Cool on low heat.
Serve hot.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix together pudding and milk until thick.
Add Cool Whip and sour cream. Mix until smooth.
Pour over layers of vanilla wafers and bananas.

title: potato-ham chowder
directions: Combine all ingredients except milk and flour in a large saucepan.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil, then simmer until potatoes are fork-tender.
Set aside.
In small bowl gradually add milk to flour, stirring constantly.
Add this mixture to soup, stirring constantly.
Heat, but do not boil, until thickened.

title: pork chop and potato casserole
directions: Fry pork chops, cut away fat and grease a deep casserole dish. Place a layer of potatoes, soups, cheeses and pork chops into dish; repeat with another layer of potatoes, soups and cheeses. Dot with butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add onion, if you desire.

title: pizza bread
directions: Crumble sausage in frying pan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until sausage is done; drain.
Split bread horizontally lengthwise, but do not cut all the way through.
Spoon sauce over cut surface of bread.
Top with sausage.
Sprinkle with cheese evenly.
Close bread sandwich-style.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
To serve, unwrap.
Cut into thick slices. May use spaghetti sauce in place of tomato sauce.

title: simple basic yeast dough
directions: Add yeast to water. Let stand a few minutes. Stir to dissolve. Combine milk, butter and sugar. Cool to lukewarm. Add eggs, salt and 2 cups flour; beat thoroughly. Stir in yeast mixture. Blend in remaining flour; beat 5 minutes. Do not knead. Brush with melted shortening (1 or 2 tablespoons). Cover and let rise until double in bulk (approximately 1 hour). Turn out on lightly floured surface. Knead 1 minute. Shape into various shapes. Makes approximately 2 dozen rolls.

title: floret soup
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan and saute the garlic for about 2 minutes.
Add the tiny florets, garlic and cook for about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally until tender.
Stir pastina into the florets mixture.
Cook for 1 to 2 minutes, then add the vegetable broth and season with salt and pepper, cover and bring to a boil.
Simmer for about 10 minutes, until pastina is cooked and the florets have softened.
Serve with warm fresh bread. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chili con carne(contest winner)
directions: In large pot add oil, beef and onion.
Cook on medium heat until beef is brown.
Drain off oil.
Add other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour, stirring frequently.

title: congealed salad
directions: Let cook for 5 minutes on medium heat the crushed pineapple with juice and jello.
Let cool.
When it begins to congeal, add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Mix and refrigerate.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until melted through.

title: orange fluff
directions: Drain fruit.
Mix dry Jell-O into Cool Whip.
Fold in cottage cheese, then fruit.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: barbecue beef sandwiches
directions: Trim fat from pot roast.
Combine roast and 3/4 bottle of barbecue sauce in crock-pot on low heat for 8 hours.
Add one cup of barbecue sauce to beef mixture and stir until blended.
